{"active":false,"cklb_version":"1.0","evaluate-stig":{"version":"1.2604.2"},"has_path":true,"id":"d7e08642-b20d-4cc8-a0f1-de20f79badad","mode":1,"stigs":[{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-23T17:12:42.0000000+00:00","module":{"name":"Scan-Windows7_Checks","version":"1.2604.2"}},"stig_name":"Windows 7 Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Windows 7","stig_id":"Windows_7_STIG","release_info":"Release: 32 Benchmark Date: 17 Jun 2020","version":"1","uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","reference_identifier":"9802","size":296,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-1070","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1070","title":"Physical security","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1070","severity":"medium","group_title":"Physical security","rule_id_src":"SV-24996r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-24996","rule_version":"1.001","rule_title":"Physical security of the Automated Information System (AIS) does not meet DISA requirements.","fix_text":"Relocate equipment to a controlled access area.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Interview the SA to determine if equipment is located in an access controlled area.\n \nNote:  Servers will be located in rooms, or locked cabinets, that are accessible only to authorized systems personnel.  Authorized user access should be verified at two points (i.e. building access and server room).  User workstations containing sensitive data should be in access controlled areas.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate physical protection can undermine all other security precautions utilized to protect the system. This can jeopardize the confidentiality, availability, and integrity of the system.  Physical security of the AIS is the first line protection of any system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4476","uuid":"af1a216f-fdf8-4992-bb5e-fc2b570f734a","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 538D5B75BE282D5CE37FC777AA52EE2FBAF031C2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Physical security of the Automated Information System (AIS) does not meet DISA requirements.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1072","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1072","title":"Shared User Accounts","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1072","severity":"medium","group_title":"Shared User Accounts","rule_id_src":"SV-25000r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25000","rule_version":"1.008","rule_title":"Shared user accounts must not be permitted on the system.","fix_text":"Create or update shared accounts documentation that minimally contains the name of the shared account(s), the system(s) on which the accounts exist, and the individuals who have access to the accounts. Remove any shared accounts that do not meet the requirements.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if any shared accounts exist.  If no shared accounts exist, this is NA.\n\nAny shared account must be documented with the ISSO.  Documentation must include the reason for the account, who has access to this account, and how the risk of using a shared account (which provides no individual identification and accountability) is mitigated.  If such documentation does not exist, or is not current, this is a finding.\n\nNote:  As an example, a shared account may be permitted for a help desk or a site security personnel machine, if that machine is standalone and has no access to the network.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Shared accounts (accounts where two or more people log on with the same user identification) do not provide adequate identification and authentication.  There is no way to provide for non-repudiation or individual accountability for system access and resource usage.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000764"],"reference_identifier":"2194","uuid":"7dbe4af9-dca0-4867-bbc9-8e55dac61dcf","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CDBFDFE38C272989FACC02C5B6746C6809B55F38\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Shared user accounts must not be permitted on the system.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1073","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1073","title":"Unsupported Service Packs","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1073","severity":"high","group_title":"Unsupported Service Packs","rule_id_src":"SV-25257r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-25257","rule_version":"2.005","rule_title":"Systems must be at supported service pack (SP) or release levels.","fix_text":"Update the system to a version of the operating system supported by the vendor.\n\nSupport for Windows 2008/2008 R2 ended 14 January 2020. After this date, systems must have Windows 2012 or greater installed.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run \"winver.exe\". \n\nIf the \"About Windows\" dialog box does not display the following version or greater, this is a finding.\n\"Microsoft Windows\nVersion 6.1 (Build 7601: Service Pack 1)\"\n      \nNo Release Candidates or Beta versions will be used in a production environment. \n\nThe initial release of Windows 7 is unsupported as of 9 April 2013. Systems must be updated to Service Pack 1.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Systems at unsupported service packs or releases will not receive security updates for new vulnerabilities and leaves them subject to exploitation.  Systems must be maintained at a service pack level supported by the vendor with new security updates.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7115","uuid":"66e599fb-5bec-44c2-b088-5c27e3333b9c","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9BA59F958141E4075131780AD507DE90AC0B181A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Systems must be at supported service pack (SP) or release levels.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1074","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1074","title":"WIN00-000100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1074","severity":"high","group_title":"WIN00-000100","rule_id_src":"SV-25270r4_rule","rule_id":"SV-25270","rule_version":"WIN00-000100","rule_title":"The Windows 7 system must use an anti-virus program.","fix_text":"Install an anti-virus solution on the system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify an anti-virus solution is installed on the system. The anti-virus solution may be bundled with an approved host-based security solution.\n\nIf there is no anti-virus solution installed on the system, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Malicious software can establish a base on individual desktops and servers. Employing an automated mechanism to detect this type of software will aid in elimination of the software from the operating system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4038","uuid":"cb8d5139-b584-4053-9fc9-b709943e7fef","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 056AE40CA42FCA004D5102E2DED05E69C7ADB041\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows 7 system must use an anti-virus program.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1075","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1075","title":"Display Shutdown Button","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1075","severity":"low","group_title":"Display Shutdown Button","rule_id_src":"SV-25111r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25111","rule_version":"3.007","rule_title":"The system allows shutdown from the logon dialog box.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cShutdown: Allow system to be shutdown without having to log on\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options. \n\nIf the value for \u201cShutdown: Allow shutdown without having to log on\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  ShutdownWithoutLogon\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preventing display of the shutdown button in the logon dialog box may encourage a hard shut down with the power button.  (However, displaying the shutdown button may allow individuals to shut down a system anonymously.)","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7050","uuid":"68947c19-016e-4f5c-9a04-83749b872da0","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 832B51C5C7A2CBC5B6B2A019E31F8694A14A80C1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system allows shutdown from the logon dialog box.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1076","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1076","title":"System Recovery Backups","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1076","severity":"low","group_title":"System Recovery Backups","rule_id_src":"SV-25001r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25001","rule_version":"1.013","rule_title":"System information backups are not created, updated, and protected according to DISA requirements.","fix_text":"Implement data backup procedures that comply with DoD requirements.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Interview the SA to determine if system recovery backup procedures are in place that comply with DoD requirements.\n\nAny of the following would be a finding:\n\n\u2022The site does not maintain emergency system recovery data.\n\u2022The emergency system recovery data is not protected from destruction and stored in a locked storage container. \n\u2022The emergency system recovery data has not been updated following the last system modification.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Recovery of a damaged or compromised system in a timely basis is difficult without a system information backup.  A system backup will usually include sensitive information such as user accounts that could be used in an attack.  As a valuable system resource, the system backup should be protected and stored in a physically secure location.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1684","uuid":"5496fbd7-3c32-4b4f-9f5c-4be027791485","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EE1E9AFE5474E84B11C791DD97D09B46E5DD2695\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'System information backups are not created, updated, and protected according to DISA requirements.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1077","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1077","title":"Incorrect ACLs for event logs","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1077","severity":"medium","group_title":"Incorrect ACLs for event logs","rule_id_src":"SV-25133r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-25133","rule_version":"2.001","rule_title":"Permissions for event logs must conform to minimum requirements.","fix_text":"Maintain the permissions on the event logs.  Standard user accounts or groups must not have access.  The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nNavigate to the log file location.  The default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\System32\\winevt\\Logs\" directory.\nFor each log file below, right click the file and select \"Properties\".\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\nSelect the \"Advanced\" button, then \"Continue\", and respond to any UAC prompts.\n\nLog Files:\nApplication.evtx\nSecurity.evtx\nSystem.evtx\n\nPermissions:\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nIf the organization has an \"Auditors\" group from previous requirements, this group may be assigned Full Control.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the permissions on the event logs.  Standard user accounts or groups must not have access.  The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nNavigate to the log file location.  The default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\System32\\winevt\\Logs\" directory.\nFor each log file below, right click the file and select \"Properties\".\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\nSelect the \"Advanced\" button, then \"Continue\", and respond to any UAC prompts.\n\nLog Files:\nApplication.evtx\nSecurity.evtx\nSystem.evtx\n\nPermissions:\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nIf the permissions for the file are not as restrictive as those listed, this is a finding.\n\nIf the organization has an \"Auditors\" group from previous requirements, the assignment of Full Control permissions to this group would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Event logs may be susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164"],"reference_identifier":"1334","uuid":"8ef84f73-07ec-456e-9521-559a2a69d2f5","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 93188B3FB62B588CC6EEFFC74685144CA547632C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Permissions for event logs must conform to minimum requirements.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1081","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1081","title":"NTFS Requirement","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1081","severity":"high","group_title":"NTFS Requirement","rule_id_src":"SV-25005r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25005","rule_version":"2.008","rule_title":"Local volumes must be formatted using NTFS.","fix_text":"Format all local partitions/drives to use NTFS.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Open the Computer Management Console.\nExpand \"Storage\" in the left pane.\nSelect \"Disk Management\".\n\nIf the file system column does not indicate \"NTFS\" as the file system for each local hard drive, this is a finding.\n\nSome hardware vendors create a small FAT partition to store troubleshooting and recovery data.  No other files must be stored here.  This must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The ability to set access permissions and auditing is critical to maintaining the security and proper access controls of a system. To support this, volumes must be formatted using the NTFS file system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"1477","uuid":"9daec34a-3acc-4c21-b0f6-7e04c2efba75","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 713A9EF8004DC9171AF34A9B561C4B7F6DB6334B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Local volumes must be formatted using NTFS.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1084","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1084","title":"Clear System Pagefile","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1084","severity":"low","group_title":"Clear System Pagefile","rule_id_src":"SV-25112r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25112","rule_version":"3.003","rule_title":"System pagefile is cleared upon shutdown.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cShutdown: Clear virtual memory pagefile\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cShutdown: Clear virtual memory pagefile\u201d is not set to \u201cDisabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\Memory Management\\\n\nValue Name:  ClearPageFileAtShutdown\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that Windows is configured to not wipe clean the system pagefile during a controlled system shutdown.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7764","uuid":"ab7759ab-9fe8-4091-9530-78b78c0986b3","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D90B7C1854ABE1E03A159243762BC93454862FCB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'System pagefile is cleared upon shutdown.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1085","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1085","title":"Removable media devices.","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1085","severity":"low","group_title":"Removable media devices.","rule_id_src":"SV-25037r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25037","rule_version":"3.006","rule_title":"Floppy media devices are not allocated upon user logon.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cDevices: Restrict floppy access to locally logged-on user only\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  Expand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\n\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\nIf the value for \u201cDevices: Restrict floppy access to locally logged-on user only\u201d is not set to \u201cDisabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nSubkey: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name: Allocatefloppies\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that Windows is configured to not limit access to floppy drives when a user is logged on locally.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2438","uuid":"7588fb2e-e70e-424b-843d-58d0b0ade31f","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-1089","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1089","title":"Legal Notice Display","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1089","severity":"medium","group_title":"Legal Notice Display","rule_id_src":"SV-25046r5_rule","rule_id":"SV-25046","rule_version":"3.011","rule_title":"The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive Logon: Message text for users attempting to log on\" to the following.\n\nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants.  Such communications and work product are private and confidential.  See User Agreement for details.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Interactive Logon: Message text for users attempting to log on\" is not set to the following, this is a finding.\n\nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants.  Such communications and work product are private and confidential.  See User Agreement for details.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeText\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: See message text above","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000048","CCI-000050","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"7146","uuid":"124ebebf-1ed2-455c-9dc8-d7f8936159e0","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BF528628620CE2F4015FE4587492A20C474AFA34\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1090","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1090","title":"Caching of logon credentials","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1090","severity":"low","group_title":"Caching of logon credentials","rule_id_src":"SV-25047r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-25047","rule_version":"3.013","rule_title":"Caching of logon credentials must be limited.","fix_text":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is NA.\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Interactive Logon: Number of previous logons to cache (in case Domain Controller is not available)\" to \"2\" logons or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is NA.\nAnalyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Interactive Logon: Number of previous logons to cache (in case Domain Controller is unavailable)\" is not set to \"2\" logons or less, this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  CachedLogonsCount\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  2 (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The default Windows configuration caches the last logon credentials for users who log on interactively to a system.  This feature is provided for system availability reasons, such as the user's machine being disconnected from the network or domain controllers being unavailable.  Even though the credential cache is well-protected, if a system is attacked, an unauthorized individual may isolate the password to a domain user account using a password-cracking program and gain access to the domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7240","uuid":"04a509c9-b611-4264-a221-78197e38f876","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BBA30A79CEA067D87BF3E74CD53CC1FF2D04C535\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Caching of logon credentials must be limited.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1093","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1093","title":"Anonymous shares are not restricted","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1093","severity":"high","group_title":"Anonymous shares are not restricted","rule_id_src":"SV-25090r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25090","rule_version":"3.018","rule_title":"Anonymous enumeration of shares must be restricted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy values for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts and shares\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts and shares\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name:   RestrictAnonymous\n\nValue Type:   REG_DWORD\nValue:   1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous logon users (null session connections) to list all account names and enumerate all shared resources can provide a map of potential points to attack the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"5798","uuid":"2dc069d1-1a35-441b-b77c-9f81eafab433","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 24CE34B5B9878E78B221FBADE419C979CF4FE784\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Anonymous enumeration of shares must be restricted.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1097","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1097","title":"Bad Logon Attempts","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1097","severity":"medium","group_title":"Bad Logon Attempts","rule_id_src":"SV-25015r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25015","rule_version":"4.002","rule_title":"The system must lockout accounts after 3 invalid logon attempts within a specified time period.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Account Lockout Policy >> \"Account lockout threshold\" to \"3\" or less invalid logon attempts (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Account Policies >> Account Lockout Policy.\n\nIf the \"Account lockout threshold\" is \"0\" or more than \"3\" attempts, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The account lockout feature, when enabled, prevents brute-force password attacks on the system.  The higher this value is, the less effective the account lockout feature will be in protecting the local system.  The number of bad logon attempts must be reasonably small to minimize the possibility of a successful password attack, while allowing for honest errors made during a normal user logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000044"],"reference_identifier":"8638","uuid":"d14345b8-d17d-4b8c-993f-ebeae90bd72b","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-1098","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1098","title":"Bad Logon Counter Reset","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1098","severity":"medium","group_title":"Bad Logon Counter Reset","rule_id_src":"SV-25016r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-25016","rule_version":"4.003","rule_title":"The reset period for the account lockout counter must be configured to 15 minutes or greater on Windows 7.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Account Lockout Policy >> \"Reset account lockout counter after\" to at least \"15\" minutes.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Account Policies >> Account Lockout Policy.\n\nIf the \"Reset account lockout counter after\" value is less than \"15\" minutes, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The account lockout feature, when enabled, prevents brute-force password attacks on the system.  This parameter specifies the period of time that must pass after failed logon attempts before the counter is reset to \"0\".  The smaller this value is, the less effective the account lockout feature will be in protecting the local system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000044","CCI-002238"],"reference_identifier":"3240","uuid":"7f39d17b-c5e6-45ec-9c65-340792294d0b","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 465451A3AB9F0B6EC8813DC094D4885735E1F7DC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The reset period for the account lockout counter must be configured to 15 minutes or greater on Windows 7.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1099","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1099","title":"Lockout Duration","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1099","severity":"medium","group_title":"Lockout Duration","rule_id_src":"SV-25014r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-25014","rule_version":"4.004","rule_title":"Windows 7 account lockout duration must be configured to 15 minutes or greater.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Account Lockout Policy >> \"Account lockout duration\" to \"15\" minutes or greater.\n\nA value of \"0\" is also acceptable, requiring an administrator to unlock the account.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Account Policies >> Account Lockout Policy.\n\nIf the \"Account lockout duration\" is less than \"15\" minutes (excluding \"0\"), this is a finding.\n\nConfiguring this to \"0\", requiring an administrator to unlock the account, is more restrictive and is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The account lockout feature, when enabled, prevents brute-force password attacks on the system.  This parameter specifies the amount of time that an account will remain locked after the specified number of failed logon attempts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002238"],"reference_identifier":"1013","uuid":"aa051d3c-ee86-46b6-a05a-0d3383b6a44d","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 165D1F31C4F723927F1BDCCDF61A0E2648E8F2C3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 7 account lockout duration must be configured to 15 minutes or greater.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1102","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1102","title":"User Right - Act as part of OS","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1102","severity":"high","group_title":"User Right - Act as part of OS","rule_id_src":"SV-25017r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25017","rule_version":"WINUR-000003","rule_title":"The Act as part of the operating system user right must be granted to no accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Act as part of the operating system\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups (to include administrators), are granted the \"Act as part of the operating system\" right, this is a finding.\n \nDocumentable Explanation:  Some applications require this right to function. Any exception needs to be documented with the ISSO.  Passwords for accounts with this user right must be protected as highly privileged accounts.  Acceptable forms of documentation include vendor published documents and application owner confirmation.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right can assume the identity of any user and gain access to resources that user is authorized to access.  Any accounts with this right can take complete control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9633","uuid":"a42f9d54-e0da-4986-9b64-c84b72bed1f1","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C8CAF168A56B52245AA825967857B1F1FF5B08B9\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Act as part of the operating system user right must be granted to no accounts.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1104","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1104","title":"Maximum Password Age","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1104","severity":"medium","group_title":"Maximum Password Age","rule_id_src":"SV-25009r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25009","rule_version":"4.011","rule_title":"The maximum password age must be configured to 60 days or less.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Password Policy >> \"Maximum Password Age\" to \"60\" days or less (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Account Policies >> Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for the \"Maximum password age\" is greater than \"60\" days, this is a finding.\nIf the value is set to \"0\" (never expires), this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The longer passwords are in use, the greater the opportunity for someone to gain unauthorized knowledge of them.  Scheduled changing of passwords hinders the ability of unauthorized users to crack passwords and gain access to a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000199"],"reference_identifier":"3323","uuid":"68e0dcb8-21dc-4c83-bb96-0e5169349733","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AEBD901AA57083AB619930B9C2402F429EB40F70\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The maximum password age must be configured to 60 days or less.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1105","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1105","title":"Minimum Password Age","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1105","severity":"medium","group_title":"Minimum Password Age","rule_id_src":"SV-25010r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25010","rule_version":"4.012","rule_title":"The minimum password age must be configured to at least 1 day.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Password Policy >> \"Minimum Password Age\" to at least \"1\" day.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Account Policies >> Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for the \"Minimum password age\" is not at least \"1\" day, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Permitting passwords to be changed in immediate succession within the same day allows users to cycle passwords through their history database.  This enables users to effectively negate the purpose of mandating periodic password changes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000198"],"reference_identifier":"1748","uuid":"a9a4cf6e-8dfc-4166-b43e-495af6ab986a","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0543DF5B4E5B8BEEA502DE6B93240AB7623AA406\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The minimum password age must be configured to at least 1 day.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1107","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1107","title":"Password Uniqueness","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1107","severity":"medium","group_title":"Password Uniqueness","rule_id_src":"SV-25008r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-25008","rule_version":"4.014","rule_title":"The password history must be configured to 24 passwords remembered.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Password Policy >> \"Enforce password history\" to \"24\" passwords remembered.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Account Policies >> Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Enforce password history\" is less than \"24\" passwords remembered, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system is more vulnerable to unauthorized access when users can recycle the same password several times without being required to change it to a unique password on a regularly scheduled basis.  This enables users to effectively negate the purpose of mandating periodic password changes.  The default value is 24 for Windows domain systems.  DoD has decided this is the appropriate value for all Windows systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000200"],"reference_identifier":"1499","uuid":"50ac94af-8547-453b-96db-dc5a3fbbb772","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 71F531645781656F0637E9F2A09FDD163341C8E8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The password history must be configured to 24 passwords remembered.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1112","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1112","title":"Dormant Accounts","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1112","severity":"low","group_title":"Dormant Accounts","rule_id_src":"SV-25213r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25213","rule_version":"4.019","rule_title":"Outdated or unused accounts must be removed from the system.","fix_text":"Regularly review accounts to determine if they are still active.  Accounts that have not been used in the last 35 days must be removed or disabled.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run the DUMPSEC utility.\nSelect \"Dump Users as Table\" from the \"Report\" menu.\nSelect the following fields, and click \"Add\" for each entry:\n\nUserName\nSID\nLastLogonTime\nAcctDisabled\n\nReview the \"LastLogonTime\".\nIf any enabled accounts have not been logged on to within the past 35 days, this is a finding.\n\nThe following accounts are exempt:\nBuilt-in administrator account (SID ending in 500)\nBuilt-in guest account (SID ending in 501)\nApplication accounts\nDisabled accounts\n\nReview the list to determine the finding validity for each account reported.\n\nIf the organization has a need for special purpose local user accounts such as a backup administrator account (see V-14224), this must be documented with the ISSO.  This would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Outdated or unused accounts provide penetration points that may go undetected.  Inactive accounts must be deleted if no longer necessary or, if still required, disable until needed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000795"],"reference_identifier":"4472","uuid":"0edec7f4-ec03-4f1c-9b94-160e7dcbe34e","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4742D3BBB7A3480AF3569E8EBE7C6BF8E5790173\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Outdated or unused accounts must be removed from the system.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1113","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1113","title":"Disable Guest Account","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1113","severity":"medium","group_title":"Disable Guest Account","rule_id_src":"SV-25021r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25021","rule_version":"4.020","rule_title":"The built-in guest account must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Guest account status\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Guest account status\" is not set to \" Disabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system faces an increased vulnerability threat if the built-in guest account is not disabled.  This account is a known account that exists on all Windows systems and cannot be deleted.  This account is initialized during the installation of the operating system with no password assigned.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000804"],"reference_identifier":"7613","uuid":"dad38c90-f893-4442-abd0-4a7707c71dcd","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0B7D28C7C01E71567E1A00CC504F91E2DBABA37B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The built-in guest account must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1114","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1114","title":"Rename Built-in Guest Account","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1114","severity":"medium","group_title":"Rename Built-in Guest Account","rule_id_src":"SV-25024r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25024","rule_version":"4.021","rule_title":"The built-in guest account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" to a name other than \"Guest\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" is not set to a value other than \"Guest\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in guest account is a well-known user account on all Windows systems and, as initially installed, does not require a password.  This can allow access to system resources by unauthorized users.  Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1213","uuid":"718d9f91-76d3-49b7-af4b-54c4ca8bba76","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-1115","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1115","title":"Rename Built-in Administrator Account","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1115","severity":"medium","group_title":"Rename Built-in Administrator Account","rule_id_src":"SV-25023r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25023","rule_version":"4.022","rule_title":"The built-in administrator account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" to a name other than \"Administrator\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" is not set to a value other than \"Administrator\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in administrator account is a well-known account subject to attack.  Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6696","uuid":"31c7840e-3c29-4e7d-99d3-54477c36d9de","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0769D331DE9EBFD36129C766CFED899B4B4F17D6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The built-in administrator account must be renamed.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1119","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1119","title":"Booting into Multiple Operating Systems","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1119","severity":"medium","group_title":"Booting into Multiple Operating Systems","rule_id_src":"SV-25256r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25256","rule_version":"5.003","rule_title":"Booting into alternate operating systems is permitted.","fix_text":"Configure the system to prevent running non-compliant alternate operating systems.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that the local system boots directly into Windows:\n\nOpen Control Panel.\nSelect \u201cSystem\u201d.\nSelect the \u201cAdvanced System Settings\u201d link.\nSelect the \u201cAdvanced\u201d tab.\nClick the Startup and Recovery \u201cSettings\u201d button.  \n\nIf the drop-down list box \u201cDefault operating system:\u201d shows any operating system other than Windows 7, this may be a finding.\n\nVerify that Windows XP Mode, a Windows Virtual PC instance of Windows XP, has not been installed on the system:\n\nOpen Control Panel.\nSelect \u201cPrograms and Features\u201d.\nIf Windows Virtual PC or Windows XP Mode are listed this may be a finding.\n\nIf all additional operating systems are STIG compliant, then this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing other operating systems to run on a secure system, can allow users to circumvent security.  If more than one operating system is installed on a computer, each must be configured to be compliant with STIG guidance.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6836","uuid":"8f9b81eb-76c3-48c8-941a-e1fdde5c1eb6","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7F7AFF35F03C0F6714410CB93E36E085B29530F8\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Booting into alternate operating systems is permitted.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1122","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1122","title":"Password Protected Screen Saver","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1122","severity":"medium","group_title":"Password Protected Screen Saver","rule_id_src":"SV-25201r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25201","rule_version":"5.006","rule_title":"The system must be configured with a password-protected screen saver.","fix_text":"Configure the policy values for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Control Panel >> Personalization >> as follows:\n\n\"Enable Screen Saver\" to \"Enabled\".\n\"Password protect the screen saver\" to \"Enabled\".\n\"Screen Saver timeout\" to \"Enabled: 900 seconds\" (or less).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If any of the registry values do not exist or are not configured as follows, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Control Panel\\Desktop\\\n\nValue Name:  ScreenSaveActive\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  1\n\nValue Name:  ScreenSaverIsSecure\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  1\n\nValue Name:  ScreenSaveTimeout\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  900 (or less)\n\nApplications requiring continuous, real-time screen display (e.g., network management products) require the following and must be documented with the ISSO.\n\n-The logon session does not have administrator rights.\n-The display station (e.g., keyboard, monitor, etc.) is located in a controlled access area.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked when unattended.  Enabling a password-protected screen saver to engage after a specified period of time helps protects critical and sensitive data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000056","CCI-000057","CCI-000060"],"reference_identifier":"9672","uuid":"f90a3e1a-2cd5-4de4-9985-cb22d1b87c62","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E93FDDFAE0D5452C41EA4561B26D1B051E1AEDC9\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured with a password-protected screen saver.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1127","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1127","title":"Restricted Administrator Group Membership","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1127","severity":"high","group_title":"Restricted Administrator Group Membership","rule_id_src":"SV-25215r6_rule","rule_id":"SV-25215","rule_version":"4.027","rule_title":"Only administrators responsible for the system must have Administrator rights on the system.","fix_text":"Configure the system to include only administrator groups or accounts that are responsible for the system in the local Administrators group.\n\nFor domain-joined workstations, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain workstation administrator group.\n\nSystems dedicated to the management of Active Directory (AD admin platforms, see V-36436 in the Active Directory Domain STIG) are exempt from this.  AD admin platforms may use the Domain Admins group or a domain administrative group created specifically for AD admin platforms (see V-43711 in the Active Directory Domain STIG).\n\nRemove any standard user accounts.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Review the local Administrators group.  Only the appropriate administrator groups or accounts responsible for administration of the system may be members of the group.\n\nFor domain-joined workstations, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain workstation administrator group.\n\nSystems dedicated to the management of Active Directory (AD admin platforms, see V-36436 in the Active Directory Domain STIG) are exempt from this.  AD admin platforms may use the Domain Admins group or a domain administrative group created specifically for AD admin platforms (see V-43711 in the Active Directory Domain STIG).\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the local administrator group.\n\nIf prohibited accounts are members of the local administrators group, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An account that does not have Administrator duties must not have Administrator rights.  Such rights would allow the account to bypass or modify required security restrictions on that machine and make it vulnerable to attack.\n\nSystem administrators must log on to systems only using accounts with the minimum level of authority necessary.\n\nFor domain-joined workstations, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain workstation administrator group (see V-36434 in the Active Directory Domain STIG).  Restricting highly privileged accounts from the local Administrators group helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nSystems dedicated to the management of Active Directory (AD admin platforms, see V-36436 in the Active Directory Domain STIG) are exempt from this.  AD admin platforms may use the Domain Admins group or a domain administrative group created specifically for AD admin platforms (see V-43711 in the Active Directory Domain STIG).\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the built-in Administrators group.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"7459","uuid":"4fb08e2c-9aa4-4f6a-a221-bc30f5819524","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 63B28732B52C46826966048C8BD170BE38BC1986\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Only administrators responsible for the system must have Administrator rights on the system.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1128","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1128","title":"Security Configuration Tools","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1128","severity":"low","group_title":"Security Configuration Tools","rule_id_src":"SV-25002r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25002","rule_version":"1.016","rule_title":"Security configuration tools are not being used to configure platforms for security compliance.","fix_text":"Security configuration tools or equivalent should be used to configure Windows systems to meet security requirements.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that security configuration tools, or an equivalent process, is being used to configure Windows systems to meet security requirements.  Security configuration tools that are integrated into Windows (such as Security Templates and Group Policy) should be used to configure platforms for security compliance.\n\nIf an alternate method is used to configure a system (e.g., manually using the DISA Windows Security STIGs, etc.) that achieves the same configured result, then this is acceptable.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Security configuration tools (such as Security Templates and Group Policy) allow system administrators to consolidate all security related system settings into a single configuration file.  These settings can then be applied consistently to any number of Windows machines.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5680","uuid":"296fd3ba-fc75-4987-b89a-8a10ab9e29af","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 50DC89906B0340D47608E3F99151153F4D3E3E97\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Security configuration tools are not being used to configure platforms for security compliance.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1130","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1130","title":"System File ACLs","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1130","severity":"medium","group_title":"System File ACLs","rule_id_src":"SV-25136r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25136","rule_version":"2.006","rule_title":"Permissions for system files and directories must conform to minimum requirements.","fix_text":"Maintain the default file ACLs and configure the Security Option: \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\" (V-3377).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default ACL settings are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (V-3377).  If the default ACLs are maintained and the referenced option is set to \"Disabled\", this is not a finding.\n\nVerify the default permissions for the sample directories below.  Non-privileged groups such as Users or Authenticated Users must not have greater than Read & execute permissions except where noted as defaults.  (Individual accounts must not be used to assign permissions.)\n\nViewing in Windows Explorer:\nRight click on the directory and select \"Properties\".\nSelect the \"Security\" tab, and the \"Advanced\" button.\n\nC:\\\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"<not inherited>\" for all\nName - Permission - Apply to\nAdministrators - Full control - This folder, subfolders and files\nSYSTEM - Full control - This folder, subfolders and files\nUsers - Read & execute - This folder, subfolders and files\nAuthenticated Users - Special - Subfolders and files only\n(Special = all permissions except Full Control, Delete subfolders and files, Change permissions, and Take ownership when viewing permission details.)\nAuthenticated Users - Create folders / append data - This folder only\n\nThe Program Files, Program Files (x86), and Windows directories have the following default permissions:\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"<not inherited>\" for all\nName - Permission - Apply to\nTrustedInstaller - Special - This folder and subfolders\n(Special = Full control when viewing permission details.)\nSYSTEM - Special - This folder only\n(Special = all permissions except Full Control, Delete subfolders and files, Change permissions, and Take ownership when viewing permission details.)\nSYSTEM - Special - Subfolders and files only\n(Special = Full control when viewing permission details.)\nAdministrators - Special - This folder only\n(Special = all permissions except Full Control, Delete subfolders and files, Change permissions, and Take ownership when viewing permission details.)\nAdministrators - Special - Subfolders and files only\n(Special = Full control when viewing permission details.)\nUsers - Read & execute - This folder, subfolders and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Special - Subfolders and files only\n(Special = Full control when viewing permission details.)\n\n\nAlternately use Icacls.\n\nIn a Command prompt (admin)\nEnter icacls followed by the directory.\n\nicacls c:\\\nicacls \"c:\\program files\" of \"c:\\program files (x86)\"\nicacls c:\\windows\n\nThe following results will be displayed as each is entered:\n\nc:\\\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(RX)\nNT AUTHORITY\\Authenticated Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(M)\nNT AUTHORITY\\Authenticated Users:(AD)\nMandatory Label\\High Mandatory Level:(OI)(NP)(IO)(NW)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files\n\nc:\\program files, c:\\program files (x86), and c:\\windows\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(F)\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(CI)(IO)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(M)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(M)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files\n\nIf a permission setting prevents a site's applications from performing properly, settings must only be changed to the minimum necessary for the application to function.  Each exception must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Changing the system's file and directory permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system and installed applications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002165"],"reference_identifier":"2242","uuid":"ab9cd915-cf76-4fee-b9af-fd7ec9656eed","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-1135","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1135","title":"Printer Share Permissions","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1135","severity":"low","group_title":"Printer Share Permissions","rule_id_src":"SV-25007r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25007","rule_version":"3.027","rule_title":"Printer share permissions must be restricted to Print for non administrators.","fix_text":"Configure the permissions on locally shared printers to ensure non administrators only have \"Print\".\n\nOpen \"Devices and Printers\" in Control Panel.\n\nRight-click on a locally attached printer.\nSelect \"Printer Properties\".\nSelect the \"Sharing\" tab.\n\nFor each printer that has the \"Share this printer\" selected:\nSelect the Security tab.\n\nAssign any non-administrative user accounts or groups \"Print\" permission only.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Open \"Devices and Printers\" in Control Panel.\n\nIf there are no locally attached printers, this is NA.\n\nPerform this check for each locally attached printer:\nRight-click on a locally attached printer.\nSelect \"Printer Properties\".\nSelect the \"Sharing\" tab.\nView whether \"Share this printer\" is checked.\n\nPerform this check on each printer that has the \"Share this printer\" selected:\nSelect the Security tab.\n\nIf any non-administrative user accounts or groups have greater than \"Print\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Improperly configured share permissions on printers can permit the addition of unauthorized print devices on the network.  Windows shares are a means by which files, folders, printers, and other resources can be published for network users to remotely access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5731","uuid":"cde385fe-a938-4276-a7f6-1d6117987d23","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7557F3F3659A34BFA828B87C01A00994C2A012B9\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Printer share permissions must be restricted to Print for non administrators.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1136","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1136","title":"Forcibly Disconnect when Logon Hours Expire","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1136","severity":"low","group_title":"Forcibly Disconnect when Logon Hours Expire","rule_id_src":"SV-25063r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25063","rule_version":"4.006","rule_title":"Users are not forcibly disconnected when logon hours expire.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cMicrosoft Network Server: Disconnect Clients When Logon Hours Expire\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  Expand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.  \n\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cMicrosoft Network Server: Disconnect Clients When Logon Hours Expire\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableForcedLogoff\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users should not be permitted to remain logged on to the network after they have exceeded their permitted logon hours.  In many cases, this indicates that a user forgot to log off before leaving for the day.  However, it may also indicate that a user is attempting unauthorized access at a time when the system may be less closely monitored.  Forcibly disconnecting users when logon hours expire protects critical and sensitive network data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001133"],"reference_identifier":"8424","uuid":"d6ce64b5-809b-4b08-909c-6416aaca8f00","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0068F3E45DCEC2E5CBA70EF0D183BD4BA4CE157F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Users are not forcibly disconnected when logon hours expire.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1140","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1140","title":"Users with Administrative Privilege","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1140","severity":"high","group_title":"Users with Administrative Privilege","rule_id_src":"SV-24997r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-24997","rule_version":"1.006","rule_title":"Users with administrative privilege must be documented and have separate accounts for administrative duties and normal operational tasks.","fix_text":"Create necessary documentation that identifies members of the Administrators group, to be maintained with the ISSO.\n\nCreate unique administrator accounts, separate from the built-in \"Administrator\" account for each user with administrative privileges.\n\nCreate separate accounts for performing normal (non-administrative) functions for each user with administrative privileges.\n\nProperly train users with administrative privileges.\n\nDo not allow the use of  the built-in Administrator account.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following:\n\nThe necessary documentation that identifies members of the Administrators group exists with the ISSO.\n\nEach user with administrative privileges has been assigned a unique administrator account, separate from the built-in \"Administrator\" account.\n\nEach user with administrative privileges has a separate account for performing normal (non-administrative) functions.\n\nAdministrators must be properly trained before being permitted to perform administrator duties.\n\nUse of the built-in Administrator account must not be allowed.\n\nIf any of these conditions are not met, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Using a privileged account to perform routine functions makes the computer vulnerable to malicious software inadvertently introduced during a session that has been granted full privileges.  The rule of least privilege must always be enforced.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5998","uuid":"299f4ee1-6dde-4e59-869f-7e1a7eeca417","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8DF8678A9D2CC51B499CC61C18F769E1E4D39569\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Users with administrative privilege must be documented and have separate accounts for administrative duties and normal operational tasks.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1141","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1141","title":"Unencrypted Password is Sent to SMB Server.","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1141","severity":"medium","group_title":"Unencrypted Password is Sent to SMB Server.","rule_id_src":"SV-25056r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25056","rule_version":"3.034","rule_title":"Unencrypted passwords must not be sent to third-party SMB Servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft Network Client: Send unencrypted password to third-party SMB servers\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Microsoft Network Client: Send unencrypted password to third-party SMB servers\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  EnablePlainTextPassword\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some non-Microsoft SMB servers only support unencrypted (plain text) password authentication.  Sending plain text passwords across the network, when authenticating to an SMB server, reduces the overall security of the environment.  Check with the vendor of the SMB server to see if there is a way to support encrypted password authentication.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000197"],"reference_identifier":"7477","uuid":"0371c0e1-5bf7-4d85-af01-d992c098e78d","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-1145","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1145","title":"Disable Automatic Logon","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1145","severity":"medium","group_title":"Disable Automatic Logon","rule_id_src":"SV-25064r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25064","rule_version":"3.040","rule_title":"Automatic logons must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"MSS: (AutoAdminLogon) Enable Automatic Logon (not recommended)\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nEnsure no passwords are stored in the \"DefaultPassword\" registry value noted below.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name: DefaultPassword","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\t\nIf the value for \"MSS: (AutoAdminLogon) Enable Automatic Logon (not recommended)\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name: AutoAdminLogon\n\nType: REG_SZ\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing a system to automatically log on when the machine is booted could give access to any unauthorized individual who restarts the computer.  Automatic logon with administrator privileges would give full access to an unauthorized individual.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5664","uuid":"65366be8-ca1e-4380-b515-bec0e9852352","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4A62E799455889A39964184CC82A1B0F006B4A88\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Automatic logons must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1148","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1148","title":"Local Users Exist on a Workstation","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1148","severity":"low","group_title":"Local Users Exist on a Workstation","rule_id_src":"SV-25214r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25214","rule_version":"4.024","rule_title":"Local users must not exist on a system in a domain.","fix_text":"Limit local user accounts on domain-joined systems.  Remove any unauthorized local accounts.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run the DUMPSEC utility.\nSelect \"Dump Users as Table\" from the \"Report\" menu.\nSelect the following fields, and click \"Add\" for each entry:\n\nUserName\nSID\nAcctDisabled\nGroups\n\nIf local users other than the built-in accounts listed below exist on a workstation in a domain, this is a finding:\n\nBuilt-in administrator account (SID ending in 500)\nBuilt-in guest account (SID ending in 501)\n\nIf the organization has a need for special purpose local user accounts such as a backup administrator account (see V-14224), this must be documented with the ISSO.  This would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To minimize potential points of attack, local users, other than built-in accounts such as Administrator and Guest accounts, should not exist on a workstation in a domain.  Users must always log onto workstations in a domain with their domain accounts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2259","uuid":"9bf6114e-f67e-428a-bf58-ff1a78b1c659","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A4DB6CAADACA0B70DE507576D597AA40C9833D39\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Local users must not exist on a system in a domain.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1150","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1150","title":"Microsoft Strong Password Filtering","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1150","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Strong Password Filtering","rule_id_src":"SV-25012r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25012","rule_version":"3.028","rule_title":"The built-in Windows password complexity policy must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Password Policy >> \"Password must meet complexity requirements\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Account Policies >> Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Password must meet complexity requirements\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.\n\nNote: If an external password filter is in use that enforces all 4 character types and requires this setting be set to \"Disabled\", this would not be considered a finding. If this setting does not affect the use of an external password filter, it must be enabled for fall-back purposes.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The use of complex passwords increases their strength against attack. The built-in Windows password complexity policy requires passwords to contain at least 3 of the 4 types of characters (numbers, upper- and lower-case letters, and special characters), as well as preventing the inclusion of user names or parts of.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000192","CCI-000193","CCI-000194","CCI-001619"],"reference_identifier":"4281","uuid":"3d9c6414-d14e-4dd8-93c3-23604c7967c4","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 68DFEA97E6F5A623AA8C935A0221FE4331B03D21\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The built-in Windows password complexity policy must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1151","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1151","title":"Secure Print Driver Installation","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1151","severity":"low","group_title":"Secure Print Driver Installation","rule_id_src":"SV-25035r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25035","rule_version":"3.029","rule_title":"Print driver installation privilege must be restricted to administrators.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Devices: Prevent users from installing printer drivers\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Devices: Prevent users from installing printer drivers\" is not set to  \"Enabled\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Print\\Providers\\LanMan Print Services\\Servers\\\n\nValue Name:  AddPrinterDrivers\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1\n\nIf site circumstances require that users be able to install print drivers for locally attached printers, this exception must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The print spooler allows users to add and to delete printer drivers on the local system.  This capability must be restricted to privileged groups to ensure only stable, non-malicious drivers are used.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"2033","uuid":"f20f2e4d-0f59-47a7-90ec-078881ced561","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A550886838E4B432BE8D1B7737A952CA956572B2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Print driver installation privilege must be restricted to administrators.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1152","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1152","title":"Anonymous Access to the Registry","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1152","severity":"high","group_title":"Anonymous Access to the Registry","rule_id_src":"SV-25137r4_rule","rule_id":"SV-25137","rule_version":"3.030","rule_title":"Anonymous access to the registry must be restricted.","fix_text":"Maintain permissions at least as restrictive as the defaults listed below for the \"winreg\" registry key.  It is recommended to not change the permissions from the defaults.\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurePipeServers\\winreg\\\n\nThe following are the same for each permission listed:\nType - Allow\nInherited from - <not inherited>\n\nColumns: Principal - Access - Applies to\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nBackup Operators - Special - This key only\n(Special = Query Value, Enumerate Subkeys, Notify, Read Control (effectively = Read)\nLOCAL SERVICE - Read - This key and subkeys","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run \"Regedit\".\nNavigate to the following registry key:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurePipeServers\\winreg\\\n\nIf the key does not exist, this is a finding.\n\nRight-click on \"winreg\" and select \"Permissions\u2026\".\nSelect \"Advanced\".\n\nIf the permissions are not as restrictive as the defaults listed below, this is a finding.\n\nThe following are the same for each permission listed:\nType - Allow\nInherited from - <not inherited>\n\nColumns: Name - Permission - Apply to\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nBackup Operators - Special - This key only\n(Special = Query Value, Enumerate Subkeys, Notify, Read Control (effectively = Read))\nLOCAL SERVICE - Read - This key and subkeys","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The registry is integral to the function, security, and stability of the Windows system.  Some processes may require anonymous access to the registry.  This must be limited to properly protect the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"4322","uuid":"33978f0f-e9d3-4324-934f-ef9e34b0c648","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2BB55D147AB8A400FE9A2184E0220A833655AA57\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Anonymous access to the registry must be restricted.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1153","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1153","title":"LanMan Authentication Level","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1153","severity":"high","group_title":"LanMan Authentication Level","rule_id_src":"SV-25105r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25105","rule_version":"3.031","rule_title":"The Lan Manager authentication level must be set to send NTLMv2 response only, and to refuse LM and NTLM.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: LAN Manager authentication level\" to \"Send NTLMv2 response only\\refuse LM & NTLM\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network security: LAN Manager authentication level\" is not set to \"Send NTLMv2 response only\\refuse LM & NTLM\" (Level 5), this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name:  LmCompatibilityLevel\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  5","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Kerberos v5 authentication protocol is the default for authentication for domains.  NTLM which is less secure, is retained in later Windows versions for compatibility with standalone systems as well as applications that may still use it.  Earlier versions of the LM/NTLM protocol are particularly vulnerable to attack and must be prevented.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1162","uuid":"018c7769-7aba-4a87-a903-5b56f45ab6a8","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BFE7DC472FB36C161A37A40CEDEDA7B28538E1B7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Lan Manager authentication level must be set to send NTLMv2 response only, and to refuse LM and NTLM.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1154","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1154","title":"Ctrl+Alt+Del Security Attention Sequence","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1154","severity":"medium","group_title":"Ctrl+Alt+Del Security Attention Sequence","rule_id_src":"SV-25045r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25045","rule_version":"3.032","rule_title":"Ctrl+Alt+Del security attention sequence is disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cInteractive Logon: Do not require CTRL ALT DEL\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cInteractive Logon: Do not require CTRL+ALT+DEL\u201d is not set to \u201cDisabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  DisableCAD\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabling the Ctrl+Alt+Del security attention sequence can compromise system security.  Because only Windows responds to the Ctrl+Alt+Del security sequence, you can be assured that any passwords you enter following that sequence are sent only to Windows.  If you eliminate the sequence requirement, malicious programs can request and receive your Windows password.  Disabling this sequence also suppresses a custom logon banner.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4267","uuid":"186f4e78-0a8f-467e-8c5c-a7025f0a3845","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F059E4D422C87441FCD4419820D37461F8F8FE7D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Ctrl+Alt+Del security attention sequence is disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1155","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1155","title":"Deny Access from the Network","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1155","severity":"medium","group_title":"Deny Access from the Network","rule_id_src":"SV-25019r5_rule","rule_id":"SV-25019","rule_version":"WINUR-000017","rule_title":"The Deny access to this computer from the network user right on workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and all local accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" to include the following.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\nLocal account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nSystems dedicated to the management of Active Directory (AD admin platforms, see V-36436 in the Active Directory Domain STIG) are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups.\n\nNote: Microsoft Security Advisory Patch 2871997 adds new built-in security groups, including \"Local account\", to Windows 7 for assigning permissions and rights to all local accounts.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" right, this is a finding.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\nLocal account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nSystems dedicated to the management of Active Directory (AD admin platforms, see V-36436 in the Active Directory Domain STIG) are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups.\n\nNote: Microsoft Security Advisory Patch 2871997 adds new built-in security groups, including \"Local account\", to Windows 7 for assigning permissions and rights to all local accounts.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on from the network.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nLocal accounts on domain-joined systems must also be assigned this right to decrease the risk of lateral movement resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"6862","uuid":"10cd2f44-9cb1-4724-89e5-b73730cbd50e","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7C2F0154DB78DB570EEE836A12FA1EE40F6A8B03\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Deny access to this computer from the network user right on workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and all local accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1157","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1157","title":"Smart Card Removal Option","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1157","severity":"medium","group_title":"Smart Card Removal Option","rule_id_src":"SV-25050r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25050","rule_version":"3.047","rule_title":"The Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Smart card removal behavior\" to  \"Lock Workstation\" or \"Force Logoff\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Interactive logon: Smart card removal behavior\" is not set to \"Lock Workstation\" or \"Force Logoff\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  SCRemoveOption\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  1 (Lock Workstation) or 2 (Force Logoff)\n\nThis may be left not configured or set to \"No action\" on workstations with the following conditions.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\n-The setting cannot be configured due to mission needs, or because it interferes with applications.\n-A policy must be in place requiring users to manually lock workstations when leaving them unattended.\n-The screen saver is properly configured to lock as required (see V-1122).","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked.  Configuring a system to lock when a smart card is removed will ensure the system is inaccessible when unattended.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5059","uuid":"414bd75c-21f5-41b0-9e47-3bf1a47b9dfc","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-1162","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1162","title":"SMB Server Packet Signing (if client agrees)","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1162","severity":"medium","group_title":"SMB Server Packet Signing (if client agrees)","rule_id_src":"SV-25061r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25061","rule_version":"3.046","rule_title":"The Windows SMB server is not enabled to perform SMB packet signing when possible.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cMicrosoft Network Server: Digitally sign communications (if Client agrees)\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cMicrosoft Network Server: Digitally sign communications (if client agrees)\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If this policy is enabled, it causes the Windows Server Message Block (SMB) server to perform SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"4383","uuid":"caea2cf2-ae66-4136-a31a-8c92495fa8fb","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B2E2883A6ACA381B5FE45D718099DD065D877B92\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows SMB server is not enabled to perform SMB packet signing when possible.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1163","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1163","title":"Encryption of Secure Channel Traffic","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1163","severity":"medium","group_title":"Encryption of Secure Channel Traffic","rule_id_src":"SV-25039r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25039","rule_version":"3.043","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic is not encrypted when possible.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cDomain Member: Digitally encrypt secure channel data (when possible)\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cDomain Member: Digitally encrypt secure channel data (when possible)\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  SealSecureChannel\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1\n\nNote: If the value for \u201cDomain Member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always)\u201d is set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted.  If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic should be encrypted.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"8939","uuid":"b4d2357e-94a2-4a21-920d-d615ee07f84e","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9F1874677DBA967200F2C1DA5A7F0D1BE9C6BCBE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Outgoing secure channel traffic is not encrypted when possible.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1164","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1164","title":"Signing of Secure Channel Traffic","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1164","severity":"medium","group_title":"Signing of Secure Channel Traffic","rule_id_src":"SV-25040r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25040","rule_version":"3.042","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic is not signed when possible.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cDomain Member: Digitally sign secure channel data (when possible)\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cDomain Member: Digitally sign secure channel data (when possible)\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  SignSecureChannel\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1\n\nNote: If the value for \u201cDomain Member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always)\u201d is set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but the channel is not integrity checked.  If this policy is enabled, all outgoing secure channel traffic should be signed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"4234","uuid":"956449bf-94ac-4021-af58-0e282def3067","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D277C27B9B5614C83C0CD6B06A8B00F55EAD4674\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Outgoing secure channel traffic is not signed when possible.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1165","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1165","title":"Computer Account Password Reset","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1165","severity":"low","group_title":"Computer Account Password Reset","rule_id_src":"SV-25041r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25041","rule_version":"3.044","rule_title":"The computer account password is prevented from being reset.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cDomain Member: Disable Machine Account Password Changes\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cDomain Member: Disable Machine Account Password Changes\u201d is not set to  \u201cDisabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  DisablePasswordChange\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis.  Enabling this policy to disable automatic password changes can make the system more vulnerable to malicious access.  Frequent password changes can be a significant safeguard for your system.  If this policy is disabled, a new password for the computer account will be generated every 30 days.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7212","uuid":"6711553e-42c3-4506-9d4f-c5436e6c2e24","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-1166","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1166","title":"SMB Client Packet Signing (if server agrees)","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1166","severity":"medium","group_title":"SMB Client Packet Signing (if server agrees)","rule_id_src":"SV-25055r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25055","rule_version":"3.045","rule_title":"The Windows SMB client is not enabled to perform SMB packet signing when possible.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cMicrosoft Network Client: Digitally sign communications (if server agrees)\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cMicrosoft Network Client: Digitally sign communications (if server agrees)\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If this policy is enabled, it causes the Windows Server Message Block (SMB) client to perform SMB packet signing when communicating with an SMB server that is enabled or required to perform SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"4420","uuid":"6f61c3ea-9f1a-406a-b444-6134898d1379","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4AB1911F5039B0D10D817028C7F2AB125291782D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows SMB client is not enabled to perform SMB packet signing when possible.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1168","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1168","title":"Members of the Backup Operators Group","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1168","severity":"medium","group_title":"Members of the Backup Operators Group","rule_id_src":"SV-25216r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25216","rule_version":"1.007","rule_title":"Members of the Backup Operators group must have separate accounts for backup duties and normal operational tasks.","fix_text":"Create the necessary documentation that identifies the members of the Backup Operators group, to be maintained with the ISSO.\n\nCreate separate accounts for backup operations for users with this privilege.\n\nCreate separate accounts for normal user functions for users with this privilege.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Review the Backup Operators group in Computer Management.\n\nIf the group contains any accounts, this must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nAny accounts that are members of the Backup Operators group must be documented, including application accounts.  Users with accounts in the Backup Operators group will have a separate user account for backup functions and for performing normal user tasks.\n\nIf the group contains no accounts, this is not a finding.\n\nIf any of the following conditions are true, this is a finding:\n\n-Each Backup Operator does not have a unique userid dedicated to the backup function.\n-Each Backup Operator does not have a separate account for normal user tasks.\n-The ISSO does not maintain a list of users belonging to the Backup Operators group.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Backup Operators are able to read and write to any file in the system, regardless of the rights assigned to it.  Backup and restore rights permit users to circumvent the file access restrictions present on NTFS disk drives for backup and restore purposes.  Members of the Backup Operators group must have separate logon accounts for performing backup duties.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1625","uuid":"9ecaa6a8-8dec-46d2-99eb-4a6aac232165","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AF5E6C63470A5EEEA179F774658F2498B5ED8F21\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Members of the Backup Operators group must have separate accounts for backup duties and normal operational tasks.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1171","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1171","title":"Format and Eject Removable Media","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1171","severity":"medium","group_title":"Format and Eject Removable Media","rule_id_src":"SV-25034r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25034","rule_version":"3.052","rule_title":"Ejection of removable NTFS media is not restricted to administrators.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cDevices: Allowed to Format and Eject Removable Media\u201d to \u201cAdministrators\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cDevices: Allowed to Format and Eject Removable Media\u201d is not set to \u201d Administrators\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\n\nValue Name:  AllocateDASD\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Removable hard drives can be formatted and ejected by others who are not members of the Administrators Group, if they are not properly configured.  Formatting and ejecting removable NTFS media should only be done by administrators.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8118","uuid":"6e38829c-4e37-4d4b-b7a7-fcc6be032545","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 214BE8E16B9A679A8D79EA6832058E29CD99DEBB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Ejection of removable NTFS media is not restricted to administrators.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1172","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1172","title":"Password Expiration Warning","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1172","severity":"low","group_title":"Password Expiration Warning","rule_id_src":"SV-25048r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25048","rule_version":"3.054","rule_title":"Users are not warned in advance that their passwords will expire.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cInteractive Logon: Prompt user to change password before expiration\u201d to \u201c14\u201d days or more.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cInteractive Logon: Prompt user to change password before expiration\u201d is not set to  \u201c14\" days or more, then this is a finding. \n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  PasswordExpiryWarning\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  14","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting configures the system to display a warning to users telling them how many days are left before their password expires.  By giving the user advanced warning, the user has time to construct a sufficiently strong password.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6225","uuid":"5f7a3633-8f60-4a0e-ae9a-778d923ba464","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2B6F64D68C3750B66098BBA16B4A558606679878\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Users are not warned in advance that their passwords will expire.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1173","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1173","title":"Global System Objects Permission Strength","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1173","severity":"low","group_title":"Global System Objects Permission Strength","rule_id_src":"SV-25115r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25115","rule_version":"3.055","rule_title":"The default permissions of global system objects are not increased.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cSystem Objects: Strengthen default permissions of internal system objects (e.g. Symbolic links)\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cSystem Objects: Strengthen default permissions of internal system objects (e.g. Symbolic links)\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\\n\nValue Name:  ProtectionMode\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows system maintains a global list of shared system resources such as DOS device names, mutexes, and semaphores. Each type of object is created with a default DACL that specifies who can access the objects with what permissions. If this policy is enabled, the default DACL is stronger, allowing non-admin users to read shared objects, but not modify shared objects that they did not create.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8696","uuid":"7e259a27-1808-43be-811d-8e82199ba518","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 897873285FDFF5A67B65B84935B145B30B69683B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The default permissions of global system objects are not increased.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-1174","group_tree":[{"id":"V-1174","title":"Idle Time Before Suspending a Session.","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-1174","severity":"low","group_title":"Idle Time Before Suspending a Session.","rule_id_src":"SV-25057r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25057","rule_version":"4.028","rule_title":"The amount of idle time required before suspending a session must be properly set.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft Network Server: Amount of idle time required before suspending session\" to \"15\" minutes or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Microsoft Network Server: Amount of idle time required before suspending session\" is not set to \"15\" minutes or less, this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  autodisconnect\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x0000000f (15) (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Open sessions can increase the avenues of attack on a system.  This setting is used to control when a computer disconnects an inactive SMB session.  If client activity resumes, the session is automatically re-established.  This protects critical and sensitive network data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001133","CCI-002361"],"reference_identifier":"9723","uuid":"4130479d-fa02-4406-ada7-ede56f6cf2d9","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E94B406DD9DEE0C9F69788E4273A5D65E912CED5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The amount of idle time required before suspending a session must be properly set.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-2372","group_tree":[{"id":"V-2372","title":"Reversible Password Encryption","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-2372","severity":"medium","group_title":"Reversible Password Encryption","rule_id_src":"SV-25013r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25013","rule_version":"3.057","rule_title":"Reversible password encryption must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Password Policy >> \"Store password using reversible encryption\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Account Policies >> Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Store password using reversible encryption\" is not disabled, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Storing passwords using reversible encryption is essentially the same as storing clear-text versions of the passwords.  For this reason, this policy must never be enabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000196"],"reference_identifier":"1251","uuid":"b7588009-5d91-4eb8-b1f6-96e042df7ad3","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E77247B5573EF64297EABBB858703DB37D4901B4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Reversible password encryption must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-2374","group_tree":[{"id":"V-2374","title":"Disable Media Autoplay","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-2374","severity":"high","group_title":"Disable Media Autoplay","rule_id_src":"SV-25175r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25175","rule_version":"3.059","rule_title":"The system is configured to autoplay removable media.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> AutoPlay Policies -> \u201cTurn off AutoPlay\u201d to \u201cEnabled:All Drives\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name:\tNoDriveTypeAutorun\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x000000ff (255)\n\nNote:  If the value for NoDriveTypeAutorun is entered manually, it should be entered as \u201cff\u201d when Hexadecimal is selected or \u201c255\u201d with Decimal selected.  Using the policy specified in the Fixes section will enter it correctly.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Autoplay begins reading from a drive as soon as you insert media in the drive.  As a result, the setup file of programs and the music on audio media starts immediately.  By default, autoplay is disabled on removable drives, such as the floppy disk drive (but not the CD-ROM drive) and on network drives.  If you enable this policy, you can also disable autoplay on all drives.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"4133","uuid":"814c419d-8563-481f-9b18-da1f90a908c3","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 59C2EC8273E65C3F8D3024FEF5C8E4EF326FD72F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system is configured to autoplay removable media.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-2908","group_tree":[{"id":"V-2908","title":"Unencrypted Remote Access","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-2908","severity":"high","group_title":"Unencrypted Remote Access","rule_id_src":"SV-25003r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25003","rule_version":"3.061","rule_title":"Unencrypted remote access to system services must not be permitted.","fix_text":"Require encryption for remote access.\n\nEncryption of userid and password information is always required.\n\nEncryption of administrator data is always required.\n\nEncryption of user data coming from or going outside the network firewall is required.\n\nEncryption of the user data inside the network firewall is also highly recommended.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify encryption is required for remote access.\n\nIf userid and password information are not encrypted, this is a finding.\n\nIf administrator data is not encrypted, this is a finding.\n\nIf user data coming from or going outside the enclave is not encrypted, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unencrypted access to system services may permit user identification and passwords that are being transmitted in clear text to be intercepted.  This could provide an intruder access to the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000068"],"reference_identifier":"5300","uuid":"d5a571b0-6203-4cdd-8151-20f254c300e2","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 55EEA435891EC9D73744F689A20A930F3CB67BB2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unencrypted remote access to system services must not be permitted.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3245","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3245","title":"File share ACLs","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3245","severity":"medium","group_title":"File share ACLs","rule_id_src":"SV-25006r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25006","rule_version":"2.015","rule_title":"File share permissions must be reconfigured to remove the Everyone group.","fix_text":"Remove permissions from the \"Everyone\" group from locally-created file shares and assign them to authorized groups.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Open the Computer Management Console.\nExpand the \"System Tools\" object in the left pane.\nExpand the \"Shared Folders\" object.\nSelect the \"Shares\" object.\nRight click any user-created shares (ignore administrative shares; the system will prompt you if Properties are selected for administrative shares).\nSelect \"Properties\".\nSelect the \"Share Permissions\" tab.\n\nIf user-created file shares have not been reconfigured to remove ACL permissions from the \"Everyone\" group, this is a finding.\n\nIf shares created by applications require the \"Everyone\" group, this must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Shares on a system can provide network access, exposing sensitive information.  If a share is necessary, permissions must be reconfigured to give the minimum access to those accounts that require it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"7940","uuid":"0bf2a878-420a-4345-b484-c689ce6b5099","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F2A63F70F85341B9926374101A95227E9EBAA64B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'File share permissions must be reconfigured to remove the Everyone group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3337","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3337","title":"Anonymous SID/Name Translation","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3337","severity":"high","group_title":"Anonymous SID/Name Translation","rule_id_src":"SV-25080r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25080","rule_version":"3.062","rule_title":"Anonymous SID/Name translation must not be allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous SID/Name translation can provide sensitive information for accessing a system.  Only authorized users must be able to perform such translations.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1990","uuid":"56629ee1-e8fd-4023-a9dd-42a12133746c","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2F15E47BB1B1BD2ACB0F552CE9545213111F5FB4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Anonymous SID/Name translation must not be allowed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3338","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3338","title":"Anonymous Access to Named Pipes","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3338","severity":"high","group_title":"Anonymous Access to Named Pipes","rule_id_src":"SV-25093r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25093","rule_version":"3.063","rule_title":"Named pipes that can be accessed anonymously must be configured to contain no values.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Named pipes that can be accessed anonymously\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network access: Named pipes that can be accessed anonymously\" contains any entries, this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  NullSessionPipes\n\nValue Type:  REG_MULTI_SZ\nValue:  (blank)\n\nNote:  Legitimate applications may add entries to this registry value.  If an application requires these entries to function properly and is documented with the ISSO, this would not be a finding.  Documentation should contain supporting information from the vendor's instructions.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Named pipes that can be accessed anonymously provide the potential for gaining unauthorized system access.  Pipes are internal system communications processes.  They are identified internally by ID numbers that vary between systems.  To make access to these processes easier, these pipes are given names that do not vary between systems.  This setting controls which of these pipes anonymous users may access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"9887","uuid":"73be971e-db07-43ac-bfe5-74733fed5265","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 79612A7EAE10BE07DD440779CF863867E0A3F0BC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Named pipes that can be accessed anonymously must be configured to contain no values.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3339","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3339","title":"Remotely Accessible Registry Paths","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3339","severity":"high","group_title":"Remotely Accessible Registry Paths","rule_id_src":"SV-25095r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25095","rule_version":"3.064","rule_title":"Unauthorized remotely accessible registry paths must not be configured.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Remotely accessible registry paths\" with the following entries:\n\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\ProductOptions \nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Server Applications \nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network access: Remotely accessible registry paths\" contains entries besides the following, this is a finding:\n\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\ProductOptions\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Server Applications\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurePipeServers\\Winreg\\AllowedExactPaths\\\n\nValue Name:  Machine\n\nValue Type:  REG_MULTI_SZ\nValue:  As defined in policy above\n\nNote:  Legitimate applications may add entries to this registry value.  If an application requires these entries to function properly and is documented with the ISSO, this would not be a finding.  Documentation should contain supporting information from the vendor's instructions.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The registry is integral to the function, security, and stability of the Windows system.  Some processes may require remote access to the registry.  This setting controls which registry paths are accessible from a remote computer.  These registry paths must be limited, as they could give unauthorized individuals access to the registry.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"1859","uuid":"a45d7556-2bb8-41cd-8b58-313e971fcad5","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6C063F49634920C57B5CC40275796411BF8F9E37\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Unauthorized remotely accessible registry paths must not be configured.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3340","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3340","title":"Anonymous Access to Network Shares","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3340","severity":"high","group_title":"Anonymous Access to Network Shares","rule_id_src":"SV-25101r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25101","rule_version":"3.065","rule_title":"Unauthorized shares can be accessed anonymously.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cNetwork access: Shares that can be accessed anonymously\u201d to be defined but containing no entries (Blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options. \n\nIf the value for \u201cNetwork access: Shares that can be accessed anonymously\u201d includes any entries, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  NullSessionShares\n\nValue Type:  REG_MULTI_SZ\nValue:  (Blank)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This is a Category 1 finding because of the potential for gaining unauthorized system access. Any shares listed can be accessed by any network user.  This could lead to the exposure or corruption of sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"5903","uuid":"139e8817-1695-4282-9f94-f816bca07f70","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 74565E92BF01AC0B048FC94E7F0EB2911FF3D1B7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Unauthorized shares can be accessed anonymously.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3343","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3343","title":"Remote Assistance - Solicit Remote Assistance","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3343","severity":"high","group_title":"Remote Assistance - Solicit Remote Assistance","rule_id_src":"SV-25170r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25170","rule_version":"3.068","rule_title":"Solicited Remote Assistance is allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the system to disable Remote Assistance by setting the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Remote Assistance \u201cSolicited Remote Assistance\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nSubkey: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\ \n\nValue Name: fAllowToGetHelp\n \nType: REG_DWORD \nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls whether or not solicited remote assistance is allowed from this computer.  Solicited assistance is help that is specifically requested by the user.  This is a Category 1 finding because it may allow unauthorized parties access to the resources on the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"4647","uuid":"3257c439-bc88-470a-8657-c492946a325d","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5DC8077B3DC644DFB4C365570093E73B7BEF3B00\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Solicited Remote Assistance is allowed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3344","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3344","title":"Limit Blank Passwords","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3344","severity":"high","group_title":"Limit Blank Passwords","rule_id_src":"SV-25022r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25022","rule_version":"4.036","rule_title":"The use of local accounts with blank passwords is not restricted to console logons only.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cAccounts: Limit local account use of blank passwords to console logon only\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  Expand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\n\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cAccounts: Limit local account use of blank passwords to console logon only\u201d is not set to \u201d Enabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\n\nValue Name:  LimitBlankPasswordUse\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This is a Category 1 finding because no accounts with blank passwords should exist on a system.  The password policy should prevent this from occurring.  However, if a local account with a blank password does exist, enabling this setting will limit the account to local console logon only.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2598","uuid":"5e23cf82-9d97-4c8d-940c-d855fcf60de3","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3CE0E60503CFBB9E9A7F5E245F040D88533E2697\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The use of local accounts with blank passwords is not restricted to console logons only.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3347","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3347","title":"Internet Information System (IIS)","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3347","severity":"high","group_title":"Internet Information System (IIS)","rule_id_src":"SV-25253r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25253","rule_version":"5.016","rule_title":"Internet Information System (IIS) or its subcomponents must not be installed on a workstation.","fix_text":"Remove \"Internet Information Services\" from the system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"To verify whether IIS is installed, perform the following:\n\nOpen Control Panel.\nSelect \"Programs and Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\n\nIf the entry for \"Internet Information Services\" is selected, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires IIS or a subset to be installed to function, this needs be documented with the ISSO.  In addition, any applicable requirements from the IIS STIG must be addressed.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Installation of Internet Information System (IIS) may allow unauthorized internet services to be hosted.  Websites must only be hosted on servers that have been designed for that purpose and can be adequately secured.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5898","uuid":"a5a9c740-a4e9-4fc1-981b-fababddbfbee","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0E10A1606DC49931BD98BCB5F4F81F3A298B896F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Internet Information System (IIS) or its subcomponents must not be installed on a workstation.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3373","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3373","title":"Maximum Machine Account Password Age","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3373","severity":"low","group_title":"Maximum Machine Account Password Age","rule_id_src":"SV-25042r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25042","rule_version":"4.043","rule_title":"The maximum age for machine account passwords is not set to requirements.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cDomain Member: Maximum Machine Account Password Age\u201d to 30 or less, but not 0.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cDomain Member: Maximum Machine Account Password Age\u201d is 0 or greater than 30 (30 is the default), this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: MaximumPasswordAge\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 30","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the maximum password age that a machine account may have.  This setting should be set to no more than 30 days, ensuring the machine changes its password monthly.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1286","uuid":"693230f7-18b8-4e4d-96a0-3596046850ab","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 586404F1C4DECE7ED4C75562F5ADB7962C724016\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The maximum age for machine account passwords is not set to requirements.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3374","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3374","title":"Strong Session Key","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3374","severity":"medium","group_title":"Strong Session Key","rule_id_src":"SV-25043r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25043","rule_version":"4.044","rule_title":"The system is not configured to require a strong session key.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cDomain Member: Require Strong (Windows 2000 or Later) Session Key\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cDomain Member: Require Strong (Windows 2000 or Later) Session Key\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  RequireStrongKey\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1\n \nWarning: This setting may prevent a system from being joined to a domain if not configured consistently between systems.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the requirement that strong session keys be used between systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"2425","uuid":"18d61a0b-56aa-4db3-93c2-df24ff8a7a6d","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9E84BDD86B2ED4C741547C34F2B1866099615336\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system is not configured to require a strong session key.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3375","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3375","title":"Domain Controller authentication for unlock","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3375","severity":"low","group_title":"Domain Controller authentication for unlock","rule_id_src":"SV-25049r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25049","rule_version":"4.045","rule_title":"Domain Controller authentication is not required to unlock the workstation.","fix_text":"Workstations - Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cInteractive logon: Require domain controller authentication to unlock workstation\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Workstations - Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. Expand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \n\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options. \n\nIf the value for \u201cInteractive logon: Require domain controller authentication to unlock workstation\u201d is not set to \u201cDisabled\u201d, then this is a finding. \n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  ForceUnlockLogon\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the behavior of the system when you attempt to unlock the workstation.  If this setting is enabled, the system will pass the credentials to the domain controller (if in a domain) for authentication before allowing the system to be unlocked.  This may cause a denial of service if the workstation looses connectivity to the domain controller.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7672","uuid":"5fcb6d8f-adcd-4aea-af15-be8b60735e55","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6FFEF3D1165FC79F1D92858A66D2D8F0C39002FD\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Domain Controller authentication is not required to unlock the workstation.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3376","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3376","title":"Storage of Passwords and Credentials","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3376","severity":"medium","group_title":"Storage of Passwords and Credentials","rule_id_src":"SV-25091r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25091","rule_version":"3.070","rule_title":"The system is configured to permit storage of passwords and credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cNetwork access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.  \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cNetwork access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name:  DisableDomainCreds\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication on the local system.  Such credentials should never be stored on the local machine as that may lead to account compromise.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"3193","uuid":"94d4b3c4-e85d-4ea8-ba90-16d4dfc8907f","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 72069D0C4634D414519B5B6C627D55148489727B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system is configured to permit storage of passwords and credentials.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3377","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3377","title":"Everyone Anonymous rights","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3377","severity":"medium","group_title":"Everyone Anonymous rights","rule_id_src":"SV-25092r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25092","rule_version":"3.071","rule_title":"The system is configured to give anonymous users Everyone rights.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cNetwork access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.  \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cNetwork access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\u201d is not set to \u201cDisabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name:  EveryoneIncludesAnonymous\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting helps define the permissions that anonymous users have.  If this setting is enabled then anonymous users have the same rights and permissions as the built-in Everyone group.  Anonymous users should not have these permissions or rights.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1605","uuid":"de368660-f83a-4f27-9df8-a0788ed42500","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ADA76333F3EAE42A10A64AFFAF79135F005AC9D4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system is configured to give anonymous users Everyone rights.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3378","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3378","title":"Sharing and Security Model for Local Accounts","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3378","severity":"medium","group_title":"Sharing and Security Model for Local Accounts","rule_id_src":"SV-25103r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25103","rule_version":"3.072","rule_title":"The system is not configured to use the Classic security model.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cNetwork access: Sharing and security model for local accounts\u201d to \u201cClassic - local users authenticate as themselves\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cNetwork access: Sharing and security model for local accounts\u201d is not set to \u201cClassic - local users authenticate as themselves\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name:  ForceGuest\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows includes two network-sharing security models - Classic and Guest only. With the classic model, local accounts must be password protected; otherwise, anyone can use guest user accounts to access shared system resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"9992","uuid":"b54363c6-0ac8-41ae-a0fd-2dc24347e7c3","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E20BE6DA7F66EB566F4FD885B0EFCF247ECB86BE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system is not configured to use the Classic security model.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3379","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3379","title":"LAN Manager Hash stored","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3379","severity":"high","group_title":"LAN Manager Hash stored","rule_id_src":"SV-25104r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25104","rule_version":"3.073","rule_title":"The system is configured to store the LAN Manager hash of the password in the SAM.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cNetwork security: Do not store LAN Manager hash value on next password change\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cNetwork security: Do not store LAN Manager hash value on next password change\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name:  NoLMHash\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls whether or not a LAN Manager hash of the password is stored in the SAM the next time the password is changed.  The LAN Manager hash uses a weak encryption algorithm and there are several tools available that use this hash to retrieve account passwords.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000196"],"reference_identifier":"6586","uuid":"9236940d-ad66-4b02-97c8-1fe70a306d75","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 76422E4EF6A9057D8F588474D37AD62AB454351A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system is configured to store the LAN Manager hash of the password in the SAM.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3380","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3380","title":"Force Logoff When Logon Hours Expire","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3380","severity":"medium","group_title":"Force Logoff When Logon Hours Expire","rule_id_src":"SV-25818r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25818","rule_version":"3.074","rule_title":"The system must be configured to force users to log off when their allowed logon hours expire.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Force logoff when logon hours expire\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network security: Force logoff when logon hours expire\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Limiting logon hours can help protect data by only allowing access during specified times.  This setting controls whether or not users are forced to log off when their allowed logon hours expire.  If logon hours are set for users, then this must be enforced.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001133"],"reference_identifier":"7185","uuid":"c29fd1e8-a5e7-4eb6-b52b-5228625c4b47","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FB6838E6D081116566A9F8C9A1FC6271504C06EB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to force users to log off when their allowed logon hours expire.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3381","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3381","title":"LDAP Client Signing","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3381","severity":"medium","group_title":"LDAP Client Signing","rule_id_src":"SV-25106r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25106","rule_version":"3.075","rule_title":"The system is not configured to recommended LDAP client signing requirements.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cNetwork security: LDAP client signing requirements\u201d to \u201cNegotiate signing\u201d at a minimum.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\t\nIf the value for \u201cNetwork security: LDAP client signing requirements\u201d is not set to at least \u201cNegotiate signing\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LDAP\\\n\nValue Name:  LDAPClientIntegrity\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the signing requirements for LDAP clients.  This setting should be set to Negotiate signing or Require signing depending on the environment and type of LDAP server in use.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5776","uuid":"e28048fb-33c8-4761-a273-49e8f8aeec5b","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0119770702B4D84EFEEFDC73D1E1EF6A2DBAA0BF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system is not configured to recommended LDAP client signing requirements.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3382","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3382","title":"Session Security for NTLM SSP Based Clients","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3382","severity":"medium","group_title":"Session Security for NTLM SSP Based Clients","rule_id_src":"SV-25107r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25107","rule_version":"3.076","rule_title":"The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based clients.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) clients\" to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\", \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) clients\" is not set to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name:  NTLMMinClientSec\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with RPC sessions.  All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1546","uuid":"9fb21a49-4c96-42ac-890f-c71358d3c6e7","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E99340D9902B0314AF338DF419D8F959A90BB052\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based clients.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3383","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3383","title":"FIPS Compliant Algorithms","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3383","severity":"medium","group_title":"FIPS Compliant Algorithms","rule_id_src":"SV-25113r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25113","rule_version":"3.077","rule_title":"The system is not configured to use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cSystem cryptography: Use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cSystem cryptography: Use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\FIPSAlgorithmPolicy\\\n\nValue Name:  Enabled\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1\n \nWarning:  Clients with this setting enabled will not be able to communicate via digitally encrypted or signed protocols with servers that do not support these algorithms.  Both the browser and web server must be configured to use TLS, or the browser will not be able to connect to a secure site.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting ensures that the system uses algorithms that are FIPS compliant for encryption, hashing, and signing.  FIPS compliant algorithms meet specific standards established by the U.S. Government and should be the algorithms used for all OS encryption functions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"2495","uuid":"f76748c4-4bb1-46b9-adbf-710cdfc48e96","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 67F28F97FCA446EFEB692101DAB9A283FEEF531C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system is not configured to use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3385","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3385","title":"Case Insensitivity for Non-Windows","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3385","severity":"medium","group_title":"Case Insensitivity for Non-Windows","rule_id_src":"SV-25114r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25114","rule_version":"3.078","rule_title":"The system must be configured to require case insensitivity for non-Windows subsystems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"System Objects: Require case insensitivity for non-Windows subsystems\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"System Objects: Require case insensitivity for non-Windows subsystems\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\Kernel\\\n\nValue Name:  ObCaseInsensitive\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the behavior of non-Windows subsystems when dealing with the case of arguments or commands.  Case sensitivity could lead to the access of files or commands that must be restricted.  To prevent this from happening, case insensitivity restrictions must be required.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9011","uuid":"dbef87bb-18e1-472d-8383-5ba3ad3bb35a","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6878D57F9FF49408B1FCBE779DB3DB6B6810372F\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The system must be configured to require case insensitivity for non-Windows subsystems.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3453","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3453","title":"TS/RDS - Password Prompting","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3453","severity":"medium","group_title":"TS/RDS - Password Prompting","rule_id_src":"SV-25261r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25261","rule_version":"5.042","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services is not configured to always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Security \u201cAlways prompt for password upon connection\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name:  fPromptForPassword\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the ability of users to supply passwords automatically as part of their remote desktop connection.  Disabling this setting would allow anyone to use the stored credentials in a connection item to connect to the terminal server.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"2316","uuid":"48197fb9-9afa-40ae-b66b-f67fd17d84ba","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 83AE801F76B9E6EBD763A931AE9D4D27397D5EAE\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Remote Desktop Services is not configured to always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3454","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3454","title":"TS/RDS - Set Encryption Level","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3454","severity":"medium","group_title":"TS/RDS - Set Encryption Level","rule_id_src":"SV-25262r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25262","rule_version":"5.043","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services is not configured with the client connection encryption set to the required level.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Security \u201cSet client connection encryption level\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d and \u201cHigh Level\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name:  MinEncryptionLevel\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  3","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote connections must be encrypted to prevent interception of data or sensitive information.  Selecting \u201cHigh Level\u201d will ensure encryption of Remote Desktop Services sessions in both directions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000068","CCI-002890"],"reference_identifier":"8840","uuid":"d120cb18-a1c9-4568-bb99-157bf68b54a7","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 31966219253EF622DEBAD971118644837CD294A8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote Desktop Services is not configured with the client connection encryption set to the required level.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3455","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3455","title":"TS/RDS - Do Not Use Temp Folders","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3455","severity":"medium","group_title":"TS/RDS - Do Not Use Temp Folders","rule_id_src":"SV-25266r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25266","rule_version":"5.044","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must be configured to use session-specific temporary folders.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Temporary Folders \u201cDo not use temporary folders per session\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name:  PerSessionTempDir\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If a communal temporary folder is used for remote desktop sessions, it might be possible for users to access other users' temporary folders. If this setting is enabled, only one temporary folder is used for all remote desktop sessions. Per session temporary folders must be established.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1201","uuid":"4fcce5eb-276e-4fc3-a500-93a0d47fc7d8","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 15005061D9D492B2CCF1AF4F4D46D42C4500ED8D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote Desktop Services must be configured to use session-specific temporary folders.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3456","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3456","title":"TS/RDS - Delete Temp Folders","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3456","severity":"medium","group_title":"TS/RDS - Delete Temp Folders","rule_id_src":"SV-25265r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25265","rule_version":"5.045","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services is not configured to delete temporary folders.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Temporary Folders \u201cDo not delete temp folder upon exit\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name:  DeleteTempDirsOnExit\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the deletion of the temporary folders when the session is terminated.  Temporary folders should always be deleted after a session is over to prevent hard disk clutter and potential leakage of information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2425","uuid":"983b7ca9-22e0-42fb-a665-79d78e8632d5","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7F9BEE55B79C004191AEC20CDFFD1BE146535DAA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote Desktop Services is not configured to delete temporary folders.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3469","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3469","title":"Group Policy - Do Not Turn off Background Refresh","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3469","severity":"medium","group_title":"Group Policy - Do Not Turn off Background Refresh","rule_id_src":"SV-51982r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-51982","rule_version":"WINCC-000029","rule_title":"Group Policies must be refreshed in the background if the user is logged on.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Group Policy -> \"Turn off background refresh of Group Policy\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Review the registry.\nIf the following registry value does not exist, this is not a finding (this is the expected result from configuring the policy as outlined in the Fix section).\nIf the following registry value exists but is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\system\\\n\nValue Name: DisableBkGndGroupPolicy\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If this setting is enabled, then Group Policy settings are not refreshed while a user is currently logged on. This could lead to instances when a user does not have the latest changes to a policy applied and is therefore operating in an insecure context.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8652","uuid":"7349d640-b5dd-4048-a820-f499cfb395f3","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A8E4893E7FFDE424EF9C3CE78EC0779A9494F70D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Group Policies must be refreshed in the background if the user is logged on.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3470","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3470","title":"Remote Assistance - Offer Remote Assistance","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3470","severity":"medium","group_title":"Remote Assistance - Offer Remote Assistance","rule_id_src":"SV-25169r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25169","rule_version":"3.082","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent unsolicited remote assistance offers.","fix_text":"Configure the system to prevent unsolicited remote assistance offers by setting the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Remote Assistance >> \"Offer Remote Assistance\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name:  fAllowUnsolicited\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0\n\nOffer remote assistance may be enabled on workstations if mitigations are in place.  This must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote assistance allows another user to view or take control of the local session of a user.  Unsolicited remote assistance is help that is offered by the remote user.  This may allow unauthorized parties access to the resources on the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"9238","uuid":"4207a65a-d495-4500-bbec-7f1c74bb999f","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8EF5F6E29DCA4A332032D9241439F1F4EA51F8F7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to prevent unsolicited remote assistance offers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3472","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3472","title":"Windows Time Service - Configure NTP Client","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3472","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows Time Service - Configure NTP Client","rule_id_src":"SV-25174r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25174","rule_version":"3.084","rule_title":"The system is configured to use an unauthorized time server.","fix_text":"If the system needs to be configured to an NTP server, configure the system to point to an authorized time server by setting the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Windows Time Service -> Time Providers \u201cConfigure Windows NTP Client\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d, and configure the \u201cNtpServer\u201d field to point to an authorized time server.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Review the following registry values:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\W32time\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: Type\nType: REG_SZ\nValue: Possible values are NoSync, NTP, NT5DS, AllSync\n\nAnd\n\nValue Name: NTPServer\nType: REG_SZ\nValue: \"address of the time server\"\n\nThe following would be a finding:\n\"Type\" has a value of \"NTP\" or \"Allsync\" AND the \"NTPServer\" value is set to \"time.windows.com\" or other unauthorized server.\n\nThe following would not be a finding:\nThe referenced registry values do not exist.\n\"Type\" has a value of \"NoSync\" or \"NT5DS\".\n\"Type\" has a value of \"NTP\" or \"Allsync\" AND the \"NTPServer\" is blank or configured to an authorized time server.\n\nFor DoD organizations, the US Naval Observatory operates stratum 1 time servers, identified at http://tycho.usno.navy.mil/ntp.html. Time synchronization will occur through a hierarchy of time servers down to the local level. Clients and lower level servers will synchronize with an authorized time server in the hierarchy. \n\nDomain joined systems are automatically configured to synchronize with domain controllers and would not be a finding unless this is changed.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows Time Service controls time synchronization settings.  Time synchronization is essential for authentication and auditing purposes.  If the Windows Time Service is used, it should synchronize with a secure, authorized time source.   Domain joined systems are automatically configured to synchronize with domain controllers.  If an NTP server is configured it should synchronize with a secure, authorized time source.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001891"],"reference_identifier":"7128","uuid":"4e94facc-9b95-4cf9-9938-5118a919b782","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7728D340627C86AD0B4CB9CC1FDCF08FB197D390\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system is configured to use an unauthorized time server.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3479","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3479","title":"Safe DLL Search Mode","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3479","severity":"medium","group_title":"Safe DLL Search Mode","rule_id_src":"SV-25072r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25072","rule_version":"3.088","rule_title":"The system is not configured to use Safe DLL search mode.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cMSS: (SafeDllSearchMode) Enable Safe DLL search mode (recommended)\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cMSS: (SafeDllSearchMode) Enable Safe DLL search mode (recommended)\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding. \n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\\n\nValue Name:  SafeDllSearchMode\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The default search behavior, when an application calls a function in a Dynamic Link Library (DLL), is to search the current directory followed by the directories contained in the systems path environment variable.  An unauthorized DLL, inserted into an applications working directory, could allow malicious code to be run on the system.  Setting this policy value forces the system to search the %Systemroot% for the DLL before searching the current directory or the rest of the path.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9900","uuid":"33224eaa-0bf6-4d97-a822-909244436ed6","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EA254E4AFBF5C817E1C5C185A62FBF086A8C06BF\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The system is not configured to use Safe DLL search mode.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3480","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3480","title":"Media Player - Disable Automatic Updates","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3480","severity":"medium","group_title":"Media Player - Disable Automatic Updates","rule_id_src":"SV-40098r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-40098","rule_version":"5.060","rule_title":"Media Player must be configured to prevent automatic checking for updates.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Media Player -> \"Prevent Automatic Updates\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsMediaPlayer\\\n\nValue Name: DisableAutoupdate\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled system updates can introduce issues to a system. The automatic check for updates performed by Windows Media Player must be disabled to ensure a constant platform and to prevent the introduction of unknown\\untested software on the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCE-10602-1","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"8165","uuid":"c0e569d0-858a-47fc-b4c1-bbf2621b9196","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BAA5CE9AE20B7A41AB8560E20F69BDC9166875C5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Media Player must be configured to prevent automatic checking for updates.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3666","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3666","title":"Session Security for NTLM SSP based Servers","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3666","severity":"medium","group_title":"Session Security for NTLM SSP based Servers","rule_id_src":"SV-25108r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25108","rule_version":"3.089","rule_title":"The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) servers\" to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\", \"Require 128-bit encryption (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) servers\" is not set to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name:  NTLMMinServerSec\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with RPC sessions. All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7787","uuid":"2fb09e26-0694-49aa-b884-33f4a18f46f2","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2724AF809DBC08F57EE2F0A82D7BBDA1471C4EBC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based servers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-3828","group_tree":[{"id":"V-3828","title":"Security-Related Software Patches","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-3828","severity":"medium","group_title":"Security-Related Software Patches","rule_id_src":"SV-25254r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25254","rule_version":"2.019","rule_title":"Security-related software patches are not applied.","fix_text":"Apply all Microsoft security-related patches to the Windows system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that the site is applying all security-related patches released by Microsoft.  Determine the local site method for doing this (e.g., connection to a WSUS server, local procedure, etc.).\n\nSeverity Override: If any of the patches not installed are Microsoft \u2018Critical\u2019, then the category code should be elevated to \u20181\u2019.\n\nNote: If a penetration scan has been run on the network, it will report findings if security-related updates are not applied.  Then, this check may be marked as \u201cNot Applicable\u201d.\n\nSome applications (such as DMS and GCSS) use a system release process to keep systems current. If this is the case, then these systems should be at the current release.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Major software vendors release security patches and hot fixes to their products when security vulnerabilities are discovered.  It is essential that these updates be applied in a timely manner to prevent unauthorized persons from exploiting identified vulnerabilities.\n\nThe severity code may be elevated to a Category I if patches deemed Critical have not been applied.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4337","uuid":"b41d4994-f682-4d0f-acaa-9e320d4fce18","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AF63E02F1FC6CB36A8880F92E1EE9B4096C23FB7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Security-related software patches are not applied.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-4108","group_tree":[{"id":"V-4108","title":"Audit Log Warning Level","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-4108","severity":"low","group_title":"Audit Log Warning Level","rule_id_src":"SV-25078r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25078","rule_version":"3.092","rule_title":"The system must generate an audit event when the audit log reaches a percentage of full threshold.","fix_text":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, or automatically archive full logs, this is NA.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"MSS: (WarningLevel) Percentage threshold for the security event log at which the system will generate a warning\" to \"90%\" or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, or automatically archive full logs, this is NA.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\nAnalyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"MSS: (WarningLevel) Percentage threshold for the security event log at which the system will generate a warning\" is not set to \"90%\" or less, this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Eventlog\\Security\\\n\nValue Name:  WarningLevel\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x0000005a (90) (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Audit records may be lost if the security log becomes full.  When the audit log reaches a given percent full, an audit event is written to the security log.  An event is recorded as a success audit under the category of System.  This option may be especially useful if the audit logs are set to be cleared manually.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000139","CCI-001855","CCI-001858"],"reference_identifier":"8765","uuid":"240e21dc-e8f1-41ec-9784-5fdf5b9c430a","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5F371B30918AAB1BCB02D5B53DD1108A24336B79\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must generate an audit event when the audit log reaches a percentage of full threshold.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-4110","group_tree":[{"id":"V-4110","title":"Disable IP Source Routing","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-4110","severity":"low","group_title":"Disable IP Source Routing","rule_id_src":"SV-25065r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25065","rule_version":"3.094","rule_title":"The system is configured to allow IP source routing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cMSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)\u201d to \u201cHighest protection, source routing is completely disabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cMSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)\u201d is not set to \u201cHighest protection, source routing is completely disabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  2","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Protects against IP source routing spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1700","uuid":"527eb93f-0425-4aca-88c2-946c966ddd6b","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4DF4B9A539B69B668AFFB6E6BE7A5E2000780EB3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system is configured to allow IP source routing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-4111","group_tree":[{"id":"V-4111","title":"Disable ICMP Redirect","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-4111","severity":"low","group_title":"Disable ICMP Redirect","rule_id_src":"SV-25066r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25066","rule_version":"3.095","rule_title":"The system is configured to redirect ICMP.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cMSS: (EnableICMPRedirect) Allow ICMP redirects to override OSPF generated routes\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cMSS: (EnableICMPRedirect) Allow ICMP redirects to override OSPF generated routes\u201d is not set to \u201cDisabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableICMPRedirect\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When disabled, forces ICMP to be routed via shortest path first.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7303","uuid":"dee529c7-1d14-4f73-bd88-43c6a4031372","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-4112","group_tree":[{"id":"V-4112","title":"Disable Router Discovery","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-4112","severity":"low","group_title":"Disable Router Discovery","rule_id_src":"SV-25071r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25071","rule_version":"3.104","rule_title":"The system is configured to detect and configure default gateway addresses.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cMSS: (PerformRouterDiscovery) Allow IRDP to detect and configure Default Gateway addresses (could lead to DoS)\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cMSS: (PerformRouterDiscovery) Allow IRDP to detect and configure Default Gateway addresses (could lead to DoS)\u201d is not set to \u201cDisabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nSubkey: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: PerformRouterDiscovery\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enables or disables the Internet Router Discovery Protocol (IRDP) used to detect and configure default gateway addresses on the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"2861","uuid":"cdd9f18d-28b8-4850-99b6-5993ef306c33","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D422353938955649C83285B872A4D0DC37823E11\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system is configured to detect and configure default gateway addresses.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-4113","group_tree":[{"id":"V-4113","title":"TCP Connection Keep-Alive Time","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-4113","severity":"low","group_title":"TCP Connection Keep-Alive Time","rule_id_src":"SV-25068r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25068","rule_version":"3.097","rule_title":"The system is configured for a greater keep-alive time than recommended.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cMSS: (KeepAliveTime) How often keep-alive packets are sent in milliseconds\u201d to \u201c300000 or 5 minutes (recommended)\u201d or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  Expand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\n\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cMSS: (KeepAliveTime) How often keep-alive packets are sent in milliseconds\u201d is not set to \u201c300000 or 5 minutes (recommended)\u201d or less, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nSubkey: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: KeepAliveTime\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  300000","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Controls how often TCP sends a keep-alive packet in attempting to verify that an idle connection is still intact.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"8932","uuid":"fd1c24e6-5519-4a7a-ba82-c97ae89786a2","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 183BD8168CC0C3ED490124ACC0C3ACD05B0C0BFD\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The system is configured for a greater keep-alive time than recommended.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-4116","group_tree":[{"id":"V-4116","title":"Name-Release Attacks","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-4116","severity":"low","group_title":"Name-Release Attacks","rule_id_src":"SV-25070r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25070","rule_version":"3.101","rule_title":"The system must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"MSS: (NoNameReleaseOnDemand) Allow the computer to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"MSS: (NoNameReleaseOnDemand) Allow the computer to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netbt\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  NoNameReleaseOnDemand\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to ignore name release requests, except from WINS servers, prevents a denial of service (DoS) attack.  The DoS consists of sending a NetBIOS name release request to the server for each entry in the server's cache, causing a response delay in the normal operation of the servers WINS resolution capability.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"9040","uuid":"a3ad44a9-6cb7-4008-8f00-48ef5e0ec8da","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C094FD4EA7CAF950C014CE582334357244DC607B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-4438","group_tree":[{"id":"V-4438","title":"TCP Data Retransmissions","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-4438","severity":"low","group_title":"TCP Data Retransmissions","rule_id_src":"SV-25077r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25077","rule_version":"5.098","rule_title":"The system must limit how many times unacknowledged TCP data is retransmitted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"MSS: (TcpMaxDataRetransmissions) How many times unacknowledged data is retransmitted (3 recommended, 5 is default)\" to \"3\" or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"MSS: (TcpMaxDataRetransmissions) How many times unacknowledged data is retransmitted (3 recommended, 5 is default)\" is not set to \"3\" or less, this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  TcpMaxDataRetransmissions\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  3 (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In a SYN flood attack, the attacker sends a continuous stream of SYN packets to a server, and the server leaves the half-open connections open until it is overwhelmed and no longer is able to respond to legitimate requests.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"1570","uuid":"23b3c474-887c-46f0-9ea2-779cbd3d0549","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 455751B9739AABC9D2EB63B654B62A5CA6FA6FE6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must limit how many times unacknowledged TCP data is retransmitted.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-4442","group_tree":[{"id":"V-4442","title":"Screen Saver Grace Period","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-4442","severity":"low","group_title":"Screen Saver Grace Period","rule_id_src":"SV-25076r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25076","rule_version":"5.102","rule_title":"This check verifies that Windows is configured to have password protection take effect within a limited time frame when the screen saver becomes active.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cMSS: (ScreenSaverGracePeriod) The time in seconds before the screen saver grace period expires (0 recommended)\u201d to \u201c5\u201d or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cMSS: (ScreenSaverGracePeriod) The time in seconds before the screen saver grace period expires (0 recommended)\u201d is not set to \u201c5\u201d or less, then this is a finding. \n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  ScreenSaverGracePeriod\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  5 (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing more than several seconds makes the computer vulnerable to a potential attack from someone walking up to the console to attempt to log onto the system before the lock takes effect.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8574","uuid":"d59c979b-29b2-4a0f-9bbb-f43fc4c2fa5c","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EFA8488608B8624380F188133391ED0D0F44076F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'This check verifies that Windows is configured to have password protection take effect within a limited time frame when the screen saver becomes active.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-4443","group_tree":[{"id":"V-4443","title":"Remotely Accessible Registry Paths and Sub-Paths","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-4443","severity":"high","group_title":"Remotely Accessible Registry Paths and Sub-Paths","rule_id_src":"SV-25097r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25097","rule_version":"3.108","rule_title":"Unauthorized remotely accessible registry paths and sub-paths must not be configured.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Remotely accessible registry paths and sub-paths\" with the following entries:\n\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\OLAP Server\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Perflib\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Print\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Windows\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\ContentIndex\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Print\\Printers\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server\\UserConfig\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server\\DefaultUserConfiguration\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Eventlog\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Sysmonlog","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network access: Remotely accessible registry paths and sub-paths\" contains entries besides the following, this is a finding:\n\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\OLAP Server\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Perflib\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Print\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Windows\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\ContentIndex\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Print\\Printers\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server\\UserConfig\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server\\DefaultUserConfiguration\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Eventlog\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Sysmonlog\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurePipeServers\\Winreg\\AllowedPaths\\\n\nValue Name:  Machine\n\nValue Type:  REG_MULTI_SZ\nValue:  As defined in policy above\n\nNote:  Legitimate applications may add entries to this registry value.  If an application requires these entries to function properly and is documented with the ISSO, this would not be a finding.  Documentation should contain supporting information from the vendor's instructions.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The registry is integral to the function, security, and stability of the Windows system.  Some processes may require remote access to the registry.  This setting controls which registry paths and sub-paths are accessible from a remote computer.  These registry paths must be limited, as they could give unauthorized individuals access to the registry.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"7567","uuid":"d3eeed99-4fb3-4f54-a2c8-7243e8de273f","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0DC08907F17C5596C7D9E373C34A744BB8A2A5D0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthorized remotely accessible registry paths and sub-paths must not be configured.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-4448","group_tree":[{"id":"V-4448","title":"Group Policy - Registry Policy Processing","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-4448","severity":"medium","group_title":"Group Policy - Registry Policy Processing","rule_id_src":"SV-25149r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25149","rule_version":"3.112","rule_title":"Group Policy objects are not reprocessed if they have not changed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Group Policy \u201cRegistry Policy Processing\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d and select the option \u201cProcess even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows 7 - If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Group Policy\\{35378EAC-683F-11D2-A89A-00C04FBBCFA2}\n\nValue Name:  NoGPOListChanges\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling this setting and then selecting the \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" option ensures that the policies will be reprocessed even if none have been changed. This way, any unauthorized changes are forced to match the domain-based group policy settings again.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6747","uuid":"45e3cae3-ae05-4e4d-8e39-c8f8eaed4eb2","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C0DEA8E8D1CDD687708FA686CB8153B6E4275A4D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Group Policy objects are not reprocessed if they have not changed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-6831","group_tree":[{"id":"V-6831","title":"Encrypting and Signing of Secure Channel Traffic","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-6831","severity":"medium","group_title":"Encrypting and Signing of Secure Channel Traffic","rule_id_src":"SV-25038r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25038","rule_version":"3.113","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic is not encrypted or signed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cDomain Member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always)\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cDomain Member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always)\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  RequireSignOrSeal\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted.  If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted and signed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"1625","uuid":"5b217f96-8ce4-41ea-9a24-623f80a08312","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 35EA3433DB8AC8EDA6086AF6C4E076D798F51E2A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Outgoing secure channel traffic is not encrypted or signed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-6832","group_tree":[{"id":"V-6832","title":"SMB Client Packet Signing (Always)","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-6832","severity":"medium","group_title":"SMB Client Packet Signing (Always)","rule_id_src":"SV-25053r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25053","rule_version":"3.114","rule_title":"The Windows SMB client is not enabled to always perform SMB packet signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cMicrosoft Network Client: Digitally sign communications (always)\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cMicrosoft Network Client: Digitally sign communications (always)\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If this policy is enabled, it causes the Windows Server Message Block (SMB) client to perform SMB packet signing when communicating with an SMB server that is enabled or required to perform SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"3182","uuid":"19cb1e24-aed1-4361-a1a8-2ed794bb583e","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B69121D82CCA47165C54EBA68E18425CB0C0C5C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows SMB client is not enabled to always perform SMB packet signing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-6833","group_tree":[{"id":"V-6833","title":"SMB Server Packet Signing (Always)","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-6833","severity":"medium","group_title":"SMB Server Packet Signing (Always)","rule_id_src":"SV-25059r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25059","rule_version":"3.115","rule_title":"The Windows SMB server is not enabled to always perform SMB packet signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cMicrosoft Network Server: Digitally sign communications (always)\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cMicrosoft Network Server: Digitally sign communications (always)\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If this policy is enabled, it causes the Windows Server Message Block (SMB) server to always perform SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"1434","uuid":"80790e52-d9a0-4076-bd0c-a9109d46b279","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B2FDF48ED35CCF5F49F54A572DC138E6B0F3C57A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows SMB server is not enabled to always perform SMB packet signing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-6834","group_tree":[{"id":"V-6834","title":"Anonymous Access to Named Pipes and Shares","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-6834","severity":"high","group_title":"Anonymous Access to Named Pipes and Shares","rule_id_src":"SV-25099r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25099","rule_version":"3.116","rule_title":"Named pipes and shares can be accessed anonymously.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cNetwork access: Restrict anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cNetwork access: Restrict anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  RestrictNullSessAccess\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This is a Category 1 finding because of the potential for gaining unauthorized system access. \n\nPipes are internal system communications processes.  They are identified internally by ID numbers that vary between systems.  To make access to these processes easier, these pipes are given names that do not vary between systems.  \n\nWhen this setting is disabled, network shares can be accessed by any network user.  This could lead to the exposure or corruption of sensitive data.\n\nThis setting configures Windows to restrict anonymous access to only those shares and pipes listed in \u201cNetwork Access: Named Pipes that can be accessed anonymously\u201d.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"1891","uuid":"99e752e3-85fe-4506-b153-aae0bd290bd9","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DFC4D30489838DDFE7ED2901026AA2DE2B07297E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Named pipes and shares can be accessed anonymously.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-6836","group_tree":[{"id":"V-6836","title":"Minimum Password Length","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-6836","severity":"medium","group_title":"Minimum Password Length","rule_id_src":"SV-25011r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25011","rule_version":"4.013","rule_title":"For systems utilizing a logon ID as the individual identifier, passwords must be a minimum of 14 characters in length.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Account Policies -> Password Policy -> \"Minimum password length\" to at least \"14\" characters.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Account Policies -> Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for the \"Minimum password length\" is less than 14 characters, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Information systems not protected with strong password schemes (including passwords of minimum length) provide the opportunity for anyone to crack the password, thus, gaining access to the system and causing the device, information, or the local network to be compromised.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000205"],"reference_identifier":"7631","uuid":"f14c7eb2-887a-408a-bfe2-df70756b3c46","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-6840","group_tree":[{"id":"V-6840","title":"Password Expiration","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-6840","severity":"medium","group_title":"Password Expiration","rule_id_src":"SV-25211r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25211","rule_version":"4.026","rule_title":"System mechanisms must be implemented to enforce automatic expiration of passwords.","fix_text":"Configure all passwords to expire.  Ensure \"Password never expires\" is not checked on all accounts in Computer Management, Local Users and Groups.  Document any exceptions with the ISSO.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run the DUMPSEC utility.\nSelect \"Dump Users as Table\" from the \"Report\" menu.\nSelect the following fields, and click \"Add\" for each entry.\n\nUserName\nSID\nPswdExpires\nAcctDisabled\nGroups\n\nIf any accounts have \"No\" in the \"PswdExpires\" column, this is a finding.\n\nThe following are exempt from this requirement:\nBuilt-in Administrator Account\nApplication Accounts\n\nAccounts that meet the requirements for allowable exceptions must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Passwords that do not expire increase exposure with a greater probability of being discovered or cracked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000199"],"reference_identifier":"4788","uuid":"1b638e9b-c19e-40be-a54c-a2317a3b766d","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 68B0465C3034E6DA6DCD9E97066E8BCF6056C00E\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'System mechanisms must be implemented to enforce automatic expiration of passwords.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-7002","group_tree":[{"id":"V-7002","title":"Password Requirement","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-7002","severity":"high","group_title":"Password Requirement","rule_id_src":"SV-25210r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25210","rule_version":"4.017","rule_title":"DoD information system access does not require the use of a password.","fix_text":"Configure all DoD information systems to require passwords to gain access.\n\nThe password required flag can be set by entering the following on a command line: \u201cNet user <account_name> /passwordreq:yes\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Using the DUMPSEC utility:\n\nSelect \u201cDump Users as Table\u201d from the \u201cReport\u201d menu.\nSelect the available fields in the following sequence, and click on the \u201cAdd\u201d button for each entry:\nUserName\nSID\nPswdRequired\nPswdExpires\nLastLogonTime\nAcctDisabled\nGroups\n\nIf any accounts listed in the user report have a \u201cNo\u201d in the \u201cPswdRequired\u201d column, then this is a finding.\n\nNote:  Some built-in or application-generated accounts (e.g., Guest, IWAM_, IUSR, etc.) will not have this flag set, even though there are passwords present.  It can be set by entering the following on a command line: \u201cNet user <account_name> /passwordreq:yes\u201d.\n \n \nSeverity Override: For a DISABLED account(s) with a blank or null password, classify/downgrade this finding to a Category 2 finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The lack of password protection enables anyone to gain access to the information system, which opens a backdoor opportunity for intruders to compromise the system as well as other resources within the same administrative domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000764"],"reference_identifier":"7580","uuid":"0c989cdd-3112-468d-a84d-9465edb443d4","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8E37190869378A0718D6F8BDA0C90FE2C4080BD7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'DoD information system access does not require the use of a password.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-11806","group_tree":[{"id":"V-11806","title":"Display of Last User Name","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-11806","severity":"low","group_title":"Display of Last User Name","rule_id_src":"SV-25044r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25044","rule_version":"3.119","rule_title":"The system is configured to allow the display of the last user name on the logon screen.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cInteractive logon: Do not display last user name\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cInteractive logon: Do not display last user name\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  DontDisplayLastUserName\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The user name of the last user to log onto a system will not be displayed.  This eliminates half of the userid/password equation that an unauthorized person would need to log on.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2219","uuid":"a06acdb8-8057-4cb4-983e-e2a1f1cc1fee","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 258D43BE2C1AE4D9D6BDE96F03881FDF021408D3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system is configured to allow the display of the last user name on the logon screen.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14224","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14224","title":"Backup Administrator Account","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14224","severity":"medium","group_title":"Backup Administrator Account","rule_id_src":"SV-24998r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-24998","rule_version":"3.121","rule_title":"The site must have a contingency for emergency administration of the system.","fix_text":"Create a contingency plan for administering a system.  Document any emergency administrator account with the ISSO and store the account information in a secure location.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if there is a contingency for administering a non-domain system with limited administrators.  An emergency administrator account must be documented with the ISSO, and it must be stored with its password in a secure location.  \n\nIf there is no contingency for administering a system in an emergency, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in administrator account, as a well known account subject to attack, is disabled by default and per STIG requirements.  Domain administrative accounts on domain-joined systems should provide sufficient availability for administering a system.  A site with limited administrators must ensure they have a contingency for administering a non-domain system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5989","uuid":"2b6d17d8-4001-4aad-a960-aa74d7051472","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FA8D2DB2392BD37B0C6AD64796E483FCB6B93AC5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The site must have a contingency for emergency administration of the system.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14225","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14225","title":"Administrator Account Password Changes","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14225","severity":"medium","group_title":"Administrator Account Password Changes","rule_id_src":"SV-24999r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-24999","rule_version":"3.122","rule_title":"Administrator passwords must be changed as required.","fix_text":"Define and enforce a policy that requires passwords for the built-in administrator account and any emergency administrator accounts to be changed at least annually or when any member of the administrative team leaves the organization.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if the site has a policy that requires passwords for the built-in administrator account and any emergency administrator accounts to be changed at least annually or when any member of the administrative team leaves the organization.  If a policy does not exist or is not enforced, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The longer a password is in use, the greater the opportunity for someone to gain unauthorized knowledge of the passwords. Passwords for the built-in administrator account and any emergency administrator accounts must be changed at least annually or when any member of the administrative team leaves the organization.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2973","uuid":"31c4962f-5fff-461d-98ed-6c0570446c0b","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7DC8BAB826DE885816D147143225DCE2D103158C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Administrator passwords must be changed as required.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14228","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14228","title":"Audit Access of Global System Objects","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14228","severity":"medium","group_title":"Audit Access of Global System Objects","rule_id_src":"SV-25027r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25027","rule_version":"3.123","rule_title":"Auditing Access of Global System Objects must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Audit: Audit the access of global system objects\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options. \n\nIf the value for \"Audit: Audit the access of global system objects\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\n\nValue Name: AuditBaseObjects\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting prevents the system from setting up a default system access control list for certain system objects, which could create a very large number of security events, filling the security log in Windows and making it difficult to identify actual issues.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCE-9150-4","CCI-001095"],"reference_identifier":"6157","uuid":"ad5ec654-478e-4912-a038-3aaf111a66cd","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 64FC4A6426E6A7D59FABFA9F52117087CE015A6D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Auditing Access of Global System Objects must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14229","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14229","title":"Audit Backup and Restore Privileges","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14229","severity":"medium","group_title":"Audit Backup and Restore Privileges","rule_id_src":"SV-25028r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25028","rule_version":"3.124","rule_title":"Audit of backup and restore privileges is not turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cAudit: Audit the use of Backup and Restore privilege\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.  \n\nIf the value for \u201cAudit: Audit the use of Backup and Restore privilege\u201d is not set to \u201cDisabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\n\nValue Name:  FullPrivilegeAuditing\n\nValue Type:  REG_Binary\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting stops the system from generating audit events for every file backed up or restored which could fill the security log in Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001095"],"reference_identifier":"7741","uuid":"fa22421a-7dd3-485a-a55c-751e6cb04585","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7E24F2861F8ED5F8510538EDDBC0FEC87D0DC1FB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Audit of backup and restore privileges is not turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14230","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14230","title":"Audit Policy Subcategory Setting","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14230","severity":"medium","group_title":"Audit Policy Subcategory Setting","rule_id_src":"SV-25029r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25029","rule_version":"3.125","rule_title":"Audit policy using subcategories is enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cAudit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.  \n\nIf the value for \u201cAudit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name:  SCENoApplyLegacyAuditPolicy\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows administrators to enable the more precise auditing capabilities present in Windows Vista and later.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"3070","uuid":"4dad8dcf-b782-48e2-9a1b-09dc0de7a2a2","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3673EF8E934910E3AD60ECBAB664646D7205B479\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Audit policy using subcategories is enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14231","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14231","title":"Hide Computer","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14231","severity":"low","group_title":"Hide Computer","rule_id_src":"SV-25067r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-25067","rule_version":"3.126","rule_title":"The system must be configured to hide the computer from the browse list.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"MSS: (Hidden) Hide Computer From the Browse List (not recommended except for highly secure environments)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"MSS: (Hidden) Hide Computer From the Browse List (not recommended except for highly secure environments)\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Lanmanserver\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  Hidden\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Identifying the computer name on a network could provide an attacker with information useful in gaining access.  This setting prevents the computer name from displaying in the browse list.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5506","uuid":"e850c058-4dfe-4358-af0f-d06f2c2298ee","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F63379EC73FF76A04F6B54D2A6BCDA62299694E2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to hide the computer from the browse list.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14232","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14232","title":"IPSec Exemptions","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14232","severity":"low","group_title":"IPSec Exemptions","rule_id_src":"SV-25069r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25069","rule_version":"3.127","rule_title":"IPSec exemptions are limited.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cMSS: (NoDefaultExempt) Configure IPSec exemptions for various types of network traffic\u201d to \u201cMulticast, broadcast and ISAKMP exempt (best for Windows XP)\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  Expand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \n\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.  \n\nIf the value for \u201cMSS: (NoDefaultExempt) Configure IPSec exemptions for various types of network traffic\u201d is not set to \u201cMulticast, broadcast and ISAKMP exempt (best for Windows XP)\u201d, then this is a finding. \n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\IPSEC\\\n\nValue Name:  NoDefaultExempt\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that Windows is configured to limit IPSec exemptions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1735","uuid":"39c45ee4-c260-4f84-b682-f53eaae7a8b3","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A04EFB469213AEB008C668301796238F4FA2C48D\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'IPSec exemptions are limited.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14234","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14234","title":"UAC - Admin Approval Mode","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14234","severity":"medium","group_title":"UAC - Admin Approval Mode","rule_id_src":"SV-25116r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25116","rule_version":"3.129","rule_title":"User Account Control for the built In admin runs in Admin Approval Mode","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cUser Account Control: Admin Approval Mode for the Built-in Administrator account\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options. \n\nIf the value for \u201cUser Account Control: Admin Approval Mode for the Built-in Administrator account\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  FilterAdministratorToken\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies whether the built-in Administrator account runs in Admin Approval Mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"1802","uuid":"e4962afe-6458-4c1d-9d17-a07b0e288058","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 51D0A4E45F3F79C65D035E6E575111713B9A8EE1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control for the built In admin runs in Admin Approval Mode' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14235","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14235","title":"UAC - Admin Elevation Prompt","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14235","severity":"medium","group_title":"UAC - Admin Elevation Prompt","rule_id_src":"SV-25117r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25117","rule_version":"3.130","rule_title":"User Account Control is configured for the appropriate elevation prompt for administrators","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cUser Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for administrators in Admin Approval Mode\u201d to \u201cPrompt for consent on the secure desktop\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cUser Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for administrators in Admin Approval Mode\u201d is not set to \u201cPrompt for consent on the secure desktop\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  ConsentPromptBehaviorAdmin\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  2 (Prompt for consent on the secure desktop)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting configures the elevation requirements for logged on administrators to complete a task that requires raised privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"3381","uuid":"deb07718-8be6-4a07-83ea-3c253be7e2f0","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E0CE121788922EAF66C61D3844AC46AE6FE3D2AA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control is configured for the appropriate elevation prompt for administrators' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14236","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14236","title":"UAC - User Elevation Prompt","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14236","severity":"medium","group_title":"UAC - User Elevation Prompt","rule_id_src":"SV-25118r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25118","rule_version":"3.131","rule_title":"User Account Control must automatically deny elevation requests for standard users.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for standard users\" to \"Automatically deny elevation requests\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for standard users\" is not set to \"Automatically deny elevation requests\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorUser\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. Denying elevation requests from standard user accounts requires tasks that need elevation to be initiated by accounts with administrative privileges.  This prevents privileged account credentials from being cached with standard user profile information to help mitigate credential theft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"5389","uuid":"ea18cdea-e30e-46bc-8325-9aad0375adad","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-14237","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14237","title":"UAC - Application Installations","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14237","severity":"medium","group_title":"UAC - Application Installations","rule_id_src":"SV-25119r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25119","rule_version":"3.132","rule_title":"User Account Control is configured to detect application installations.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cUser Account Control: Detect application installations and prompt for elevation\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.  \n\nIf the value for \u201cUser Account Control: Detect application installations and prompt for elevation\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableInstallerDetection\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This requires Windows to respond to application installation requests by prompting for credentials.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"4262","uuid":"61255872-2209-4764-8560-3f2df90a72fd","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-14239","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14239","title":"UAC - UIAccess Application Elevation","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14239","severity":"medium","group_title":"UAC - UIAccess Application Elevation","rule_id_src":"SV-25121r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25121","rule_version":"3.134","rule_title":"User Account Control - Elevate UIAccess applications that are in secure locations.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cUser Account Control: Only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options. \n\nIf the value for \u201cUser Account Control: Only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableSecureUIAPaths\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies whether Windows only allows applications installed in a secure location, such as the Program Files or the Windows\\System32 folders, on the file system to run with elevated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"9895","uuid":"5db94ce2-8329-451c-a314-64fbf5ebbbec","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0B1B3433F71C449423A6C938BBE4B134C08B97A9\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control - Elevate UIAccess applications that are in secure locations.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14240","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14240","title":"UAC - All Admin Approval Mode","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14240","severity":"medium","group_title":"UAC - All Admin Approval Mode","rule_id_src":"SV-25122r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25122","rule_version":"3.137","rule_title":"User Account Control - Run all admins in Admin Approval Mode.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cUser Account Control: Run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options. \n\nIf the value for \u201cUser Account Control: Run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableLUA\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that UAC has not been disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"7606","uuid":"5a8f0542-fcc6-4b81-a4d3-47a8b5c03ece","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8EDA2B693125B3C1F9C6FC5DFF35B62686864C2E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control - Run all admins in Admin Approval Mode.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14241","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14241","title":"UAC - Secure Desktop Mode","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14241","severity":"medium","group_title":"UAC - Secure Desktop Mode","rule_id_src":"SV-25123r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25123","rule_version":"3.135","rule_title":"User Account Control - Switch to secure desktop.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cUser Account Control: Switch to the secure desktop when prompting for elevation\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options. \n\nIf the value for \u201cUser Account Control: Switch to the secure desktop when prompting for elevation\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  PromptOnSecureDesktop\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that the elevation prompt is only used in secure desktop mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"5361","uuid":"4732e3a9-6c16-4e51-8893-2d28c74dadba","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 344641A1F51B6D37F315EA74BF413F4C18393B1E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'User Account Control - Switch to secure desktop.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14242","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14242","title":"UAC - Non UAC Compliant Application Virtualization","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14242","severity":"medium","group_title":"UAC - Non UAC Compliant Application Virtualization","rule_id_src":"SV-25124r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25124","rule_version":"3.136","rule_title":"User Account Control - Non UAC compliant applications run in virtualized file and registry entries.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cUser Account Control: Virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options. \n\nIf the value for \u201cUser Account Control: Virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableVirtualization\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that non UAC compliant applications will run in virtualized file and registry entries in per user locations allowing them to run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"8453","uuid":"04b9495e-89ea-4d80-b62a-86e715d460b5","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 597C468EDE3DB8E5B067D0F6141C757E4E5497A6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control - Non UAC compliant applications run in virtualized file and registry entries.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14243","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14243","title":"Enumerate Administrator Accounts on Elevation","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14243","severity":"medium","group_title":"Enumerate Administrator Accounts on Elevation","rule_id_src":"SV-25176r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25176","rule_version":"5.132","rule_title":"Require username and password to elevate a running application.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Credential User Interface \u201cEnumerate administrator accounts on elevation\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\CredUI\n\nValue Name:  EnumerateAdministrators\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that the system is configured to always require users to type in a user name and password to elevate a running application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"9835","uuid":"9bfd1dd4-45f3-4597-8bfd-8ece8d35692a","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C8498B74B6EFF470352BC3076D2FF25A82F6F5FF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Require username and password to elevate a running application.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14247","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14247","title":"TS/RDS - Prevent Password Saving","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14247","severity":"medium","group_title":"TS/RDS - Prevent Password Saving","rule_id_src":"SV-25258r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25258","rule_version":"5.116","rule_title":"Terminal Services / Remote Desktop Service - Prevent password saving in the Remote Desktop Client.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Connection Client \u201cDo not allow passwords to be saved\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:   HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:   \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name:   DisablePasswordSaving\n\nType:   REG_DWORD\nValue:   1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that the system is configured to prevent users from saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"6182","uuid":"8599585a-dca7-4c64-887b-ac78f5f0dca9","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-14248","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14248","title":"TS/RDS - Remote User Connections","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14248","severity":"medium","group_title":"TS/RDS - Remote User Connections","rule_id_src":"SV-25259r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25259","rule_version":"5.117","rule_title":"Users must be prevented from connecting using Remote Desktop Services.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Connections \"Allow users to connect remotely using Remote Desktop Services\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nIf Remote Desktop Services for remote administration is necessary, enabling this would not be a finding. Restricted Admin mode must be used.  This must be document with the ISSO.\nSee Microsoft article KB2871997 for patches required to add this function to systems prior to Windows 8.1.\n\nRestricted Admin mode for Remote Desktop Connections can be implemented for each session using a command line switch to start the Remote Desktop Client or through a group policy to enable it for all sessions.\n\nThe command line to do this is \"mstsc /restrictedadmin\".\n\nTo enable this with group policy, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Credentials Delegation >> \"Restrict delegation of credentials to remote servers\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name:  fDenyTSConnections\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1\n\nIf Remote Desktop Services for remote administration is necessary, enabling this would not be a finding. Restricted Admin mode must be used.  This must be document with the ISSO.\nSee Microsoft article KB2871997 for patches required to add this function to systems prior to Windows 8.1.\n\nRestricted Admin mode for Remote Desktop Connections can be implemented for each session using a command line switch to start the Remote Desktop Client or through a group policy to enable it for all sessions.\n\nThe command line to do this is \"mstsc /restrictedadmin\".\n\nTo enable this with group policy, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Credentials Delegation >> \"Restrict delegation of credentials to remote servers\" to \"Enabled\".","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing a remote desktop session to a workstation enables another avenue of access that could be exploited.  The system must be configured to prevent users from connecting to a computer using Remote Desktop Services.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002314"],"reference_identifier":"7599","uuid":"5f0644df-a366-485e-96a3-97f0fe7237be","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 53434889169B21A6D7835C4BD4A4E3EF0AB254C1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Users must be prevented from connecting using Remote Desktop Services.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14249","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14249","title":"TS/RDS - Drive Redirection","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14249","severity":"medium","group_title":"TS/RDS - Drive Redirection","rule_id_src":"SV-25260r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25260","rule_version":"5.118","rule_title":"Terminal Services / Remote Desktop Services - Local drives prevented from sharing with Terminal Servers/Remote Session Hosts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Device and Resource Redirection \u201cDo not allow drive redirection\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name:  fDisableCdm\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that the system is configured to prevent users from sharing the local drives on their client computers to Remote Session Hosts that they access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"7676","uuid":"751d2a2f-2bac-4aa9-91f6-bd547d586ff8","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 99BC0517CE04B9D5A8D70EF08B62E2CF2FB433B1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Terminal Services / Remote Desktop Services - Local drives prevented from sharing with Terminal Servers/Remote Session Hosts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14253","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14253","title":"RPC - Unauthenticated RPC Clients","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14253","severity":"medium","group_title":"RPC - Unauthenticated RPC Clients","rule_id_src":"SV-25172r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25172","rule_version":"5.123","rule_title":"Restrict unauthenticated RPC clients.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Remote Procedure Call \u201cRestrictions for Unauthenticated RPC clients\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d and \u201cAuthenticated\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Rpc\\\n\nValue Name:  RestrictRemoteClients\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that the system is configured to restrict unauthenticated RPC clients from connecting to the RPC server.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001967"],"reference_identifier":"5836","uuid":"33f32a70-227f-4631-bd01-b258bf18721d","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E7A5B83AAF0D7E2299290E48745BF9AD63846FB0\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Restrict unauthenticated RPC clients.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14256","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14256","title":"Internet Download / Online Ordering","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14256","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Download / Online Ordering","rule_id_src":"SV-25155r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25155","rule_version":"5.126","rule_title":"Web publishing and online ordering wizards prevented from downloading list of providers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication setting \u2018Turn off Internet download for Web publishing and online ordering wizards\u2019 to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\n\nValue Name:  NoWebServices\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that the system is configured to prevent Windows from downloading a list of providers for the Web publishing and online ordering wizards.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9433","uuid":"9639a07e-bb24-4903-8e7f-1eeb92d499e9","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BADBC99CF5B46072764AF2007CFF593EA45D3D1F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Web publishing and online ordering wizards prevented from downloading list of providers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14259","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14259","title":"Printing Over HTTP","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14259","severity":"medium","group_title":"Printing Over HTTP","rule_id_src":"SV-25157r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25157","rule_version":"5.129","rule_title":"Prevent printing over HTTP.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication setting \u2018Turn off printing over HTTP\u2019 to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\n\nValue Name:  DisableHTTPPrinting\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that the system is configured to prevent the client computer\u2019s ability to print over HTTP, which allows the computer to print to printers on the intranet as well as the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3065","uuid":"1b49b078-2d0e-4220-a59d-b99abb783588","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DFE3BEE9384CF1ABBF307AD2714A3166836430AF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Prevent printing over HTTP.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14260","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14260","title":"HTTP Printer Drivers","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14260","severity":"medium","group_title":"HTTP Printer Drivers","rule_id_src":"SV-25151r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25151","rule_version":"5.130","rule_title":"Computer prevented from downloading print driver packages over HTTP.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication setting \u2018Turn off downloading of print drivers over HTTP\u2019 to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\n\nValue Name:  DisableWebPnPDownload\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that the system is configured to prevent the computer from downloading print driver packages over HTTP.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4199","uuid":"2f44563a-a589-4cd1-86d1-7f596680450d","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 54ABD1CB1C7438575588DE2544E01CEED7CC4FC6\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Computer prevented from downloading print driver packages over HTTP.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14261","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14261","title":"Windows Update Device Drive Searching","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14261","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows Update Device Drive Searching","rule_id_src":"SV-25165r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25165","rule_version":"5.131","rule_title":"Windows is prevented from using Windows Update to search for drivers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication setting \u2018Turn off Windows Update device driver searching\u2019 to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DriverSearching\n\nValue Name:  DontSearchWindowsUpdate\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that the system is configured to prevent Windows from searching Windows Update for device drivers when no local drivers for a device are present.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"2096","uuid":"0fd9ef54-2bfd-4250-b8d0-7dde32a3beac","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Wind