be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C8EE4D503422B306A23A715B1A802C0FD855CD2D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Preserve zone information when saving attachments.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14269","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14269","title":"Attachment Mgr - Hide Mech to Remove Zone Info","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14269","severity":"medium","group_title":"Attachment Mgr - Hide Mech to Remove Zone Info","rule_id_src":"SV-25206r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25206","rule_version":"5.135","rule_title":"Hide mechanism for removing zone information from file attachments.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Attachment Manager -> \u201cHide mechanisms to remove zone information\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_Current_User\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name:  HideZoneInfoOnProperties\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that users cannot manually remove zone information from saved file attachments.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2844","uuid":"b22e940f-5991-4a82-a4e0-21ace4faebf2","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9968CAEC907395A5F9F2AAF56DA12E1D49BE280C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Hide mechanism for removing zone information from file attachments.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14270","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14270","title":"Attachment Mgr - Scan with Antivirus","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14270","severity":"medium","group_title":"Attachment Mgr - Scan with Antivirus","rule_id_src":"SV-25207r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25207","rule_version":"5.136","rule_title":"Notify antivirus when file attachments are opened.","fix_text":"Configure policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Attachment Manager -> \u201cNotify antivirus programs when opening attachments\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_Current_User\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name:  ScanWithAntiVirus\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  3","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that antivirus programs are notified when a user opens a file attachment.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9676","uuid":"406998c5-2ff8-4d9d-85f9-05869420128e","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8A346F084BD3D699501AC1AEC5914136782FA9BC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Notify antivirus when file attachments are opened.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-14271","group_tree":[{"id":"V-14271","title":"Application Account Passwords","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-14271","severity":"medium","group_title":"Application Account Passwords","rule_id_src":"SV-25212r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25212","rule_version":"4.018","rule_title":"Application account passwords must meet DoD requirements for length, complexity and changes.","fix_text":"Create application/service account passwords that are at least 15 characters in length and meet complexity requirements.  Change application/service account passwords that are manually generated and entered by a system administrator at least annually or whenever an administrator with knowledge of the password leaves the organization.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The site should have a local policy to ensure that passwords for application/service accounts are at least 15 characters in length and meet complexity requirements for all passwords.  Application/service account passwords manually generated and entered by a system administrator must be changed at least annually or whenever a system administrator that has knowledge of the password leaves the organization.\n\nInterview the system administrators on their policy for application/service accounts.  If it does not meet the above requirements, this is a finding.\n\nUsing the DUMPSEC utility:\n\nSelect \"Dump Users as Table\" from the \"Report\" menu.\nSelect the available fields in the following sequence, and click on the \"Add\" button for each entry:\n\nUserName\nSID\nPswdRequired\nPswdExpires\nPswdLastSetTime\nLastLogonTime\nAcctDisabled\nGroups\n\nIf any application accounts listed in the Dumpsec user report have a date older than one year in the \"PwsdLastSetTime\" column, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Setting application accounts to expire may cause applications to stop functioning.  The site will have a policy that application account passwords are changed at least annually or when a system administrator with knowledge of the password leaves the organization.  Application/service account passwords will be at least 15 characters and follow complexity requirements for all passwords.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000205","CCI-002142"],"reference_identifier":"4765","uuid":"ce277e16-3333-4acd-a2e8-188cbc8f0976","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 93B3C13A17F53D2045E0C364BFF68AC1B683D078\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Application account passwords must meet DoD requirements for length, complexity and changes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-15505","group_tree":[{"id":"V-15505","title":"HBSS McAfee Agent","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15505","severity":"medium","group_title":"HBSS McAfee Agent","rule_id_src":"SV-25255r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-25255","rule_version":"5.140","rule_title":"The HBSS McAfee Agent must be installed.","fix_text":"Deploy the McAfee Agent as detailed in accordance with the DoD HBSS STIG.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run \"Services.msc\".\n\nVerify the McAfee Agent service is running, depending on the version installed.\n\nVersion - Service Name\nMcAfee Agent v5.x - McAfee Agent Service\nMcAfee Agent v4.x - McAfee Framework Service\n\nIf the service is not listed or does not have a Status of \"Started\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The McAfee Agent is the client side distributed component of McAfee ePolicy Orchestrator (McAfee ePO) which provides a secure communication channel between the ePO server and managed point products.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4267","uuid":"88d9af23-b383-45e5-93bf-1bb38f57e201","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2F0CE9767968D8F6B0722F6C55FCFD985CB62303\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The HBSS McAfee Agent must be installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-15666","group_tree":[{"id":"V-15666","title":"Windows Peer to Peer Networking","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15666","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows Peer to Peer Networking","rule_id_src":"SV-25140r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25140","rule_version":"5.202","rule_title":"Turn off Windows Peer-to-Peer Networking Services.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> Microsoft Peer-to-Peer Networking Services \u201cTurn Off Microsoft Peer-to-Peer Networking Services\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Peernet\\\n\nValue Name:  Disabled\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies Microsoft Peer-to-Peer Networking Service is turned off.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6795","uuid":"ad83b137-d057-4564-82dc-9c0ee8dd9105","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F0965CC8541C716C9E21CCAAC1B5F9BC2C3CC740\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Turn off Windows Peer-to-Peer Networking Services.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-15667","group_tree":[{"id":"V-15667","title":"Prohibit Network Bridge","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15667","severity":"medium","group_title":"Prohibit Network Bridge","rule_id_src":"SV-25141r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25141","rule_version":"5.203","rule_title":"Prohibit Network Bridge in Windows.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> Network Connections \u201cProhibit installation and configuration of Network Bridge on your DNS domain network\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Network Connections\\\n\nValue Name:  NC_AllowNetBridge_NLA\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies the Network Bridge cannot be installed and configured.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6719","uuid":"36bd7fd5-8f9c-498e-9bc2-3ea3c751954b","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B34350A937CA5722ED541FA9B5B233EBC52A37DB\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Prohibit Network Bridge in Windows.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-15672","group_tree":[{"id":"V-15672","title":"Event Viewer Events.asp Links","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15672","severity":"low","group_title":"Event Viewer Events.asp Links","rule_id_src":"SV-25152r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25152","rule_version":"5.214","rule_title":"Event Viewer events.asp links are available.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication settings \u201cTurn off Event Viewer \u201cEvents.asp\u201d links\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, then this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\EventViewer\\\n\nValue Name:  MicrosoftEventVwrDisableLinks\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Ben