n":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15712","severity":"low","group_title":"Search \u2013 Exchange Folder Indexing","rule_id_src":"SV-25185r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25185","rule_version":"5.233","rule_title":"Indexing of mail items in Exchange folders when Outlook is running in uncached mode must be turned off.","fix_text":"If Outlook is not installed on the system, this is NA.\nIf Outlook is installed on the system, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Search -> \"Enable indexing uncached Exchange folders\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If Outlook is not installed on the system, this is NA.\nIf Outlook is installed on the system and the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Windows Search\\\n\nValue Name:  PreventIndexingUncachedExchangeFolders\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Indexing of encrypted items may expose sensitive data.  This setting prevents mail items in a Microsoft Exchange folder from being indexed when Outlook is running in uncached mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2097","uuid":"664054f2-4256-4493-b8bd-6743198f48e6","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CE38A19F60CBE8B473551DC056185DB5E8547DEB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Indexing of mail items in Exchange folders when Outlook is running in uncached mode must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-15713","group_tree":[{"id":"V-15713","title":"Defender \u2013 SpyNet Reporting","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15713","severity":"medium","group_title":"Defender \u2013 SpyNet Reporting","rule_id_src":"SV-25186r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25186","rule_version":"5.234","rule_title":"Turn off Windows Defender SpyNet reporting.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Defender \u201cConfigure Microsoft Spynet Reporting\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value exists and is set to \u201c1\u201d (Basic) or \u201c2\u201d (Advanced), this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\\\n\nValue Name:  SpyNetReporting\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1 or 2 = a Finding","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that SpyNet membership is disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4572","uuid":"e260b3de-b394-4e41-b268-6d115f3e3faa","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ED4DCA6361C20A6A4DFA3B5452523EECAA22B121\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Turn off Windows Defender SpyNet reporting.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-15718","group_tree":[{"id":"V-15718","title":"Windows Explorer \u2013 Heap Termination","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15718","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows Explorer \u2013 Heap Termination","rule_id_src":"SV-25191r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25191","rule_version":"5.239","rule_title":"Disable heap termination on corruption in Windows Explorer.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Explorer \u201cTurn off heap termination on corruption\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name:  NoHeapTerminationOnCorruption\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that heap termination on corruption is disabled.  This may prevent Windows Explorer from terminating immediately from certain legacy plug-in applications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"3171","uuid":"becceaf8-8324-405a-8268-b8dd6e4480d1","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 90793CB17A33B9800F1848933E3F5D0F1FF53DC0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Disable heap termination on corruption in Windows Explorer.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-15722","group_tree":[{"id":"V-15722","title":"Media DRM \u2013 Internet Access","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15722","severity":"medium","group_title":"Media DRM \u2013 Internet Access","rule_id_src":"SV-25197r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25197","rule_version":"5.247","rule_title":"Prevent Windows Media Digital Rights Management (DRM) from accessing the Internet.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Media Digital Rights Management \u201cPrevent Windows Media DRM Internet Access\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WMDRM\\\n\nValue Name:  DisableOnline\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that Windows Media DRM will be prevented from accessing the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6966","uuid":"8aed2613-f7bd-42e8-a303-8d8e92add5c5","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8F44D2D1C7785DC9AAD85CD375EEA1C24C800B1D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Prevent Windows Media Digital Rights Management (DRM) from accessing the Internet.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-15724","group_tree":[{"id":"V-15724","title":"Gadgets \u2013 Unsigned Gadgets","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15724","severity":"medium","group_title":"Gadgets \u2013 Unsigned Gadgets","rule_id_src":"SV-25267r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25267","rule_version":"5.250","rule_title":"Unsigned gadgets must not be installed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Desktop Gadgets ->  \"Restrict unpacking and installation of gadgets that are not digitally signed\" to \"Enabled\".   \n\nTo turn off Desktop Gadgets completely, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Desktop Gadgets -> \"Turn off desktop gadgets\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If Desktop Gadgets have been disabled, this is NA.\nVerify the following registry value to determine if Desktop Gadgets have been disabled:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Windows\\Sidebar\\\n\nValue Name:  TurnOffSidebar\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1\n\nIf Desktop Gadgets have not been disabled and the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Windows\\Sidebar\\\n\nValue Name:  TurnOffUnsignedGadgets\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled installation of applications can introduce various issues, including system instability, and allow access to sensitive information.  Installation of applications must be controlled by the enterprise.  This setting prevents unsigned gadgets from being installed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"3526","uuid":"afa2b338-0b55-41f3-9923-ca589c0cb02a","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CAFFD1994BB196557B5AACD52852960DE4848466\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unsigned gadgets must not be installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-15725","group_tree":[{"id":"V-15725","title":"Gadgets \u2013 More Gadgets Link","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15725","severity":"medium","group_title":"Gadgets \u2013 More Gadgets Link","rule_id_src":"SV-25268r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25268","rule_version":"5.251","rule_title":"The More Gadgets link must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Desktop Gadgets -> \"Override the More Gadgets Link\" to \"Enabled\" with \"about:blank\" entered in the \"Override Gadget Location\".\n\nTo turn off Desktop Gadgets completely, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Desktop Gadgets -> \"Turn off desktop gadgets\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If Desktop Gadgets have been disabled, this is NA.\nVerify the following registry value to determine if Desktop Gadgets have been disabled:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Windows\\Sidebar\\\n\nValue Name:  TurnOffSidebar\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1\n\nIf Desktop Gadgets have not been disabled and the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Windows\\Sidebar\\\n\nValue Name:  OverrideMoreGadgetsLink\n\nType:  REG_SZ\nValue:  about:blank","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled installation of applications can introduce various issues, including system instability, and allow access to sensitive information.  Installation of applications must be controlled by the enterprise.  This setting prevents access to gadgets through the More Gadgets link.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"7061","uuid":"48372dc4-86c1-493a-9a15-7255dba4f5dc","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-15726","group_tree":[{"id":"V-15726","title":"Gadgets \u2013 User Installed Gadgets","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15726","severity":"medium","group_title":"Gadgets \u2013 User Installed Gadgets","rule_id_src":"SV-25269r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25269","rule_version":"5.252","rule_title":"User-installed gadgets must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Desktop Gadgets - > \"Turn Off user-installed desktop gadgets\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nTo turn off Desktop Gadgets completely, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Desktop Gadgets -> \"Turn off desktop gadgets\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If Desktop Gadgets have been disabled, this is NA.\nVerify the following registry value to determine if Desktop Gadgets have been disabled:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Windows\\Sidebar\\\n\nValue Name:  TurnOffSidebar\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1\n\nIf Desktop Gadgets have not been disabled and the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Windows\\Sidebar\\\n\nValue Name:  TurnOffUserInstalledGadgets\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled installation of applications can introduce various issues, including system instability, and allow access to sensitive information.  Installation of applications must be controlled by the enterprise.  This setting prevents user-installed gadgets from running.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"2073","uuid":"4bcb5050-cf4a-43b3-945a-f26aaa7716cf","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5E78F2AC6E7AB3C0118DF3A8C74AEE9139622D63\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User-installed gadgets must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-15727","group_tree":[{"id":"V-15727","title":"User Network Sharing","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15727","severity":"medium","group_title":"User Network Sharing","rule_id_src":"SV-25208r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25208","rule_version":"5.253","rule_title":"Prevent users from sharing files from within their profiles.","fix_text":"Note:  This setting is under USER Configuration not COMPUTER Configuration \n\nConfigure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Network Sharing \u201cPrevent users from sharing files within their profile\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note:  This setting is in HKEY_CURRENT_USER, not HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\n\nIf the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name:  NoInPlaceSharing\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that users are prevented from sharing files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6782","uuid":"cffa74f0-9a88-4674-99ec-4060aa533829","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CAA174F661C3030E1A896ADCD3921B79A85353F0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Prevent users from sharing files from within their profiles.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-15823","group_tree":[{"id":"V-15823","title":"Software Certificate Installation Files","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-15823","severity":"medium","group_title":"Software Certificate Installation Files","rule_id_src":"SV-25004r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25004","rule_version":"2.021","rule_title":"Software certificate installation files must be removed from a system.","fix_text":"Remove any certificate installation files found on a system.\n\nThis does not apply to server-based applications that have a requirement for .p12 certificate files (e.g., Oracle Wallet Manager).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Search all drives for *.p12 and *.pfx files.\n\nIf any files with these extensions exist, then this is a finding.\n\nThis does not apply to server-based applications that have a requirement for .p12 certificate files (e.g., Oracle Wallet Manager).  Some applications create files with extensions of .p12 that are NOT certificate installation files.  Removal from systems of non-certificate installation files are not required.  These should be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Use of software certificates and their accompanying installation files for end users to access resources is less secure than the use of hardware-based certificates.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9376","uuid":"a7182cff-acae-4ff3-aebe-70afc6f4efbb","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-16006","group_tree":[{"id":"V-16006","title":"Unnecessary Features Installed","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-16006","severity":"medium","group_title":"Unnecessary Features Installed","rule_id_src":"SV-25252r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25252","rule_version":"5.260","rule_title":"The system must not have unnecessary features installed.","fix_text":"Uninstall any prohibited features listed in the manual check.\n\nOpen Control Panel.\nSelect \u201cPrograms and Features\u201d.\nSelect \u201cTurn Windows features on or off\u201d.\n\nFeatures currently prohibited:  \nGames\nWindows Media Center (under Media Features)\nSimpleTCP Services\nTelnet (Client or Server)\nTFTP Client","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Perform the following to verify installed Features:\n\nOpen Control Panel.\nSelect \"Programs and Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\n\nFeatures currently prohibited:\nGames\nWindows Media Center (under Media Features)\nSimpleTCP Services\nTelnet (Client or Server)\nTFTP Client\n\nIf any of the listed features is selected, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows includes additional features available for installation.  The majority of these are unnecessary and may also increase the attack surface of the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6686","uuid":"ed8b521f-89a8-41db-ba8f-e542c0e73db0","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DCBCBDDB23823DB5DD48E51466C59F757539A900\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must not have unnecessary features installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-16008","group_tree":[{"id":"V-16008","title":"UAC - Application Elevations","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-16008","severity":"medium","group_title":"UAC - Application Elevations","rule_id_src":"SV-25120r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25120","rule_version":"3.140","rule_title":"UAC - All application are elevated.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cUser Account Control: Only elevate executables that are signed and validated\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options. \n\nIf the value for \u201cUser Account Control: Only elevate executables that are signed and validated\u201d is not set to \u201cDisabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  ValidateAdminCodeSignatures\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that Windows elevates all applications, not just signed ones.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"6013","uuid":"9e0027f3-2efe-4b6f-a053-6c680c989c89","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EEBEDBFB0E79BA973D83F45D1416C409B55597B2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'UAC - All application are elevated.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-16020","group_tree":[{"id":"V-16020","title":"Windows Customer Experience Improvement Program","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-16020","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows Customer Experience Improvement Program","rule_id_src":"SV-25163r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25163","rule_version":"5.254","rule_title":"Windows Customer Experience Improvement Program is disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication Settings -> \u201cTurn off Windows Customer Experience Improvement Program\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_Local_Machine\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\SQMClient\\Windows\n\nValue Name:  CEIPEnable\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that the Windows Customer Experience Improvement Program is disabled so information is not passed to the vendor.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3505","uuid":"21a090c4-dca7-4fa0-ad17-51e5771e8a16","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 85D0E4D74ACC7C0166BECA7ED372BB5338B88D4D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Customer Experience Improvement Program is disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-16021","group_tree":[{"id":"V-16021","title":"Help Experience Improvement Program","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-16021","severity":"medium","group_title":"Help Experience Improvement Program","rule_id_src":"SV-25202r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25202","rule_version":"5.255","rule_title":"Help Experience Improvement Program is disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication Settings -> \u201cTurn off Help Experience Improvement Program\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_Current_User\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Assistance\\Client\\1.0\n\nValue Name:  NoImplicitFeedback\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that the Windows Help Experience Improvement Program is disabled to prevent information from being passed to the vendor.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8241","uuid":"9a0e9359-6943-4c81-b423-2f24af315c36","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6C958799A9EE96ECF4B3DC68DC95793BB2D0D655\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Help Experience Improvement Program is disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-16047","group_tree":[{"id":"V-16047","title":"Built-in Admin Account Status","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-16047","severity":"medium","group_title":"Built-in Admin Account Status","rule_id_src":"SV-25020r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25020","rule_version":"4.039","rule_title":"The built-in administrator account must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Administrator account status\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Administrator account status\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in administrator account is a well-known account subject to attack.  It also provides no accountability to individual administrators on a system.  It must be disabled to prevent its use.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000764"],"reference_identifier":"9644","uuid":"4fc7c24c-757c-4957-84d1-391ac301f9fe","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-16048","group_tree":[{"id":"V-16048","title":"Help Ratings","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-16048","severity":"medium","group_title":"Help Ratings","rule_id_src":"SV-25203r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25203","rule_version":"5.256","rule_title":"Disable Help Ratings feed back.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication Settings -> \u201cTurn off Help Ratings\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_Current_User\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Assistance\\Client\\1.0\n\nValue Name:  NoExplicitFeedback\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that the users cannot provide ratings feedback to Microsoft for Help content.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3218","uuid":"8c309be0-9882-46db-a79c-58f199ee649b","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-17373","group_tree":[{"id":"V-17373","title":"Secure Removable Media \u2013 CD-ROM","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-17373","severity":"low","group_title":"Secure Removable Media \u2013 CD-ROM","rule_id_src":"SV-25036r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25036","rule_version":"3.004","rule_title":"Secure Removable Media \u2013 CD-ROM","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cDevices: Restrict CD-ROM access to locally logged-on user only\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.  Expand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\n\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\nIf the value for \u201cDevices: Restrict CD-ROM access to locally logged-on user only\u201d is not set to \u201cDisabled\u201d, then this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nSubkey: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name: AllocateCDRoms\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This check verifies that Windows is configured to not limit access to CD drives when a user is logged on locally.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2500","uuid":"ac4d82be-daa9-4d42-8b57-6ebc0685817c","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5D8862DF86D881CE39089F19E70BB5EABC872D13\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Secure Removable Media \u2013 CD-ROM' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-18010","group_tree":[{"id":"V-18010","title":"User Right - Debug Programs","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-18010","severity":"high","group_title":"User Right - Debug Programs","rule_id_src":"SV-25018r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25018","rule_version":"WINUR-000016","rule_title":"Unauthorized accounts must not have the Debug programs user right.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Debug Programs\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \u201cDebug programs\u201d right, this is a finding.\n\nIf Administrators require this right for troubleshooting or application issues, it should be assigned on a \ntemporary basis as needed.\n\nDocumentable Explanation: Some applications may require this right to function. Any exception needs to be documented with the ISSO. Acceptable forms of documentation include vendor published documents and application owner confirmation.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Debug Programs\" user right can attach a debugger to any process or to the kernel, providing complete access to sensitive and critical operating system components.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8420","uuid":"dcf965a9-8060-4e1e-8d32-65eae2ec3fc1","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 26ED78CB2B66C62FE8261F3E4615D23F7A13DE2D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthorized accounts must not have the Debug programs user right.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21950","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21950","title":"SPN Target Name Validation Level","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21950","severity":"medium","group_title":"SPN Target Name Validation Level","rule_id_src":"SV-25273r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25273","rule_version":"3.150","rule_title":"The service principal name (SPN) target name validation level must be configured to Accept if provided by client.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft network server: Server SPN target name validation level\" to \"Accept if provided by client\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Microsoft network server: Server SPN target name validation level\" is not set to \"Accept if provided by client\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  SmbServerNameHardeningLevel\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If a service principle name (SPN) is provided by the client, it is validated against the server's list of SPNs, aiding in the prevention of spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9992","uuid":"d8fc3779-141a-42da-9da8-0230507925eb","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 22FDDF78B405C953BDC576AFAE7C3D7F0BA09003\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The service principal name (SPN) target name validation level must be configured to Accept if provided by client.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21951","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21951","title":"Computer Identity Authentication for NTLM","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21951","severity":"medium","group_title":"Computer Identity Authentication for NTLM","rule_id_src":"SV-25274r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25274","rule_version":"3.151","rule_title":"Services using Local System that use Negotiate when reverting to NTLM authentication must use the computer identity vs. authenticating anonymously.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network Security: Allow Local System to use computer identity for NTLM\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network Security: Allow Local System to use computer identity for NTLM\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\\n\nValue Name:  UseMachineId\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Services using Local System that use Negotiate when reverting to NTLM authentication may gain unauthorized access if allowed to authenticate anonymously instead of using the computer identity.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000778"],"reference_identifier":"8712","uuid":"bc7ad3fc-8e8a-4086-b2af-cd2dcb811036","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 74A346ECAFE50385CC8A4387FE5630D21F1972D9\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Services using Local System that use Negotiate when reverting to NTLM authentication must use the computer identity vs. authenticating anonymously.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21952","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21952","title":"NTLM NULL Session Fallback","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21952","severity":"medium","group_title":"NTLM NULL Session Fallback","rule_id_src":"SV-25275r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25275","rule_version":"3.152","rule_title":"NTLM must be prevented from falling back to a Null session.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network Security: Allow LocalSystem NULL session fallback\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network Security: Allow LocalSystem NULL session fallback\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name:  allownullsessionfallback\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"NTLM sessions that are allowed to fall back to Null (unauthenticated) sessions may gain unauthorized access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6009","uuid":"1bf6c233-c54d-4a3d-bab0-03704d724cc9","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 074FD5D0B9924DB930E18B80812C3626319E469E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'NTLM must be prevented from falling back to a Null session.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21953","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21953","title":"PKU2U Online Identities Authentication","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21953","severity":"medium","group_title":"PKU2U Online Identities Authentication","rule_id_src":"SV-25276r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25276","rule_version":"3.153","rule_title":"PKU2U authentication using online identities must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network Security: Allow PKU2U authentication requests to this computer to use online identities\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network Security: Allow PKU2U authentication requests to this computer to use online identities\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\pku2u\\\n\nValue Name:  AllowOnlineID\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"PKU2U is a peer-to-peer authentication protocol.  This setting prevents online identities from authenticating to domain-joined systems.  Authentication will be centrally managed with Windows user accounts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4682","uuid":"a8bb31b7-ba7d-4083-adec-a1c67b09c135","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C2919EC825098264BD4B8003DB2C672DD63E505C\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'PKU2U authentication using online identities must be prevented.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21954","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21954","title":"Kerberos Encryption Types","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21954","severity":"medium","group_title":"Kerberos Encryption Types","rule_id_src":"SV-25277r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-25277","rule_version":"3.154","rule_title":"The use of DES encryption suites must not be allowed for Kerberos encryption.","fix_text":"Configure the policy for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Configure encryption types allowed for Kerberos\" to \"Enabled\" with only the following selected:\n\nRC4_HMAC_MD5\nAES128_HMAC_SHA1\nAES256_HMAC_SHA1\nFuture encryption types\n\nOptions such as RC4_HMAC_MD5 may also be excluded to align with STIGs for later Windows versions.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Review the value to the following registry key to verify the DES_CBC_CRC and DES_CBC_MD5 encryption suites are not allowed.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Kerberos\\Parameters\\\nValue Name:  SupportedEncryptionTypes\nType:  REG_DWORD\n\nThe values are determined by the selection of encryption suites in the policy \"Network Security: Configure encryption types allowed for Kerberos\".\n\nDue to the various possible combinations, it is not possible to include all acceptable values as viewed directly in the registry.\n\nThe value must be converted to binary to determine configuration of specific bits.  This will determine whether this is a finding.\n\nNote the value for the registry key.\nFor example when all suites, including the DES suites are selected, the value will be \"0x7fffffff (2147483647)\".\n\nOpen the Windows calculator (Run/Search for \"calc\").\nSelect \"View\", then \"Programmer\".\nSelect \"Dword\" and either \"Hex\" or \"Dec\".\nEnter the appropriate form of the value found for the registry key (e.g., Hex - enter 0x7fffffff, Dec - enter 2147483647).\nSelect \"Bin\".\n\nThe returned value may vary in length, up to 32 characters.\n\nIf either of the 2 right most characters are \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf both of the 2 right most characters are \"0\", this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Certain encryption types are no longer considered secure.  This setting configures a minimum encryption type for Kerberos, preventing the use of the DES encryption suites.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"2981","uuid":"a234bb42-ee9a-499f-97dc-4f2515f67595","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FC12D926B8287E1E72F4829ABF2449B4BA77E038\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The use of DES encryption suites must not be allowed for Kerberos encryption.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21955","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21955","title":"IPv6 Source Routing","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21955","severity":"low","group_title":"IPv6 Source Routing","rule_id_src":"SV-25278r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25278","rule_version":"3.155","rule_title":"IPv6 source routing must be configured to highest protection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting IPv6) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)\" to \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting IPv6) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)\" is not set to \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip6\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  DisableIpSourceRouting\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  2","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IPv6 source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4749","uuid":"73f6075b-c6b9-4436-9f49-dccb42932a98","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9FE080EC6E5D7E31FF683BEDDFAD16CC86F58B4A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'IPv6 source routing must be configured to highest protection.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21956","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21956","title":"IPv6 TCP Data Retransmissions","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21956","severity":"low","group_title":"IPv6 TCP Data Retransmissions","rule_id_src":"SV-25279r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25279","rule_version":"3.156","rule_title":"IPv6 TCP data retransmissions must be configured to prevent resources from becoming exhausted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"MSS: (TcpMaxDataRetransmissions IPv6) How many times unacknowledged data is retransmitted (3 recommended, 5 is default)\" to \"3\" or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"MSS: (TcpMaxDataRetransmissions IPv6) How many times unacknowledged data is retransmitted (3 recommended, 5 is default)\" is not set to \"3\" or less, this is a finding.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip6\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  TcpMaxDataRetransmissions\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  3 (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring Windows to limit the number of times that IPv6 TCP retransmits unacknowledged data segments before aborting the attempt helps prevent resources from becoming exhausted.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"2472","uuid":"8c10dd1c-1948-4dea-afd2-8ed1c6b2f6d7","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 83EAA7D653CD3910DF1A8FF7F43ADD39663D45A9\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'IPv6 TCP data retransmissions must be configured to prevent resources from becoming exhausted.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21960","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21960","title":"Elevate when setting a network\u2019s location","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21960","severity":"low","group_title":"Elevate when setting a network\u2019s location","rule_id_src":"SV-25286r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25286","rule_version":"5.270","rule_title":"Require domain users to elevate when setting a network\u2019s location.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> Network Connections -> \u201cRequire domain users to elevate when setting a network's location\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Network Connections\\\n\nValue Name:  NC_StdDomainUserSetLocation\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy requires domain users to elevate when setting a network\u2019s location.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"6288","uuid":"d3504f05-7895-4456-9060-f26dab523b21","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DC04D536A9F586A8E784CA2608CAA4E48800A2AA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Require domain users to elevate when setting a network\u2019s location.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21961","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21961","title":"Direct Access \u2013 Route Through Internal Network","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21961","severity":"low","group_title":"Direct Access \u2013 Route Through Internal Network","rule_id_src":"SV-25287r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25287","rule_version":"5.271","rule_title":"Route all Direct Access  traffic through internal network.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> Network Connections -> \u201cRoute all traffic through the internal network\u201d to \u201cEnabled: Enabled State\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\TCPIP\\v6Transition\\\n\nValue Name:  Force_Tunneling\n\nType:  REG_SZ\nValue:  Enabled","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting ensures all traffic is routed through the internal network, allowing monitoring and preventing split tunneling.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9733","uuid":"8be68fab-c5d2-440c-a3ff-6984648cb6c1","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 81720B1ED6CF446FD784A21F98BABA1176D11564\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Route all Direct Access  traffic through internal network.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21963","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21963","title":"Windows Update Point and Print Driver Search","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21963","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows Update Point and Print Driver Search","rule_id_src":"SV-25289r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25289","rule_version":"5.272","rule_title":"Prevent searching Windows Update for point and print drivers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Printers -> \u201cExtend Point and Print connection to search Windows Update\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name:  DoNotInstallCompatibleDriverFromWindowsUpdate\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting will prevent Windows from searching Windows Update for point and print drivers.  Only the local driver store and server driver cache will be searched.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"2689","uuid":"d37c2979-8247-41e1-9f35-cfd71b97574e","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E1C228C3E66B7E4303D2B66463C879040E880591\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Prevent searching Windows Update for point and print drivers.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21964","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21964","title":"Prevent device metadata retrieval from Internet","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21964","severity":"low","group_title":"Prevent device metadata retrieval from Internet","rule_id_src":"SV-25290r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-25290","rule_version":"5.273","rule_title":"Device metadata retrieval from the Internet must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Installation >> \"Prevent device metadata retrieval from the Internet\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Device Metadata\\\n\nValue Name:  PreventDeviceMetadataFromNetwork\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  This setting will prevent Windows from retrieving device metadata from the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7284","uuid":"b37f2d15-7b5d-4ca6-ae83-17fad9883b6c","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D4444AF0FF7F331A913EFFA2E31E14522C6FB552\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Device metadata retrieval from the Internet must be prevented.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21965","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21965","title":"Prevent Windows Update for device driver search","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21965","severity":"low","group_title":"Prevent Windows Update for device driver search","rule_id_src":"SV-25291r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25291","rule_version":"5.274","rule_title":"Prevent Windows Update for device driver search","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Device Installation -> \u201cSpecify Search Order for device driver source locations\u201d to \u201cEnabled: Do not search Windows Update\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:   \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DriverSearching\\\n\nValue Name:  SearchOrderConfig\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting will prevent from searching Windows Update for device drivers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"8237","uuid":"6f103498-83ad-48c9-acf4-ace3a5d5dbd5","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DE76641EACBB66A125B2B47C823B554B604B6140\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Prevent Windows Update for device driver search' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21966","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21966","title":"Handwriting personalization data sharing","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21966","severity":"low","group_title":"Handwriting personalization data sharing","rule_id_src":"SV-25292r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25292","rule_version":"5.275","rule_title":"Prevent handwriting personalization data sharing with Microsoft.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communications Management - > Internet Communication settings -> \u201cTurn off handwriting personalization data sharing\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\TabletPC\\\n\nValue Name:  PreventHandwritingDataSharing\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting prevents data from the handwriting recognition personalization tool being shared with Microsoft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5610","uuid":"bf707611-d644-4cab-ba8f-23e6a18bfc6b","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E87F2FBAD93BAF825359A9ECE220D6D5BD166727\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Prevent handwriting personalization data sharing with Microsoft.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21967","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21967","title":"MSDT Interactive Communication","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21967","severity":"low","group_title":"MSDT Interactive Communication","rule_id_src":"SV-25293r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25293","rule_version":"5.276","rule_title":"Prevent Microsoft Support Diagnostic Tool (MSDT) interactive communication with Microsoft.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Troubleshooting and Diagnostics -> Microsoft Support Diagnostic Tool -> \u201cMicrosoft Support Diagnostic Tool: Turn on MSDT interactive communication with Support Provider\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\ScriptedDiagnosticsProvider\\Policy\\\n\nValue Name:  DisableQueryRemoteServer\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting prevents the MSDT from communicating with and sending collected data to Microsoft, the default support provider.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4056","uuid":"df0ed6f9-2b49-44ce-9d7d-5fc1634a1502","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CF29E92531724E780E8A72046C1879E212875759\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Prevent Microsoft Support Diagnostic Tool (MSDT) interactive communication with Microsoft.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21969","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21969","title":"Windows Online Troubleshooting Service","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21969","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows Online Troubleshooting Service","rule_id_src":"SV-25295r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25295","rule_version":"5.277","rule_title":"Prevent access to Windows Online Troubleshooting Service (WOTS).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Troubleshooting and Diagnostics -> Scripted Diagnostics -> \u201cTroubleshooting: Allow users to access online troubleshooting content on Microsoft servers from the Troubleshooting Control Panel (via Windows Online Troubleshooting Service - WOTS)\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\ScriptedDiagnosticsProvider\\Policy\\\n\nValue Name:  EnableQueryRemoteServer\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting prevents users from searching troubleshooting content on Microsoft servers.  Only local content will be available.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6514","uuid":"706fe66d-9b36-4857-a5e4-960944841ffc","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D6E180D9EEAF3C46E4543E6D17BA1582BD8E3BA5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Prevent access to Windows Online Troubleshooting Service (WOTS).' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21970","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21970","title":"Disable PerfTrack","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21970","severity":"low","group_title":"Disable PerfTrack","rule_id_src":"SV-25296r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25296","rule_version":"5.278","rule_title":"Disable Performance PerfTrack.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Troubleshooting and Diagnostics -> Windows Performance PerfTrack -> \u201cEnable/Disable PerfTrack\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WDI\\{9c5a40da-b965-4fc3-8781-88dd50a6299d}\\\n\nValue Name:  ScenarioExecutionEnabled\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting prevents responsiveness events from being aggregated and sent to Microsoft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1924","uuid":"5062dcf1-351e-4a32-b73f-95ffb9374c5f","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-21971","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21971","title":"Application Compatibility Program Inventory","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21971","severity":"low","group_title":"Application Compatibility Program Inventory","rule_id_src":"SV-25297r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25297","rule_version":"5.279","rule_title":"Prevent the Application Compatibility Program Inventory from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Application Compatibility -> \u201cTurn off Program Inventory\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppCompat\\\n\nValue Name:  DisableInventory\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting will prevent the Program Inventory from collecting data about a system and sending the information to Microsoft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1757","uuid":"9b5b99c9-d2c7-4f83-8cdd-6ed3cfd7fbb1","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2785BF0BD90D35C334CE7320B130EB7C8A39FCAE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Prevent the Application Compatibility Program Inventory from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21973","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21973","title":"Autoplay for non-volume devices","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21973","severity":"medium","group_title":"Autoplay for non-volume devices","rule_id_src":"SV-25299r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25299","rule_version":"5.280","rule_title":"Turn off autoplay for non-volume devices.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> AutoPlay Policies -> \u201cTurn off Autoplay for non-volume devices\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name:  NoAutoplayfornonVolume\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting will disable autoplay for non-volume devices (such as Media Transfer Protocol (MTP) devices).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"4431","uuid":"27f2a720-f360-4a35-ac1d-8ec4b788dfeb","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5A9E4E45FBF17650F5C4B904E6464EFDB3EFB5CA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Turn off autoplay for non-volume devices.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21974","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21974","title":"Turn Off Game Updates","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21974","severity":"low","group_title":"Turn Off Game Updates","rule_id_src":"SV-25300r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25300","rule_version":"5.281","rule_title":"Turn off downloading of game updates.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Game Explorer -> \u201cTurn off game updates\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\GameUX\\\n\nValue Name:  GameUpdateOptions\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting will prevent the system from downloading game update information from Windows Metadata Services.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"9250","uuid":"bed6eb82-bfc4-4624-be21-89afbc0f17b4","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CF7BC8F211BBDD78FC7C5A7DD445456F5455DD79\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Turn off downloading of game updates.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21975","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21975","title":"Prevent Joining Homegroup","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21975","severity":"medium","group_title":"Prevent Joining Homegroup","rule_id_src":"SV-25301r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25301","rule_version":"5.282","rule_title":"Prevent the system from joining a homegroup.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> HomeGroup -> \u201cPrevent the computer from joining a homegroup\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Homegroup\\\n\nValue Name:  DisableHomeGroup\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting will prevent a system from being joined to a homegroup.  Homegroups are a method of sharing data and printers on a home network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2144","uuid":"4a64deb5-82c5-457f-bf67-0c31a45ad6b4","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CFEBBC41C21B82E4CB00CD874E8DD629156D3936\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Prevent the system from joining a homegroup.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21978","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21978","title":"Windows Anytime Upgrade","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21978","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows Anytime Upgrade","rule_id_src":"SV-25304r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25304","rule_version":"5.284","rule_title":"Windows Anytime Upgrade is not disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Anytime Upgrade -> \u201cPrevent Windows Anytime Upgrade from running\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\WAU\\\n\nValue Name:  Disabled\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting will prevent Windows Anytime Upgrade from running.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3734","uuid":"28ba372d-76d8-420a-bfdf-c17bce7b103c","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 90915B001A2DFA9BE297C5A1AA456FF91AF0C7BD\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Anytime Upgrade is not disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-21980","group_tree":[{"id":"V-21980","title":"Explorer Data Execution Prevention","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-21980","severity":"medium","group_title":"Explorer Data Execution Prevention","rule_id_src":"SV-25306r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-25306","rule_version":"5.285","rule_title":"Explorer Data Execution Prevention is disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Explorer -> \u201cTurn off Data Execution Prevention for Explorer\u201d to \u201cDisabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value doesn\u2019t exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name:  NoDataExecutionPrevention\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting will prevent Data Execution Prevention from being turned off for Windows Explorer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"8737","uuid":"0da3dc83-d3ba-4dc0-8a0e-544670cb6d50","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5A6DDCCA255A6163ABAF6FB543A1B1B1AE492933\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Explorer Data Execution Prevention is disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-22692","group_tree":[{"id":"V-22692","title":"Default Autorun Behavior","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-22692","severity":"high","group_title":"Default Autorun Behavior","rule_id_src":"SV-27159r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-27159","rule_version":"5.286","rule_title":"The default autorun behavior must be configured to prevent autorun commands.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> AutoPlay Policies -> \"Default behavior for AutoRun\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Do not execute any autorun commands\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name:  NoAutorun\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing autorun commands to execute may introduce malicious code to a system.  Configuring this setting prevents autorun commands from executing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"6822","uuid":"324b6566-7be6-42ed-9941-b78b7d3bcf1c","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FEE3D8187AC8A8955CCC569603C71ECA96EDA14C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The default autorun behavior must be configured to prevent autorun commands.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26070","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26070","title":"Winlogon Registry Permissions","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26070","severity":"high","group_title":"Winlogon Registry Permissions","rule_id_src":"SV-33309r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-33309","rule_version":"2.023","rule_title":"Standard user accounts must only have Read permissions to the Winlogon registry key.","fix_text":"Maintain permissions at least as restrictive as the defaults listed below for the \"WinLogon\" registry key.  It is recommended to not change the permissions from the defaults.\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nThe following are the same for each permission listed:\nType - Allow\nInherited from - MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\nApply to - This key and subkeys\n\nColumns: Name - Permission\nTrustedInstaller - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\nUsers - Read","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run \"Regedit\".\nNavigate to the following registry key:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nRight-click on \"WinLogon\" and select \"Permissions\u2026\".\nSelect \"Advanced\".\n\nIf the permissions are not as restrictive as the defaults listed below, this is a finding.\n\nThe following are the same for each permission listed:\nType - Allow\nInherited from - MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\nApply to - This key and subkeys\n\nColumns: Name - Permission\nTrustedInstaller - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\nUsers - Read","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Permissions on the Winlogon registry key must only allow privileged accounts to change registry values. If standard users have this capability there is a potential for programs to run with elevated privileges when a privileged user logs on to the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2703","uuid":"a968f4f8-5330-4a4d-a725-65836e60a697","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2D3CE1A232A4AB4BF39A36AE11CA21A313E71D89\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Standard user accounts must only have Read permissions to the Winlogon registry key.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26283","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26283","title":"Restrict Anonymous SAM Enumeration","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26283","severity":"high","group_title":"Restrict Anonymous SAM Enumeration","rule_id_src":"SV-36025r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-36025","rule_version":"3.019","rule_title":"Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts will not be allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy values for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \u201cNetwork access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts\u201d to \u201cEnabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in. \nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options. \n\nIf the value for \u201cNetwork access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts\u201d is not set to \u201cEnabled\u201d, then this is a finding. \n\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictAnonymousSAM\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This is a Category 1 finding as it allows anonymous logon users (null session connections) to list all account names, thus providing a list of potential points to attack the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7292","uuid":"b69af38f-8e87-43e9-9d17-2241cd1a5052","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 66F49F484AEC852BDDC039944EECEDCDC7B32735\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts will not be allowed.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26359","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26359","title":"Legal Banner Dialog Box Title","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26359","severity":"low","group_title":"Legal Banner Dialog Box Title","rule_id_src":"SV-34594r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-34594","rule_version":"3.014","rule_title":"The Windows dialog box title for the legal banner must be configured.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options \u201cInteractive Logon: Message title for users attempting to log on\u201d to \u201cDoD Notice and Consent Banner\u201d, \u201cUS Department of Defense Warning Statement\u201d, or a site defined equivalent.  \n\nIf a site defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the banner text required in V-1089.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \u201cInteractive Logon: Message title for users attempting to log on\u201d is not set to \u201cDoD Notice and Consent Banner\u201d, \u201cUS Department of Defense Warning Statement\u201d, or a site defined equivalent, this is a finding.  \n\nIf a site defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the banner text required in V-1089.\n\nAutomated tools may only search for the titles defined above.  If a site defined title is used, a manual review will be required.\n\nThe policy referenced configures the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeCaption\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: See message title above","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000048","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"3852","uuid":"549ec3d2-9d68-4c88-b42c-4c486e7f5d3e","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F191587723C47EC4C5F6D7F2B59DEE745F6885C3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows dialog box title for the legal banner must be configured.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26469","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26469","title":"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26469","severity":"medium","group_title":"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller","rule_id_src":"SV-35924r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-35924","rule_version":"WINUR-000001","rule_title":"Unauthorized accounts must not have the Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller user right.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right may be able to retrieve the credentials of other accounts from Credential Manager.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3615","uuid":"07f58e48-06e2-440d-9e11-1fd09ea96fb6","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 436FBCAAD010AB6E8126FB9DB3B4C2ABDE21DEF6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthorized accounts must not have the Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller user right.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26470","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26470","title":"Access this computer from the network","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26470","severity":"medium","group_title":"Access this computer from the network","rule_id_src":"SV-35925r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-35925","rule_version":"WINUR-000002","rule_title":"The Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Access this computer from the network\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Access this computer from the network\" right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf a domain application account such as for a management tool requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account, managed at the domain level, must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length and frequency of changes as defined in the Windows server STIGs.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right may access resources on the system, and must be limited to those that require it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"6921","uuid":"62812a4d-72bf-4fe8-a216-e3ae66452f3b","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D21D42716DC62CDACB143F89633AD53040D46187\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26472","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26472","title":"Allow log on locally","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26472","severity":"medium","group_title":"Allow log on locally","rule_id_src":"SV-35927r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-35927","rule_version":"WINUR-000005","rule_title":"Unauthorized accounts will not have the \"Allow log on locally\" user right.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment -> \"Allow log on locally\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators\nUsers   \n\nSystems dedicated to managing Active Directory (AD admin platforms), must only allow Administrators, removing the Users group.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view. \nNavigate to Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Allow log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nUsers\n\nSystems dedicated to managing Active Directory (AD admin platforms), must only allow Administrators, removing the Users group.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Allow log on locally\" right can log on interactively to a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"2713","uuid":"9d3bde7f-a106-4376-b563-23248b6b0647","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6C5FF4654E9BCFC81BD8DF251E1644BB4F79640F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthorized accounts will not have the \"Allow log on locally\" user right.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26473","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26473","title":"Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26473","severity":"medium","group_title":"Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services","rule_id_src":"SV-35928r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-35928","rule_version":"WINUR-000006","rule_title":"Unauthorized accounts must not have the Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services user right.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).\n\nAdministrators may be granted this user right if Remote Desktop Services is necessary for remote administration.  Restricted Admin mode must be used.  This must be document with the ISSO.\nSee Microsoft article KB2871997 for patches required to add this function to systems prior to Windows 8.1.\n\nRestricted Admin mode for Remote Desktop Connections can be implemented for each session using a command line switch to start the Remote Desktop Client or through a group policy to enable it for all sessions.\n\nThe command line to do this is \"mstsc /restrictedadmin\".\n\nTo enable this with group policy, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Credentials Delegation >> \"Restrict delegation of credentials to remote servers\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services\" right, this is a finding.\n\nAdministrators may be granted this user right if Remote Desktop Services is necessary for remote administration.  Restricted Admin mode must be used.  This must be document with the ISSO.\nSee Microsoft article KB2871997 for updates required to add this function to systems prior to Windows 8.1.\n\nRestricted Admin mode for Remote Desktop Connections can be implemented for each session using a command line switch to start the Remote Desktop Client or through a group policy to enable it for all sessions.\n\nThe command line to do this is \"mstsc /restrictedadmin\".\n\nTo enable this with group policy, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Credentials Delegation >> \"Restrict delegation of credentials to remote servers\" to \"Enabled\".","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right can access a system through Remote Desktop.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"8091","uuid":"96f2abe9-7f14-4647-9107-097e89de3f18","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 975CD264E0B72F860398C845A4B039FF48AC640C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthorized accounts must not have the Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services user right.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26474","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26474","title":"Back up files and directories","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26474","severity":"medium","group_title":"Back up files and directories","rule_id_src":"SV-35929r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-35929","rule_version":"WINUR-000007","rule_title":"Unauthorized accounts must not have the Back up files and directories user right.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Back up files and directories\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Back up files and directories\" right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Back up files and directories\" user right can circumvent file and directory permissions and could allow access to sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"7175","uuid":"3d5e0373-bfc3-4a7a-a897-9ed893fe0f45","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6939E68146E0F0CB01FADB3990F7588A70CB0354\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthorized accounts must not have the Back up files and directories user right.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26476","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26476","title":"Change the system time","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26476","severity":"medium","group_title":"Change the system time","rule_id_src":"SV-35931r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-35931","rule_version":"WINUR-000009","rule_title":"Unauthorized accounts must not have the Change the system time user right.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Change the system time\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators\nLocal Service","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Change the system time\" right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nLocal Service","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Change the system time\" user right can change the system time, which can impact authentication, as well as affect time stamps on event log entries.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"1326","uuid":"b7c5d250-2199-48ad-b263-8cade3a9e9d8","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A2AB74758258C46A1D794ACA229E6E63A1A7A713\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthorized accounts must not have the Change the system time user right.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26478","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26478","title":"Create a pagefile","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26478","severity":"medium","group_title":"Create a pagefile","rule_id_src":"SV-35933r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-35933","rule_version":"WINUR-000011","rule_title":"Unauthorized accounts must not have the Create a pagefile user right.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create a pagefile\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create a pagefile\" right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create a pagefile\" user right can change the size of a pagefile, which could affect system performance.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2304","uuid":"3d055b06-0529-4fee-bc67-142429cb5862","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 96B0C967FF17CBCC743C9D58AF8123DAD0D02715\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthorized accounts must not have the Create a pagefile user right.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26479","group_tree":[{"i