ight can circumvent file and directory permissions and could allow access to sensitive data.  It could also be used to over-write more current data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"6627","uuid":"be1df8b5-a528-4f7e-ad2d-8e1d1324c0c5","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C10E4B3C975AD0EEB354583116999E0539031FB0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthorized accounts must not have the Restore files and directories user right.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26506","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26506","title":"Take ownership of files or other objects","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26506","severity":"medium","group_title":"Take ownership of files or other objects","rule_id_src":"SV-35961r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-35961","rule_version":"WINUR-000042","rule_title":"Unauthorized accounts must not have the Take ownership of files or other objects user right.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Analyze the system using the Security Configuration and Analysis snap-in.\nExpand the Security Configuration and Analysis tree view.\nNavigate to Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" user right can take ownership of objects and make changes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3714","uuid":"e0d7826f-1a45-4e0c-8936-75f916610eb5","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-26529","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26529","title":"Audit - Credential Validation - Success","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26529","severity":"medium","group_title":"Audit - Credential Validation - Success","rule_id_src":"SV-35966r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-35966","rule_version":"WINAU-000101","rule_title":"The system will be configured to audit \"Account Logon -> Credential Validation\" successes.","fix_text":"Detailed auditing subcategories are configured in Security Settings -> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration.   The summary level settings under Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Audit Policy will not be enforced (see V-14230).\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration -> System Audit Policies -> Account Logon -> \"Audit Credential Validation\" with \u201cSuccess\u201d selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \u201cAudit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\u201d must be set to \u201cEnabled\u201d (V-14230) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n-Open a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\u201cRun as Administrator\u201d).\n-Enter \u201cAuditPol /get /category:*\u201d.\n\nCompare the Auditpol settings with the following.  If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nAccount Logon -> Credential Validation  - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred as well as detecting attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nCredential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"6919","uuid":"6d7e02fa-1594-4a6d-a932-2c5e98b216a1","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DD1D5C73712D95EDC3F4F2C4C8D8F984BC1F5697\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system will be configured to audit \"Account Logon -> Credential Validation\" successes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26530","group_tree":[{"