gs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred as well as detecting attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSecurity System Extension records events related to extension code being loaded by the security subsystem.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"2640","uuid":"d154cb81-3d24-4ea5-8b42-2a180014e635","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A19546A9AFDBD594DC8E617E97F362204B034E95\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system will be configured to audit \"System -> Security System Extension\" successes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26557","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26557","title":"Audit - System Integrity - Success","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26557","severity":"medium","group_title":"Audit - System Integrity - Success","rule_id_src":"SV-36003r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-36003","rule_version":"WINAU-000905","rule_title":"The system will be configured to audit \"System -> System Integrity\" successes.","fix_text":"Detailed auditing subcategories are configured in Security Settings -> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration.   The summary level settings under Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Audit Policy will not be enforced (see V-14230).\n\nCon