isibility.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000382"],"reference_identifier":"3922","uuid":"23342884-7e3d-4c47-a960-f7cd46c35fab","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7CB5A0ECA319C9F00362FAF556D13EFA1E8706E2\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Teredo IPv6 transition technology will be disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26579","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26579","title":"Maximum Log Size - Application","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26579","severity":"medium","group_title":"Maximum Log Size - Application","rule_id_src":"SV-36021r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-36021","rule_version":"WINAU-100100","rule_title":"The Application event log must be configured to a minimum size requirement.","fix_text":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Event Log Service -> Application -> \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Application\\\n\nValue Name:  MaxSize\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly.  This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"3332","uuid":"181e6002-430d-4a9f-863e-f8443a63b820","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3F2A74A550BC9CD89C94C90C13D5D13CC66C0455\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Application event log must be configured to a minimum size requirement.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26580","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26580","title":"Maximum Log Size - Security","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26580","severity":"medium","group_title":"Maximum Log Size - Security","rule_id_src":"SV-36022r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-36022","rule_version":"WINAU-100101","rule_title":"The Security event log size must be configured to 196608 KB or greater.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> Security >> \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"196608\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA. This must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Security\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00030000 (196608) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly.  This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"2641","uuid":"0653ccd2-67aa-460b-b8a3-169b8baebea6","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1E6A9B41CA25038535721780BFC5BC39257B429F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Security event log size must be configured to 196608 KB or greater.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26581","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26581","title":"Maximum Log Size - Setup","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26581","severity":"medium","group_title":"Maximum Log Size - Setup","rule_id_src":"SV-36023r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-36023","rule_version":"WINAU-100102","rule_title":"The Setup event log must be configured to a minimum size requirement.","fix_text":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Event Log Service -> Setup -> \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Setup\\\n\nValue Name:  MaxSize\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly.  This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"1836","uuid":"6a652e04-1668-4010-bcf2-3f3db42d097b","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 342E1641054FEB8C168297873FC1575A3E9919EF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Setup event log must be configured to a minimum size requirement.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-26582","group_tree":[{"id":"V-26582","title":"Maximum Log Size - System","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-26582","severity":"medium","group_title":"Maximum Log Size - System","rule_id_src":"SV-36024r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-36024","rule_version":"WINAU-100103","rule_title":"The System event log must be configured to a minimum size requirement.","fix_text":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Event Log Service -> System -> \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  MaxSize\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly.  This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"9106","uuid":"551b149f-4236-48b0-aad5-810da8a5a1a3","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2F3D97A5E6C6AB10317110884371FEAF20FAD3B5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The System event log must be configured to a minimum size requirement.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-32272","group_tree":[{"id":"V-32272","title":"WINPK-000001","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-32272","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINPK-000001","rule_id_src":"SV-42595r5_rule","rule_id":"SV-42595","rule_version":"WINPK-000001","rule_title":"The DoD Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store.","fix_text":"Install the DoD Root CA certificates.\nDoD Root CA 2\nDoD Root CA 3\nDoD Root CA 4\n\nThe InstallRoot tool is available on IASE at http://iase.disa.mil/pki-pke/Pages/tools.aspx.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the DoD Root CA certificates are installed as Trusted Root Certification Authorities.\n\nThe certificates and thumbprints referenced below apply to unclassified systems; see PKE documentation for other networks.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\nExecute the following command:\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\root | Where-object {$_.Subject -Like \"*DoD*\"} | FL Subject, Thumbprint\nIf the following information is not displayed, this is finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 8C941B34EA1EA6ED9AE2BC54CF687252B4C9B561\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 4, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\n\nAlternately use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\nRun \"MMC\".\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\nClick \"OK\".\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to \"Trusted Root Certification Authorities >> Certificates\".\nIf there are no entries for \"DoD Root CA 2\", \"DoD Root CA 3\", and \"DoD Root CA 4\", this is a finding.\n\nFor each of the DoD Root CA certificates noted above:\nRight click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\nSelect the \"Details\" Tab.\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted below, this is a finding.\nDoD Root CA 2 - 8C941B34EA1EA6ED9AE2BC54CF687252B4C9B561\nDoD Root CA 3 - D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nDoD Root CA 4 - B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure secure DoD websites and DoD-signed code are properly validated, the system must trust the DoD Root Certificate Authorities (CAs). The DoD root certificates will ensure that the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the DoD CAs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"5832","uuid":"48c6a622-1f24-4602-952e-254d3682f34e","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 578ED57037D19D58A2CBD552D78E7B76F4E39E4C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The DoD Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-32273","group_tree":[{"id":"V-32273","title":"WINPK-000002","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-32273","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINPK-000002","rule_id_src":"SV-42601r4_rule","rule_id":"SV-42601","rule_version":"WINPK-000002","rule_title":"The External Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the ECA Root CA certificates on unclassified systems.\nECA Root CA 2\nECA Root CA 4\n\nThe InstallRoot tool is available on IASE at http://iase.disa.mil/pki-pke/Pages/tools.aspx.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the ECA Root CA certificates are installed on unclassified systems as Trusted Root Certification Authorities.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\nExecute the following command:\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\root | Where-object {$_.Subject -Like \"*ECA*\"} | FL Subject, Thumbprint\nIf the following information is not displayed, this is finding.\n\nSubject: CN=ECA Root CA 2, OU=ECA, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: C313F919A6ED4E0E8451AFA930FB419A20F181E4\n\nSubject: CN=ECA Root CA 4, OU=ECA, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 73E8BB08E337D6A5A6AEF90CFFDD97D9176CB582\n\nAlternately use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\nRun \"MMC\".\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\nClick \"OK\".\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to \"Trusted Root Certification Authorities >> Certificates\".\nIf there are no entries for \"ECA Root CA 2\", and \"ECA Root CA 4\", this is a finding.\n\nFor each of the ECA Root CA certificates noted above:\nRight click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\nSelect the \"Details\" Tab.\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted below, this is a finding.\nECA Root CA 2 - C313F919A6ED4E0E8451AFA930FB419A20F181E4\nECA Root CA 4 - 73E8BB08E337D6A5A6AEF90CFFDD97D9176CB582","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure secure websites protected with External Certificate Authority (ECA) server certificates are properly validated, the system must trust the ECA Root CAs. The ECA root certificates will ensure the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the External CAs. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"6297","uuid":"d01f5b7a-cc82-4f71-8acc-dfc7bb78945a","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B72FF0420E89BAAC937E4123B77F1328358E49F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The External Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store on unclassified systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-32274","group_tree":[{"id":"V-32274","title":"WINPK-000003","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-32274","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINPK-000003","rule_id_src":"SV-42606r6_rule","rule_id":"SV-42606","rule_version":"WINPK-000003","rule_title":"The DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\nDoD Root CA 2 - DoD Interoperability Root CA 1 - 22BBE981F0694D246CC1472ED2B021DC8540A22F\nDoD Root CA 3 - DoD Interoperability Root CA 2 - FFAD03329B9E527A43EEC66A56F9CBB5393E6E13\nDoD Root CA 3 - DoD Interoperability Root CA 2 - FCE1B1E25374DD94F5935BEB86CA643D8C8D1FF4\n\nAdministrators should run the Federal Bridge Certification Authority (FBCA) Cross-Certificate Removal Tool once as an administrator and once as the current user.\n\nThe FBCA Cross-Certificate Remover tool and user guide is available on IASE at http://iase.disa.mil/pki-pke/Pages/tools.aspx.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the DoD Interoperability cross-certificates are installed on unclassified systems as Untrusted Certificates.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\nExecute the following command:\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where-object {$_.Issuer -Like \"*DoD Interoperability*\" -and $_.Subject -Like \"*DoD*\"} | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint\nIf the following information is not displayed, this is finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=DoD Interoperability Root CA 1, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 22BBE981F0694D246CC1472ED2B021DC8540A22F\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=DoD Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: FFAD03329B9E527A43EEC66A56F9CBB5393E6E13\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=DoD Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: FCE1B1E25374DD94F5935BEB86CA643D8C8D1FF4\n\nAlternately use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\nRun \"MMC\".\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\nClick \"OK\".\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to \"Untrusted Certificates >> Certificates\".\n\nFor each certificate with \"DoD Root CA\u2026\" under \"Issued To\" and \"DoD Interoperability Root CA\u2026\" under \"Issued By\":\nRight click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\nSelect the \"Details\" Tab.\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\nDoD Root CA 2 - DoD Interoperability Root CA 1 - 22BBE981F0694D246CC1472ED2B021DC8540A22F\nDoD Root CA 3 - DoD Interoperability Root CA 2 - FFAD03329B9E527A43EEC66A56F9CBB5393E6E13\nDoD Root CA 3 - DoD Interoperability Root CA 2 - FCE1B1E25374DD94F5935BEB86CA643D8C8D1FF4","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DoD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DoD Root CAs, the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"1228","uuid":"e86067b1-89f0-440c-a395-9868fff61f8b","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 67871886F471DC29A9A70F9269BB6E712DD9127B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-32282","group_tree":[{"id":"V-32282","title":"WINRG-000001 Active Setup\\Installed Components Registry Permissions","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-32282","severity":"high","group_title":"WINRG-000001 Active Setup\\Installed Components Registry Permissions","rule_id_src":"SV-42618r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-42618","rule_version":"WINRG-000001","rule_title":"Standard user accounts must only have Read permissions to the Active Setup\\Installed Components registry key.","fix_text":"Maintain the default permissions of the following registry keys:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Active Setup\\Installed Components\\\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\Active Setup\\Installed Components\\ (64-bit systems only)\n \nUsers - Read\nAdministrators - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nCREATOR OWNER - Special\n(Special = Full Control - Subkeys only)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run \"Regedit\".\nNavigate to the following registry keys and review the permissions:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Active Setup\\Installed Components\\\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\Active Setup\\Installed Components\\ (64-bit systems)\n\nIf the default permissions listed below have been changed, this is a finding.\n\nUsers - Read\nAdministrators - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nCREATOR OWNER - Special\n(Special = Full Control - Subkeys only)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Permissions on the Active Setup\\Installed Components registry key must only allow privileged accounts to add or change registry values.  If standard user accounts have this capability there is a potential for programs to run with elevated privileges when a privileged user logs on to the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9836","uuid":"6987857a-f736-4b59-9578-6489524df31d","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-34974","group_tree":[{"id":"V-34974","title":"Always Install with Elevated Privileges Disabled","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-34974","severity":"high","group_title":"Always Install with Elevated Privileges Disabled","rule_id_src":"SV-46219r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-46219","rule_version":"WINCC-000001","rule_title":"The Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Installer -> \"Always install with elevated privileges\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nSubkey: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: AlwaysInstallElevated\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Standard user accounts must not be granted elevated privileges.  Enabling Windows Installer to elevate privileges when installing applications can allow malicious persons and applications to gain full control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"5437","uuid":"8d99b738-c0ce-4dc1-b22b-545b12bbb99b","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CBC786753C8709E1A093EAA7AC715D80F04D1BB0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-36439","group_tree":[{"id":"V-36439","title":"Local admin accounts filtered token policy enabled on domain systems.","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-36439","severity":"medium","group_title":"Local admin accounts filtered token policy enabled on domain systems.","rule_id_src":"SV-47847r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-47847","rule_version":"WINRG-000003","rule_title":"Local administrator accounts must have their privileged token filtered to prevent elevated privileges from being used over the network on domain systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"Apply UAC restrictions to local accounts on network logons\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is NA. \nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding: \n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LocalAccountTokenFilterPolicy\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)\n\nThis setting may cause issues with some network scanning tools if local administrative accounts are used remotely.  Scans should use domain accounts where possible.  If a local administrative account must be used, temporarily enabling the privileged token by configuring the registry value to 1 may be required.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A compromised local administrator account can provide means for an attacker to move laterally between domain systems. \n\nWith User Account Control enabled, filtering the privileged token for local administrator accounts will prevent the elevated privileges of these accounts from being used over the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"4146","uuid":"e9a8746d-b8a1-4878-a92c-aa33e29e639e","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 497AFC0AADA0C04AE23FD8194D16A688074881AF\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Local administrator accounts must have their privileged token filtered to prevent elevated privileges from being used over the network on domain systems.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-36440","group_tree":[{"id":"V-36440","title":"Inbound Firewall Exception for Administration","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-36440","severity":"medium","group_title":"Inbound Firewall Exception for Administration","rule_id_src":"SV-47860r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-47860","rule_version":"WINFW-000100","rule_title":"Inbound exceptions to the firewall on domain workstations must only allow authorized management systems and remote management hosts.","fix_text":"Ensure firewall exceptions to inbound connections on domain workstations only allow authorized management systems and remote management hosts.\n\nFirewall rules can be complex and should be thoroughly tested be applying in a production environment.\n\nOne method for restricting inbound connections is to only allow exceptions for a specific scope of remote IP addresses.  For any inbound rules that allow connections from other systems, configure the Scope for Remote IP address to those of authorized management systems and remote management hosts. This may be defined as an IP address, subnet or range. Apply the rule to all firewall profiles.\n\nIf a third-party firewall is used, configure inbound exceptions to only include authorized remote management hosts.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify firewall exceptions for inbound connections on domain workstations only allow authorized management systems and remote management hosts.\n\nReview inbound firewall exception rules in Windows Firewall with Advanced Security.  Firewall rules can be complex and should be reviewed with the firewall administrator.\n\nOne method for restricting inbound connections is to only allow exceptions for a specific scope of remote IP addresses.\n\nIf allowed inbound exceptions are not limited to authorized management systems and remote management hosts, this is a finding.\n\nIf a third-party firewall is used, ensure comparable settings are in place.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing inbound access to domain workstations from other systems may allow lateral movement across systems if credentials are compromised.  Limiting inbound connections only from authorized management systems and remote management hosts will help limit this exposure.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000067"],"reference_identifier":"3888","uuid":"e54985f1-a98d-4159-80ed-fc238fa0e01c","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F81BA2A106B51392EA19333329B1E426C4E07ECE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Inbound exceptions to the firewall on domain workstations must only allow authorized management systems and remote management hosts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-36451","group_tree":[{"id":"V-36451","title":"Accounts with administrative privileges Internet access","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-36451","severity":"high","group_title":"Accounts with administrative privileges Internet access","rule_id_src":"SV-47865r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-47865","rule_version":"1.006-01","rule_title":"Policy must require that administrative user accounts not be used with applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email.","fix_text":"Establish a site policy to prohibit the use applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email, by administrative user accounts.  Ensure the policy is enforced.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if site policy prohibits the use of applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email, by administrative user accounts, except as necessary for local service administration.  If it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Using applications that access the internet or have potential internet sources using administrative privileges exposes a system to compromise.  If a flaw in an application is exploited while running as a privileged user, the entire system could be compromised.  Web browsers and email are common attack vectors for introducing malicious code and must not be run with an administrative user account.\n\nSince administrative user accounts may generally change or work around technical restrictions for running a web browser or other applications, it is essential that policy requires administrative users not access the internet or use applications, such as email.\n\nThe policy should define specific exceptions for local service administration.  These exceptions may include HTTP(S)-based tools that are used for the administration of the local system, services, or attached devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6410","uuid":"d5aae0da-f5b4-4d5f-a311-68cec1c33d78","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E125DED7472046110DBE8583CD22388A2B14C874\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Policy must require that administrative user accounts not be used with applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-36701","group_tree":[{"id":"V-36701","title":"WINCC-000078","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-36701","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINCC-000078","rule_id_src":"SV-49948r6_rule","rule_id":"SV-49948","rule_version":"WINCC-000078","rule_title":"The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) system-wide Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR) must be enabled and configured to Application Opt In.","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> EMET -> \"System ASLR\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Application Opt-In\" selected.\n\nThe Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit must be installed on the system and the administrative template files added to make this setting available.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nIf EMET has not been installed and DEP and SEHOP are configured as required in V-68843 and V-68847, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\EMET\\SysSettings\\\n\nValue Name:  ASLR\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  3","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attackers are constantly looking for vulnerabilities in systems and applications.  The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit can enable several mechanisms, such as Data Execution Prevention (DEP), Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR), and Structured Exception Handler Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) on the system and applications adding additional levels of protection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"3867","uuid":"0e535cfb-b75d-48ab-9b81-fc4a9848e562","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1A68DFCF99B3B7434652F716DFF5D1359670FBD2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) system-wide Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR) must be enabled and configured to Application Opt In.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-36702","group_tree":[{"id":"V-36702","title":"WINCC-000079","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-36702","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINCC-000079","rule_id_src":"SV-50031r6_rule","rule_id":"SV-50031","rule_version":"WINCC-000079","rule_title":"The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) Default Protections for Internet Explorer must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> EMET >> \"Default Protections for Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nNote: The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit must be installed on the system and the administrative template files added to make this setting available.   \n\nDue to a change in the registry structure for EMET 5.5, if the system has a previous version of EMET installed and configured, this setting needs to be set to \"Not Configured\" prior to the upgrade to EMET 5.5, and the new administrative template files copied to the appropriate area.  The setting can then be re-enabled.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nIf EMET has not been installed and DEP and SEHOP are configured as required in V-68843 and V-68847, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\EMET\\Defaults\\\n\nValue Name: *\\Internet Explorer\\iexplore.exe\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: +EAF+ eaf_modules:mshtml.dll;flash*.ocx;jscript*.dll;vbscript.dll;vgx.dll +ASR asr_modules:npjpi*.dll;jp2iexp.dll;vgx.dll;msxml4*.dll;wshom.ocx;scrrun.dll;vbscript.dll asr_zones:1;2\n\nDue to a change in the registry structure for EMET 5.5, if the system has a previous version of EMET installed and configured, this setting needs to be set to \"Not Configured\" prior to the upgrade to EMET 5.5, and the new administrative template files copied to the appropriate area.  The setting can then be re-enabled.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attackers are constantly looking for vulnerabilities in systems and applications.  The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit can enable several mechanisms, such as Data Execution Prevention (DEP), Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR), and Structured Exception Handler Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) on the system and applications adding additional levels of protection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"1407","uuid":"f7559e01-14f4-439f-a031-2587014f39cb","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 027FA27450B9ACECD6F40E53B023B4D8EE8B3E35\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) Default Protections for Internet Explorer must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-36703","group_tree":[{"id":"V-36703","title":"WINCC-000080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-36703","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINCC-000080","rule_id_src":"SV-50043r6_rule","rule_id":"SV-50043","rule_version":"WINCC-000080","rule_title":"The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) Default Protections for Recommended Software must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> EMET >> \"Default Protections for Recommended Software\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nNote: The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit must be installed on the system and the administrative template files added to make this setting available.   \n\nDue to a change in the registry structure for EMET 5.5, if the system has a previous version of EMET installed and configured, this setting needs to be set to \"Not Configured\" prior to the upgrade to EMET 5.5, and the new administrative template files copied to the appropriate area.  The setting can then be re-enabled.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nIf EMET has not been installed and DEP and SEHOP are configured as required in V-68843 and V-68847, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\EMET\\Defaults\\\nValue Type: REG_SZ (for each Value below)\n\nValues noted as \"Blank\" are empty in the registry.\n\nValue Name: *\\Adobe\\*\\Reader\\AcroRd32.exe\nValue: +EAF+ eaf_modules:AcroRd32.dll;Acrofx32.dll;AcroForm.api\n\nValue Name: *\\Adobe\\Acrobat*\\Acrobat\\Acrobat.exe\nValue: +EAF+ eaf_modules:AcroRd32.dll;Acrofx32.dll;AcroForm.api\n\nValue Name: *\\Java\\jre*\\bin\\java.exe\nValue: -HeapSpray\n\nValue Name: *\\Java\\jre*\\bin\\javaw.exe\nValue: -HeapSpray\n\nValue Name: *\\Java\\jre*\\bin\\javaws.exe\nValue: -HeapSpray\n\nValue Name: *\\OFFICE1*\\EXCEL.EXE\nValue: +ASR asr_modules:flash*.ocx\n\nValue Name: *\\OFFICE1*\\INFOPATH.EXE\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\OFFICE1*\\LYNC.EXE\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\OFFICE1*\\MSACCESS.EXE\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\OFFICE1*\\MSPUB.EXE\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\OFFICE1*\\OIS.EXE\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\OFFICE1*\\OUTLOOK.EXE\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\OFFICE1*\\POWERPNT.EXE\nValue: +ASR asr_modules:flash*.ocx\n\nValue Name: *\\OFFICE1*\\PPTVIEW.EXE\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\OFFICE1*\\VISIO.EXE\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\OFFICE1*\\VPREVIEW.EXE\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\OFFICE1*\\WINWORD.EXE\nValue: +ASR asr_modules:flash*.ocx\n\nValue Name: *\\Windows NT\\Accessories\\wordpad.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nDue to a change in the registry structure for EMET 5.5, if the system has a previous version of EMET installed and configured, this setting needs to be set to \"Not Configured\" prior to the upgrade to EMET 5.5, and the new administrative template files copied to the appropriate area.  The setting can then be re-enabled.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attackers are constantly looking for vulnerabilities in systems and applications.  The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit can enable several mechanisms, such as Data Execution Prevention (DEP), Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR), and Structured Exception Handler Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) on the system and applications adding additional levels of protection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"4146","uuid":"369088bc-ee8c-42fc-ab3e-d08bccba0289","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E63CCBE3EB6857A9937220E83D8F341960865414\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) Default Protections for Recommended Software must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-36704","group_tree":[{"id":"V-36704","title":"WINCC-000081","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-36704","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINCC-000081","rule_id_src":"SV-50050r6_rule","rule_id":"SV-50050","rule_version":"WINCC-000081","rule_title":"The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) Default Protections for Popular Software must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> EMET >> \"Default Protections for Popular Software\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nNote: The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit must be installed on the system and the administrative template files added to make this setting available.   \n\nDue to a change in the registry structure for EMET 5.5, if the system has a previous version of EMET installed and configured, this setting needs to be set to \"Not Configured\" prior to the upgrade to EMET 5.5, and the new administrative template files copied to the appropriate area.  The setting can then be re-enabled.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nIf EMET has not been installed and DEP and SEHOP are configured as required in V-68843 and V-68847, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\EMET\\Defaults\\\nValue Type: REG_SZ (for each Value below)\n\nValues noted as \"Blank\" are empty in the registry.\n\nValue Name: *\\7-Zip\\7z.exe\nValue: -EAF\n\nValue Name: *\\7-Zip\\7zG.exe\nValue: -EAF\n\nValue Name: *\\7-Zip\\7zFM.exe\nValue: -EAF\n\nValue Name: *\\Adobe\\Adobe Photoshop CS*\\Photoshop.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Foxit Reader\\Foxit Reader.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Google\\Chrome\\Application\\chrome.exe\nValue: +EAF+ eaf_modules:chrome_child.dll\n\nValue Name: *\\Google\\Google Talk\\googletalk.exe\nValue: -DEP\n\nValue Name: *\\iTunes\\iTunes.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Microsoft Lync\\communicator.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\mIRC\\mirc.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Mozilla Firefox\\firefox.exe\nValue: +EAF+ eaf_modules:mozjs.dll;xul.dll\n\nValue Name: *\\Mozilla Firefox\\plugin-container.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Mozilla Thunderbird\\plugin-container.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Mozilla Thunderbird\\thunderbird.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Opera\\*\\opera.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Opera\\opera.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Pidgin\\pidgin.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\QuickTime\\QuickTimePlayer.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Real\\RealPlayer\\realconverter.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Real\\RealPlayer\\realplay.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Safari\\Safari.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\SkyDrive\\SkyDrive.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Skype\\Phone\\Skype.exe\nValue: -EAF\n\nValue Name: *\\VideoLAN\\VLC\\vlc.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Winamp\\winamp.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Windows Live\\Mail\\wlmail.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Windows Live\\Photo Gallery\\WLXPhotoGallery.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Windows Live\\Writer\\WindowsLiveWriter.exe\nValue:  \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\Windows Media Player\\wmplayer.exe\nValue: -EAF -MandatoryASLR\n\nValue Name: *\\WinRAR\\rar.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\WinRAR\\unrar.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\WinRAR\\winrar.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\WinZip\\winzip32.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nValue Name: *\\WinZip\\winzip64.exe\nValue: \"Blank\"\n\nDue to a change in the registry structure for EMET 5.5, if the system has a previous version of EMET installed and configured, this setting needs to be set to \"Not Configured\" prior to the upgrade to EMET 5.5, and the new administrative template files copied to the appropriate area.  The setting can then be re-enabled.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attackers are constantly looking for vulnerabilities in systems and applications.  The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit can enable several mechanisms, such as Data Execution Prevention (DEP), Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR), and Structured Exception Handler Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) on the system and applications adding additional levels of protection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"2781","uuid":"f65a6fcd-c1ee-462d-b16a-b7c7ef584b5c","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EA8A912EB40182B57714D02EEABD690106BCAA4F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) Default Protections for Popular Software must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-36705","group_tree":[{"id":"V-36705","title":"WINCC-000082","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-36705","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINCC-000082","rule_id_src":"SV-50057r6_rule","rule_id":"SV-50057","rule_version":"WINCC-000082","rule_title":"The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) system-wide Data Execution Prevention (DEP) must be enabled and configured to at least Application Opt Out.","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> EMET -> \"System DEP\" to \"Enabled\" with at least \"Application Opt-Out\" selected. \n\nThe Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit must be installed on the system and the administrative template files added to make this setting available.\n\nDocument applications that do not function properly due to this setting, and are opted out, with the ISSO.\n\nOpted out exceptions can be configured with the following command:\nEMET_Conf --Set \"application path\\executable name\" -DEP\n\nAlternately, configure exceptions in System Properties:\nSelect \"System\" in Control Panel.\nSelect \"Advanced system settings\".\nClick \"Settings\" in the \"Performance\" section.\nSelect the \"Data Execution Prevention\" tab.\nSelect \"Turn on DEP for all programs and services except those I select:\".\n\nApplications that are opted out are configured in the window below this selection.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nIf EMET has not been installed and DEP and SEHOP are configured as required in V-68843 and V-68847, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\EMET\\SysSettings\\\n\nValue Name:  DEP\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  2 (Application Opt Out)\n\nApplications that do not function properly due to this setting, and are opted out, must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attackers are constantly looking for vulnerabilities in systems and applications.  The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit can enable several mechanisms, such as Data Execution Prevention (DEP), Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR), and Structured Exception Handler Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) on the system and applications adding additional levels of protection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"1287","uuid":"a85fd9fa-85e6-4b9f-8dba-97b2db096b5e","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 817EBC29D1CAE3B7AC491468841D3A85DF3930E7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) system-wide Data Execution Prevention (DEP) must be enabled and configured to at least Application Opt Out.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-36706","group_tree":[{"id":"V-36706","title":"WINCC-000083","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-36706","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINCC-000083","rule_id_src":"SV-50063r6_rule","rule_id":"SV-50063","rule_version":"WINCC-000083","rule_title":"The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) system-wide Structured Exception Handler Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) must be configured to Application Opt Out.","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> EMET -> \"System SEHOP\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Application Opt-Out\" selected.\n\nThe Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit must be installed on the system and the administrative template files added to make this setting available.\n\nDocument applications that do not function properly due to this setting, and are opted out, with the ISSO.\n\nOpted out exceptions can be configured with the following command:\nEMET_Conf --Set \"application path\\executable name\" -SEHOP","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nIf EMET has not been installed and DEP and SEHOP are configured as required in V-68843 and V-68847, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\EMET\\SysSettings\\\n\nValue Name:  SEHOP\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  2\n\nApplications that do not function properly due to this setting, and are opted out, must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attackers are constantly looking for vulnerabilities in systems and applications.  The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit can enable several mechanisms, such as Data Execution Prevention (DEP), Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR), and Structured Exception Handler Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) on the system and applications adding additional levels of protection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"2173","uuid":"a8073ff1-aadb-4e90-be2e-eaa700e650d5","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 64B43BB834D5529AF3FBC155EE32B2A953A2DF53\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) system-wide Structured Exception Handler Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) must be configured to Application Opt Out.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-36757","group_tree":[{"id":"V-36757","title":"WN08-MO-000005","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-36757","severity":"medium","group_title":"WN08-MO-000005","rule_id_src":"SV-87197r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-87197","rule_version":"WIN00-000210","rule_title":"Bluetooth must be turned off unless approved by the organization.","fix_text":"Turn off Bluetooth radios not organizationally approved. Establish an organizational policy for the use of Bluetooth.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA if the system does not have Bluetooth.\n\nVerify the Bluetooth radio is turned off unless approved by the organization. If it is not, this is a finding.\n\nApproval must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If not configured properly, Bluetooth may allow rogue devices to communicate with a system.  If a rogue device is paired with a system, there is potential for sensitive information to be compromised.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9305","uuid":"1c2016ca-9223-42f7-9593-1b960f42df47","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 32B2AD2BD55CFDAE623CAE1E3BA5ADDAE4AE0710\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Bluetooth must be turned off unless approved by the organization.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-36759","group_tree":[{"id":"V-36759","title":"WN08-MO-000006","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-36759","severity":"medium","group_title":"WN08-MO-000006","rule_id_src":"SV-87199r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-87199","rule_version":"WIN00-000220","rule_title":"Bluetooth must be turned off when not in use.","fix_text":"Turn off Bluetooth radios when not in use. Establish an organizational policy for the use of Bluetooth to include training of personnel.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA if the system does not have Bluetooth.\n\nVerify the organization has a policy to turn off Bluetooth when not in use and personnel are trained. If it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If not configured properly, Bluetooth may allow rogue devices to communicate with a system.  If a rogue device is paired with a system, there is potential for sensitive information to be compromised.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2395","uuid":"f93739b6-094f-4569-8b88-d1397095db24","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DE0AC8A42808ECAB8D0304E16CF02840B16EF578\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Bluetooth must be turned off when not in use.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-36762","group_tree":[{"id":"V-36762","title":"WN08-MO-000007","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-36762","severity":"medium","group_title":"WN08-MO-000007","rule_id_src":"SV-87201r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-87201","rule_version":"WIN00-000230","rule_title":"The system must notify the user when a Bluetooth device attempts to connect.","fix_text":"Configure Bluetooth to notify users if devices attempt to connect.\nView Bluetooth Settings.\nEnsure \"Alert me when a new Bluetooth device wants to connect\" is checked.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA if the system does not have Bluetooth.\n\nVerify Bluetooth notifies users if devices attempt to connect.\nSearch for \"Bluetooth\".\nSelect \"Devices and Printers\".\nView Bluetooth Settings.\nIf \"Alert me when a new Bluetooth device wants to connect\" is not checked, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If not configured properly, Bluetooth may allow rogue devices to communicate with a system.  If a rogue device is paired with a system, there is potential for sensitive information to be compromised.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8713","uuid":"3eb64e2c-2e89-4a88-8406-6f6a7db510a6","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E0D4BDED837AC73227E542BE12B39544FA047747\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The system must notify the user when a Bluetooth device attempts to connect.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-39137","group_tree":[{"id":"V-39137","title":"WINGE-000100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-39137","severity":"high","group_title":"WINGE-000100","rule_id_src":"SV-50951r7_rule","rule_id":"SV-50951","rule_version":"WINGE-000100","rule_title":"The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) v5.5 or later must be installed on the system.","fix_text":"Install EMET v5.5 or later on the system. EMET is available for download from Microsoft.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nIf EMET has not been installed and DEP and SEHOP are configured as required in V-68843 and V-68847, this is NA.\n\nVerify EMET v5.5 or later is installed on the system.\n\nIf EMET is not installed, or at the minimum required version, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attackers are constantly looking for vulnerabilities in systems and applications.  The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit can enable several mechanisms, such as Data Execution Prevention (DEP), Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR), and Structured Exception Handler Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) on the system and applications adding additional levels of protection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2578","uuid":"7c05a2e4-7d29-4956-860e-45d2c548d1ec","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DA2157597DBA7861C89B8D4250841BAD782655F7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) v5.5 or later must be installed on the system.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-40237","group_tree":[{"id":"V-40237","title":"WINPK-000004","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-40237","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINPK-000004","rule_id_src":"SV-52395r4_rule","rule_id":"SV-52395","rule_version":"WINPK-000004","rule_title":"The US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\nDoD Root CA 2 - US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 1 - DA36FAF56B2F6FBA1604F5BE46D864C9FA013BA3\n\nAdministrators should run the Federal Bridge Certification Authority (FBCA) Cross-Certificate Removal Tool once as an administrator and once as the current user.\n\nThe FBCA Cross-Certificate Remover tool and user guide is available on IASE at http://iase.disa.mil/pki-pke/Pages/tools.aspx.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate is installed on unclassified systems as an Untrusted Certificate.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\nExecute the following command:\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where-object {$_.Issuer -Like \"*CCEB Interoperability*\"} | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint\nIf the following information is not displayed, this is finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 1, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: DA36FAF56B2F6FBA1604F5BE46D864C9FA013BA3\n\nAlternately use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\nRun \"MMC\".\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\nClick \"OK\".\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to \"Untrusted Certificates >> Certificates\".\n\nFor each certificate with \"US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA \u2026\" under \"Issued By\":\nRight click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\nSelect the \"Details\" Tab.\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificate below is not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\nDoD Root CA 2 - US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 1 - DA36FAF56B2F6FBA1604F5BE46D864C9FA013BA3","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DoD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DoD Root CAs, the US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"8812","uuid":"57174751-7bd0-4ccc-ac65-5ff741eb6da1","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1BDDF4C2A02B616E2B25E335978448C29416C164\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-42420","group_tree":[{"id":"V-42420","title":"WINFW-000001","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-42420","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINFW-000001","rule_id_src":"SV-55080r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-55080","rule_version":"WINFW-000001","rule_title":"A host-based firewall must be installed and enabled on the system.","fix_text":"Install and enable a host-based firewall on the system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if a host-based firewall is installed and enabled on the system.  If a host-based firewall is not installed and enabled on the system, this is a finding.\n\nThe configuration requirements will be determined by the applicable firewall STIG.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack, allowing or blocking inbound and outbound connections based on a set of rules.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3873","uuid":"6a18f900-2cb0-41c8-80de-01980b2ccbde","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 78A508F1250724230B380BAA6847761B058690BC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'A host-based firewall must be installed and enabled on the system.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-56421","group_tree":[{"id":"V-56421","title":"WINCC-000147","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-56421","severity":"low","group_title":"WINCC-000147","rule_id_src":"SV-70677r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-70677","rule_version":"WINCC-000147","rule_title":"The touch keyboard or input panel must not highlight keys as passwords are entered.","fix_text":"If the system does not have a touch screen, this is NA.\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Tablet PC -> Input Panel -> \"Turn off password security in Input Panel\" to at least \"Enabled: Medium High\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system does not have a touch screen, this is NA.\nIf the system has a touch screen and the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\TabletTip\\1.7\\\n\nValue Name:  PasswordSecurityState\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1\n\nValue Name:  PasswordSecurity\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  4 or 5 \n(1, 2, or 3 are a finding)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The touch keyboard or input panel may highlight keys as passwords are entered, providing visibility to nearby persons, and compromising them.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000206"],"reference_identifier":"4096","uuid":"6c8bacde-9c58-4a33-be7b-f168e9485f72","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 02F063C19D475C265E47C7BF0A145BAABB763083\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The touch keyboard or input panel must not highlight keys as passwords are entered.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-57637","group_tree":[{"id":"V-57637","title":"WIN00-000018","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-57637","severity":"medium","group_title":"WIN00-000018","rule_id_src":"SV-75119r3_rule","rule_id":"SV-75119","rule_version":"WIN00-000018","rule_title":"The operating system must employ a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs.","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nConfigure an application whitelisting program to employ a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs.\n\nConfiguration of whitelisting applications will vary by the program.  AppLocker is a whitelisting application built into Windows 7 Enterprise.\n\nIf AppLocker is used, it is configured through group policy in Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Application Control Policies >> AppLocker.\n\nImplementation guidance for AppLocker is available in the NSA paper \"Application Whitelisting using Microsoft AppLocker\" under the Microsoft Windows section of the following link:\n\nhttps://www.nsa.gov/ia/mitigation_guidance/security_configuration_guides/operating_systems.shtml","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nVerify the operating system employs a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs.\n\nIf an application whitelisting program is not in use on the system, this is a finding.\n\nConfiguration of whitelisting applications will vary by the program.\n\nAppLocker is a whitelisting application built into Windows 7 Enterprise.  A deny-by-default implementation is initiated by enabling any AppLocker rules within a category, only allowing what is specified by defined rules.\n\nIf AppLocker is used, perform the following to view the configuration of AppLocker:\nOpen PowerShell.\n\nIf the AppLocker PowerShell module has not been previously imported, execute the following first:\nImport-Module AppLocker\n\nExecute the following command, substituting [c:\\temp\\file.xml] with a location and file name appropriate for the system:\nGet-AppLockerPolicy -Effective -XML > c:\\temp\\file.xml\n\nThis will produce an xml file with the effective settings that can be viewed in a browser or opened in a program such as Excel for review.\n\nImplementation guidance for AppLocker is available in the NSA paper \"Application Whitelisting using Microsoft AppLocker\" under the Microsoft Windows section of the following link:\n\nhttps://www.nsa.gov/ia/mitigation_guidance/security_configuration_guides/operating_systems.shtml","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Utilizing a whitelist provides a configuration management method for allowing the execution of only authorized software. Using only authorized software decreases risk by limiting the number of potential vulnerabilities.\n\nThe organization must identify authorized software programs and only permit execution of authorized software. The process used to identify software programs that are authorized to execute on organizational information systems is commonly referred to as whitelisting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001774"],"reference_identifier":"1580","uuid":"233304ce-0776-4242-b71c-adf14392031a","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E5740BF4D1B142C66FDAA4817DBC89B31D7B1B77\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The operating system must employ a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-68843","group_tree":[{"id":"V-68843","title":"WIN00-000145","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-68843","severity":"high","group_title":"WIN00-000145","rule_id_src":"SV-83437r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-83437","rule_version":"WIN00-000145","rule_title":"Data Execution Prevention (DEP) must be configured to at least OptOut.","fix_text":"Configure DEP to at least OptOut.\n\nOpen a command prompt (cmd.exe) or PowerShell with elevated privileges (Run as administrator).\nEnter \"BCDEDIT /set {current} nx OptOut\".  (If using PowerShell \"{current}\" must be enclosed in quotes.)\n\"AlwaysOn\", a more restrictive selection, is also valid but does not allow applications that do not function properly to be opted out of DEP.\n\nNote: Suspend BitLocker before making changes to the DEP configuration.\n\nOpted out exceptions can be configured in the \"System Properties\".\n\nOpen \"System\" in Control Panel.\nSelect \"Advanced system settings\".\nClick \"Settings\" in the \"Performance\" section.\nSelect the \"Data Execution Prevention\" tab.\nApplications that are opted out are configured in the window below the selection \"Turn on DEP for all programs and services except those I select:\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If DEP is configured through the Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) (V-36705), this is NA.\n\nVerify the DEP configuration.\nOpen a command prompt (cmd.exe) or PowerShell with elevated privileges (Run as administrator).\nEnter \"BCDEdit /enum {current}\". (If using PowerShell \"{current}\" must be enclosed in quotes.)\nIf the value for \"nx\" is not \"OptOut\", this is a finding.\n(The more restrictive configuration of \"AlwaysOn\" would not be a finding.)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attackers are constantly looking for vulnerabilities in systems and applications. Data Execution Prevention (DEP) prevents harmful code from running in protected memory locations reserved for Windows and other programs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"7209","uuid":"c3a2c007-ec07-4897-935d-da0c84bbbf59","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4A3C40535D06900F626882A3669CABCDDF0DF634\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Data Execution Prevention (DEP) must be configured to at least OptOut.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-68847","group_tree":[{"id":"V-68847","title":"WIN00-000150","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-68847","severity":"high","group_title":"WIN00-000150","rule_id_src":"SV-83443r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-83443","rule_version":"WIN00-000150","rule_title":"Structured Exception Handling Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) must be turned on.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\kernel\\\n\nValue Name: DisableExceptionChainValidation\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If SEHOP is configured through the Enhanced Mitigation Experience Toolkit (EMET) (V-36706), this is NA.\n\nVerify SEHOP is turned on.\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\kernel\\\n\nValue Name: DisableExceptionChainValidation\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attackers are constantly looking for vulnerabilities in systems and applications. Structured Exception Handling Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) blocks exploits that use the Structured Exception Handling overwrite technique, a common buffer overflow attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"9394","uuid":"8cc9014b-3ce0-4a96-bedc-1ccd0fce602a","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8B8DD06A2ED278E202E52D8DA69F668BB442A53C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Structured Exception Handling Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) must be turned on.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-72573","group_tree":[{"id":"V-72573","title":"WIN00-000200","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-72573","severity":"medium","group_title":"WIN00-000200","rule_id_src":"SV-87203r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-87203","rule_version":"WIN00-000200","rule_title":"Wireless network adapters must be turned off when the system is connected to a wired network.","fix_text":"Configure systems to turn off wireless network adapters when systems are connected to wired networks.  If this is not possible, develop and implement a policy that users must turn off wireless network adapters when systems are connected to wired networks.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA for systems that do not have wireless network adapters.\n\nDisabling of wired network adapters can be accomplished through various means.  Third-party software that manages this is the most reliable solution.  Some network adapters may have a configuration option to address this locally.  At minimum, the organization must have a policy that users turn off wireless network adapters when connected to a wired network.\n\nIf wireless network adapters are not turned off when the system is connected to a wired network, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If a client device supports simultaneous use of wireless and wired connections, then this increases the probability that an adversary who can access the device using its wireless interface can then route traffic through the device\u2019s wired interface to attack devices on the wired network or obtain sensitive DoD information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8854","uuid":"b8e115e3-e5d8-43c1-92ca-4273fba497ec","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 63DCBBE11694B294D203AE1018D473578EED6A6F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Wireless network adapters must be turned off when the system is connected to a wired network.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-72753","group_tree":[{"id":"V-72753","title":"WINCC-000150","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-72753","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINCC-000150","rule_id_src":"SV-87385r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-87385","rule_version":"WINCC-000150","rule_title":"WDigest Authentication must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"WDigest Authentication (disabling may require KB2871997)\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nNote: Microsoft Security Advisory update 2871997 is required for this setting to be effective on Windows 7.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\Wdigest\\\n\nValue Name: UseLogonCredential\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)\n\nNote: Microsoft Security Advisory update 2871997 is required for this setting to be effective on Windows 7.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When the WDigest Authentication protocol is enabled, plain text passwords are stored in the Local Security Authority Subsystem Service (LSASS) exposing them to theft.  This setting will prevent WDigest from storing credentials in memory.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5543","uuid":"e9cc7738-d950-4994-9038-76b796218a19","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 17566456B601A58F38E1631E5F8EF46F33DA8EC4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'WDigest Authentication must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-73519","group_tree":[{"id":"V-73519","title":"WIN00-000170","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-73519","severity":"medium","group_title":"WIN00-000170","rule_id_src":"SV-88171r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-88171","rule_version":"WIN00-000170","rule_title":"The Server Message Block (SMB) v1 protocol must be disabled on the SMB server.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"Configure SMBv1 Server\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nThe system must be restarted for the change to take effect.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SMB1\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"SMBv1 is a legacy protocol that uses the MD5 algorithm as part of SMB. MD5 is known to be vulnerable to a number of attacks such as collision and preimage attacks as well as not being FIPS compliant.\n\nDisabling SMBv1 support may prevent access to file or print sharing resources with systems or devices that only support SMBv1. File shares and print services hosted on Windows Server 2003 are an example, however Windows Server 2003 is no longer a supported operating system. Some older network attached devices may only support SMBv1.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9903","uuid":"810eb3d7-b162-4bbf-bff8-16ce9ff0abad","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-73523","group_tree":[{"id":"V-73523","title":"WIN00-000180","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-73523","severity":"medium","group_title":"WIN00-000180","rule_id_src":"SV-88175r2_rule","rule_id":"SV-88175","rule_version":"WIN00-000180","rule_title":"The Server Message Block (SMB) v1 protocol must be disabled on the SMB client.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"Configure SMBv1 client driver\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Disable driver (recommended)\" selected for \"Configure MrxSmb10 driver\".\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"Configure SMBv1 client (extra setting needed for pre-Win8.1/2012R2)\" to \"Enabled\" with the following three lines of text entered for \"Configure LanmanWorkstation Dependencies\":\nBowser\nMRxSmb20\nNSI\n\nThe system must be restarted for the changes to take effect.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\mrxsmb10\\\n\nValue Name: Start\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000004 (4)\n\nIf the following registry value includes MRxSmb10, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\\n\nValue Name: DependOnService\n\nType: REG_MULTI_SZ\nValue: Default values after removing MRxSmb10 include the following, which are not a finding:\nBowser\nMRxSmb20\nNSI","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"SMBv1 is a legacy protocol that uses the MD5 algorithm as part of SMB. MD5 is known to be vulnerable to a number of attacks such as collision and preimage attacks as well as not being FIPS compliant.\n\nDisabling SMBv1 support may prevent access to file or print sharing resources with systems or devices that only support SMBv1. File shares and print services hosted on Windows Server 2003 are an example, however Windows Server 2003 is no longer a supported operating system. Some older network attached devices may only support SMBv1.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9657","uuid":"71c0dc42-8063-4a77-b3d0-b1a6b024354a","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C4DDA580D76C393DA3578312F499596C15686CEA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Server Message Block (SMB) v1 protocol must be disabled on the SMB client.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-75915","group_tree":[{"id":"V-75915","title":"WIN00-000190","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-75915","severity":"medium","group_title":"WIN00-000190","rule_id_src":"SV-90595r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-90595","rule_version":"WIN00-000190","rule_title":"Orphaned security identifiers (SIDs) must be removed from user rights on Windows 7.","fix_text":"Remove any unresolved SIDs found in User Rights assignments and determined to not be for currently valid accounts or groups by removing the accounts or groups from the appropriate group policy.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Review the effective User Rights setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nReview each User Right listed for any unresolved SIDs to determine whether they are valid, such as due to being temporarily disconnected from the domain. (Unresolved SIDs have the format of \"*S-1-\u2026\".)\n\nIf any unresolved SIDs exist and are not for currently valid accounts or groups, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Accounts or groups given rights on a system may show up as unresolved SIDs for various reasons including deletion of the accounts or groups.  If the account or group objects are reanimated, there is a potential they may still have rights no longer intended.  Valid domain accounts or groups may also show up as unresolved SIDs if a connection to the domain cannot be established for some reason.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5795","uuid":"ff5c5041-c111-48f2-a5bd-e9c50a821933","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 591B770082CB1427F87E3BE64F9691011739A1B6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Orphaned security identifiers (SIDs) must be removed from user rights on Windows 7.' matches the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-102613","group_tree":[{"id":"V-102613","title":"WINCC-000030","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-102613","severity":"medium","group_title":"WINCC-000030","rule_id_src":"SV-111559r1_rule","rule_id":"SV-111559","rule_version":"WINCC-000030","rule_title":"The Windows Explorer Preview pane must be disabled for Windows 7.","fix_text":"Ensure the following settings are configured for Windows 7 locally or applied through group policy. \n\nConfigure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Explorer >> Explorer Frame Pane \"Turn off Preview Pane\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nConfigure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components Windows Explorer >> Explorer Frame Pane \"Turn on or off details pane\" to \"Enabled\" and \"Configure details pane\" to \"Always hide\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\n\nValue Name: NoPreviewPane\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\n\nValue: 1\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\n\nValue Name: NoReadingPane\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\n\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"DPMS_XCCDF_Benchmark_Windows_7_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A known vulnerability in Windows could allow the execution of malicious code by either opening a compromised document or viewing it in the Windows Preview pane.\n\nOrganizations must disable the Windows Preview pane and Windows Detail pane.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3623","uuid":"e5840273-8cf9-4311-8cab-ee1e4cbc5fec","stig_uuid":"c72758fa-0fec-48d0-b90f-cf02bbeace21","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows7_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C5F7C00276CEFD14AA786062E35D16357F116772\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows Explorer Preview pane must be disabled for Windows 7.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 7 workstation."}]},{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-23T17:12:42.0000000+00:00","module":{"name":"Scan-IE11_Checks","version":"1.2604.2"}},"stig_name":"Microsoft Internet Explorer 11 Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Microsoft Internet Explorer 11","stig_id":"IE_11_STIG","release_info":"Release: 7 Benchmark Date: 01 Apr 2026","version":"2","uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","reference_identifier":"5696","size":137,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-223015","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223015","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223015","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223015r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223015","rule_version":"DTBI015-IE11","rule_title":"The Internet Explorer warning about certificate address mismatch must be enforced.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page 'Turn on certificate address mismatch warning' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page 'Turn on certificate address mismatch warning' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"WarnOnBadCertRecving\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This parameter warns users if the certificate being presented by the website is invalid. Since server certificates are used to validate the identity of the web server it is critical to warn the user of a potential issue with the certificate being presented by the web server. This setting aids to prevent spoofing attacks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59339","V-46475","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6065","uuid":"64b2d6c8-b777-491d-9790-5e0fe001f837","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F2D852FBE80143BC98DE465A7AB0DB8EDA454129\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Internet Explorer warning about certificate address mismatch must be enforced.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223016","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223016","title":"SRG-APP-000175","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223016","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","rule_id_src":"SV-223016r961038_rule","rule_id":"SV-223016","rule_version":"DTBI018-IE11","rule_title":"Check for publishers certificate revocation must be enforced.","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nOpen Internet Explorer.\nFrom the menu bar, select \"Tools\".\nFrom the \"Tools\" drop-down menu, select \"Internet Options\". From the \"Internet Options\" window, select the \"Advanced\" tab from the \"Advanced\" tab window, scroll down to the \"Security\" category, and select the \"Check for publisher's certificate revocation\" box.\n\nNote: Manual entry in the registry key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Current Version\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing for the value \"State\", set to \"REG_DWORD = 23C00\", may first be required.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nOpen Internet Explorer.\nFrom the menu bar, select \"Tools\".\nFrom the \"Tools\" drop-down menu, select \"Internet Options\". From the \"Internet Options\" window, select the \"Advanced\" tab, from the \"Advanced\" tab window, scroll down to the \"Security\" category, and verify the \"Check for publisher's certificate revocation\" box is selected.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n HKCU\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing Criteria\n\nIf the value \"State\" is \"REG_DWORD = 23C00\", this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Check for publisher's certificate revocation options should be enforced to ensure all PKI signed objects are validated.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000605","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59341","V-46477","CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"5435","uuid":"c9873fb3-0abf-4c17-8572-214d5832a792","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B4A68FA1E910419173E9138F1DC8272EAF4874D8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Check for publishers certificate revocation must be enforced.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223017","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223017","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223017","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","rule_id_src":"SV-223017r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223017","rule_version":"DTBI022-IE11","rule_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Download signed ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Download signed ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Active X controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. Signed code is better than unsigned code in that it may be easier to determine its author, but it is still potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. This policy setting allows you to manage whether users may download signed ActiveX controls from a page in the zone. If you enable this policy, users can download signed controls without user intervention. If you select Prompt in the drop-down box, users are queried whether to download controls signed by untrusted publishers. Code signed by trusted publishers is silently downloaded. If you disable the policy setting, signed controls cannot be downloaded.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59345","V-46481","CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"4053","uuid":"b721b2cb-01be-43ec-a259-f50d5c1cc417","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8FFC2FB2A5D2B90C9BF983832F718EA549D91196\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Internet zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223018","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223018","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223018","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","rule_id_src":"SV-223018r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223018","rule_version":"DTBI023-IE11","rule_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unsigned code is potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. This policy setting allows you to manage whether users may download unsigned ActiveX controls from the zone. If you enable this policy setting, users can run unsigned controls without user intervention. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are queried to choose whether to allow the unsigned control to run. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot run unsigned controls. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot run unsigned controls.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59347","V-46483","CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"3956","uuid":"364d1e40-8cf5-4884-8e4e-80ebd5471bc8","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7B7D73FDF181D723592AFA3E00CD24C6F79661C4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223019","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223019","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223019","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223019r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223019","rule_version":"DTBI024-IE11","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59365","V-46501","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4814","uuid":"9bd506eb-5443-4794-834c-231423d02749","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CADCE27B33B705EA22B35BF44EAA4E7816E7A48C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223020","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223020","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223020","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223020r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223020","rule_version":"DTBI031-IE11","rule_title":"The Java permissions must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59371","V-46507","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1046","uuid":"97058862-263f-457d-986f-73f7999efdc9","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223021","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223021","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223021","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","rule_id_src":"SV-223021r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223021","rule_version":"DTBI032-IE11","rule_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Access data sources across domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Access data sources across domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1406\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The ability to access data zones across domains could cause the user to unknowingly access content hosted on an unauthorized server. Access to data sources across multiple domains must be controlled based upon the site being browsed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer can access data from another security zone using the Microsoft XML Parser (MSXML) or ActiveX Data Objects (ADO).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59373","V-46509","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"9882","uuid":"dd1f345d-2774-456f-b45d-25c51aaa8e46","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4A446579EE9FC13371791462FD98C9CE6880E8A2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223022","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223022","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223022","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223022r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223022","rule_version":"DTBI036-IE11","rule_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value for \"1802\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Content hosted on sites located in the Internet zone are likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore this feature should be blocked for this zone. Drag and drop or copy and paste files must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59375","V-46511","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6925","uuid":"097fd42f-0173-4a34-b836-052413df163c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6B3DFDA6F6DA61989F73940A5EDF1AD04E4A2596\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223023","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223023","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223023","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223023r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223023","rule_version":"DTBI038-IE11","rule_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1804\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applications may be run and files may be downloaded from an IFRAME reference in the HTML of the pages in this zone. Launching of programs in IFRAME must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. If you enable this policy setting, applications can run and files can be downloaded from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone without user intervention. If you disable this setting, users are prevented from running applications and downloading files from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59377","V-46513","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9372","uuid":"45a9fb38-efe6-4726-8525-6ebc8110ee9a","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7CE5BB313C6B29AF15107E74B78819E9DF45F8D0\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Internet zone).' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223024","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223024","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223024","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","rule_id_src":"SV-223024r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223024","rule_version":"DTBI039-IE11","rule_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\InternetSettings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1607\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Frames that navigate across different domains are a security concern, because the user may think they are accessing pages on one site while they are actually accessing pages on another site. It is possible that a website hosting malicious content could use this feature in a manner similar to cross-site scripting (XSS). This policy setting allows you to manage the opening of sub-frames and access of applications across different domains.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59379","V-46515","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"8712","uuid":"371df427-2fe2-4c5b-9705-50108d0ebf4c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F6594363583C6551E789DC7B086CB2F265EFBA74\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223025","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223025","title":"SRG-APP-000231","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223025","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","rule_id_src":"SV-223025r961128_rule","rule_id":"SV-223025","rule_version":"DTBI042-IE11","rule_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Userdata persistence' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Userdata persistence' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1606\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Userdata persistence must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. It is possible for sites hosting malicious content to exploit this feature as part of an attack against visitors browsing the site. This policy setting allows you to manage the preservation of information in the browser's history, in Favorites, in an XML store, or directly within a web page saved to disk. When a user returns to a persisted page, the state of the page can be restored if this policy setting is not appropriately configured.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59381","V-46517","CCI-001199"],"reference_identifier":"4223","uuid":"421398e3-ea30-4489-803d-d630349498a0","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FEB62FD747ADC50E31A6FBCD4EC3713B02B098D1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223026","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223026","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223026","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223026r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223026","rule_version":"DTBI044-IE11","rule_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1407\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A malicious script could use the clipboard in an undesirable manner, for example, if the user had recently copied confidential information to the clipboard while editing a document, a malicious script could harvest that information. It might be possible to exploit other vulnerabilities in order to send the harvested data to the attacker. Allow paste operations via script must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59385","V-46521","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1069","uuid":"072c7e66-bb4e-4e92-9649-b0bf8747682c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4391896C244DC6AC6CC951EC746CD630E198CE05\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223027","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223027","title":"SRG-APP-000219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223027","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","rule_id_src":"SV-223027r1043178_rule","rule_id":"SV-223027","rule_version":"DTBI046-IE11","rule_title":"Logon options must be configured to prompt (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Logon options' to 'Enabled', and select 'Prompt for user name and password' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Logon options' must be 'Enabled', and 'Prompt for user name and password' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1A00\" is REG_DWORD = 65536 (decimal), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users could submit credentials to servers operated by malicious individuals who could then attempt to connect to legitimate servers with those captured credentials. Care must be taken with user credentials, automatic logon performance, and how default Windows credentials are passed to the websites. This policy setting allows management of settings for logon options. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from varying logon options. \u201cAnonymous logon\u201d disables HTTP authentication and uses the guest account only for the Common Internet File System (CIFS) protocol. \u201cPrompt for user name and password\u201d queries users for user IDs and passwords. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. \u201cAutomatic logon only in Intranet zone\u201d queries users for user IDs and passwords in other zones. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. \u201cAutomatic logon with current user name and password\u201d attempts logon using Windows NT Challenge Response. If Windows NT Challenge Response is supported by the server, the logon uses the user's network user name and password for login. If Windows NT Challenge Response is not supported by the server, the user is queried to provide the user name and password. If you disable this policy setting, logon is set to \u201cAutomatic logon only in Intranet zone\u201d. If you do not configure this policy setting, logon is set to \u201cAutomatic logon only in Intranet zone\u201d. The most secure option is to configure this setting to \u201cEnabled\u201d; \u201cAnonymous logon\u201d, but configuring this setting to \u201cEnabled\u201d; \u201cPrompt for user name and password\u201d, provides a reasonable balance between security and usability.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59387","V-46523","CCI-001184"],"reference_identifier":"8319","uuid":"b73b0471-d9f9-4ed2-9ce5-07696a3b1d5b","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A717865D47E88BAFD41A4F4844BD5AD40A4AD256\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Logon options must be configured to prompt (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223028","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223028","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223028","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223028r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223028","rule_version":"DTBI061-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be configured with High Safety (Intranet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Intranet Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'High Safety' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Intranet Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'High Safety' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 65536, (Decimal), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59389","V-46525","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9450","uuid":"4a951f27-5ea4-4481-aae0-f28f1dee2a1b","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 485E5990B49011F12C35FB10BBC166B64C62CAFC\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Java permissions must be configured with High Safety (Intranet zone).' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223029","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223029","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223029","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223029r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223029","rule_version":"DTBI062-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Intranet zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Intranet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Intranet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59865","V-46999","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"5128","uuid":"8d6a658b-afdd-4c63-a114-734db8a6a0d5","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7124A03883D71C75D1A8E0A28ED3B9CB8B547695\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Intranet zone.' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223030","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223030","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223030","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223030r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223030","rule_version":"DTBI091-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be configured with High Safety (Trusted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Trusted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'High Safety' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Trusted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'High Safety' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 65536, (Decimal), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59407","V-46543","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3793","uuid":"a2ef6f33-919e-4add-ba30-bcf82c7a66a2","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 841C293EF5002CB543119D9B469554E76AF88F49\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Java permissions must be configured with High Safety (Trusted Sites zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223031","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223031","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223031","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223031r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223031","rule_version":"DTBI092-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Trusted Sites zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Trusted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Trusted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59875","V-47009","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"7029","uuid":"858fa962-0a2d-412f-8e4d-e7a47f90c571","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F344E08C8E7B44C95455EBCB24DD7C47B204E769\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Trusted Sites zone.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223032","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223032","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223032","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","rule_id_src":"SV-223032r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223032","rule_version":"DTBI1000-IE11","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains within a window must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2708\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59409","V-46545","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"9937","uuid":"3aea05a5-0fca-452b-be1e-4a79c9fabad1","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 128457622016CE361B62987ADA71C6387C840E92\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Dragging of content from different domains within a window must be disallowed (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223033","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223033","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223033","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","rule_id_src":"SV-223033r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223033","rule_version":"DTBI1005-IE11","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2709\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you enable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when both the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59411","V-46547","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"8426","uuid":"afb1cad1-1e88-43bc-a37e-b881220ba228","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 07D756D885D620C7945DE9AA2D8ABAFFD0123646\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223034","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223034","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223034","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","rule_id_src":"SV-223034r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223034","rule_version":"DTBI1010-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict ActiveX Install -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict ActiveX Install -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59413","V-46549","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"6647","uuid":"22c3c78b-c1c6-4a25-9c16-4a66c4c8d1b5","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223035","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223035","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223035","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","rule_id_src":"SV-223035r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223035","rule_version":"DTBI1020-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict ActiveX Install -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict ActiveX Install -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59417","V-46553","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"6551","uuid":"6a0471aa-2072-4b3a-baab-4c6e4e0524b6","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 181F24DCB062192BB0B726F9C00C810AAA90C69B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (iexplore).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223036","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223036","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223036","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","rule_id_src":"SV-223036r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223036","rule_version":"DTBI1025-IE11","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains within a window must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2708\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59419","V-46555","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"3513","uuid":"87524157-efcd-4ac7-9f4f-e0cd6e91797b","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BEF2C565BF0F0EBC38644EAE82C6569BBAA72CB1\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Dragging of content from different domains within a window must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223037","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223037","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223037","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223037r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223037","rule_version":"DTBI1046-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Internet zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59863","V-46997","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"7984","uuid":"d4fcb4b0-19d8-44e8-80d3-2f22892553ed","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FB2E9E482FA3FC5F57626D530A39A7843C2EB551\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Internet zone.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223038","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223038","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223038","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223038r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223038","rule_version":"DTBI1051-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Restricted Sites zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59871","V-47005","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"3195","uuid":"d6c2f137-96f7-4926-9235-684894014c85","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E0E360816D1475F6EE93ED42DF50C866AA3AAB4E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Restricted Sites zone.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223039","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223039","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223039","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-223039r961194_rule","rule_id":"SV-223039","rule_version":"DTBI1060-IE11","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings must be enabled.","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> \u201dPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings\u201d to \u201dEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> \u201dPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings\u201d must be \u201dEnabled\u201d. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverride\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter prevents the user from browsing to or downloading from sites that are known to host malicious content. SmartScreen Filter also prevents the execution of files that are known to be malicious. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-79201","V-64711","CCI-001242"],"reference_identifier":"1709","uuid":"e55ae7ed-57fb-4788-93f9-3c22b6edfafd","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A8625212D7B5116068649DE6B458BD98E895C418\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223040","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223040","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223040","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","rule_id_src":"SV-223040r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223040","rule_version":"DTBI1065-IE11","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet must be enabled.","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> \u201dPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet\u201d to \u201dEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> \u201dPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet\u201d must be \u201dEnabled\u201d. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter.\n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter warns the user about executable files that Internet Explorer users do not commonly download from the internet. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-79203","V-64713","CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"9929","uuid":"b430d0b0-854b-4f19-8ef6-81432b24dc45","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C1DE6DED22BBE5BFDC1A2335C65AE99AFC8D5EF2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet must be enabled.' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223041","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223041","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223041","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223041r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223041","rule_version":"DTBI1070-IE11","rule_title":"Prevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> \u201dPrevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls\u201d to \u201dEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> \u201dPrevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls\u201d must be \u201dEnabled\u201d. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to prevent the installation of ActiveX controls on a per-user basis. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls cannot be installed on a per-user basis. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, ActiveX controls can be installed on a per-user basis.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-79205","V-64715","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"6135","uuid":"0caf4dfe-fb98-4472-aa1a-bea4b730d21d","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6A75454B6ECF995DD11357D9AE64ED28BFC4677C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Prevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223042","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223042","title":"SRG-APP-000427","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223042","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000427","rule_id_src":"SV-223042r961596_rule","rule_id":"SV-223042","rule_version":"DTBI1075-IE11","rule_title":"Prevent ignoring certificate errors option must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> \u201dPrevent ignoring certificate errors\u201d to \u201dEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> \u201dPrevent ignoring certificate errors\u201d must be \u201dEnabled\u201d. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventIgnoreCertErrors\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting prevents the user from ignoring Secure Sockets Layer/Transport Layer Security (SSL/TLS) certificate errors that interrupt browsing (such as \u201cexpired\u201d, \u201crevoked\u201d, or \u201cname mismatch\u201d errors) in Internet Explorer. If you enable this policy setting, the user cannot continue browsing. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose to ignore certificate errors and continue browsing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-79207","V-64717","CCI-001954"],"reference_identifier":"3773","uuid":"e267fc3a-6379-49ab-ba09-1356be324221","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3E0DADEE7F3625819D7CB1C2089E31283E921BA7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Prevent ignoring certificate errors option must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223043","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223043","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223043","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-223043r961194_rule","rule_id":"SV-223043","rule_version":"DTBI1080-IE11","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Internet Zone must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Internet Zone >> \u201dTurn on SmartScreen Filter scan\u201d to \u201dEnabled\u201d, and select \u201dEnable\u201d from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Internet Zone >> \u201dTurn on SmartScreen Filter scan\u201d must be \u201dEnabled\u201d and \u201dEnable\u201d selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-79209","V-64719","CCI-001242"],"reference_identifier":"2253","uuid":"1236cfbc-dc03-45f2-abb0-e14d2d0beb45","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0FB110B4C5D1DBCDF027CFB0F4B1DF209FFFD75F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Internet Zone must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223044","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223044","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223044","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-223044r961194_rule","rule_id":"SV-223044","rule_version":"DTBI1085-IE11","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Restricted Sites Zone must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Restricted Sites Zone >> \u201dTurn on SmartScreen Filter scan\u201d to \u201dEnabled\u201d, and select \u201dEnable\u201d from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Restricted Sites Zone >> \u201dTurn on SmartScreen Filter scan\u201d must be \u201dEnabled\u201d and \u201dEnable\u201d selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-79211","V-64721","CCI-001242"],"reference_identifier":"8355","uuid":"1b541099-d1f2-40c1-b640-be9066f8427f","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223045","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223045","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223045","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223045r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223045","rule_version":"DTBI1090-IE11","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Intranet Zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Intranet Zone >> \u201dInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe\u201d to \u201dEnabled\u201d, and select \u201dDisable\u201d from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Intranet Zone >> \u201dInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe\u201d must be \u201dEnabled\u201d and \u201dDisable\u201d selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-79213","V-64723","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"5265","uuid":"aa098b62-6d07-4981-bdef-b1fc0fc8800a","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E825F6DBC0E9FF93D36CD280CA419C5589852593\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Intranet Zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223046","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223046","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223046","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223046r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223046","rule_version":"DTBI1095-IE11","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Trusted Sites Zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Trusted Sites Zone >> \u201dInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe\u201d to \u201dEnabled\u201d, and select \u201dDisable\u201d from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Trusted Sites Zone >> \u201dInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe\u201d must be \u201dEnabled\u201d and \u201dDisable\u201d selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-79215","V-64725","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"1949","uuid":"28f168a8-69f8-4c89-8ba7-83e8769c7b70","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 685B631DA23A297372A2BCC10C283B0C21F3573E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Trusted Sites Zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223048","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223048","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223048","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223048r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223048","rule_version":"DTBI1105-IE11","rule_title":"Run once selection for running outdated ActiveX controls must be disabled.","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Security Features >> Add-on Management, set \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Security Features >> Add-on Management, verify \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" is set to \u201cEnabled\u201d. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"RunThisTimeEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-87395","V-72757","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9544","uuid":"782256c0-d270-45e3-a95b-3c05fbab6b72","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5FB8C491F3962ECC5AC21098EFB8583A728985F9\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Run once selection for running outdated ActiveX controls must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223049","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223049","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223049","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223049r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223049","rule_version":"DTBI1110-IE11","rule_title":"Enabling outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer must be blocked.","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Security Features >> Add-on Management, set \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Security Features >> Add-on Management, verify \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" is set to \u201cDisabled\u201d. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"VersionCheckEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-87397","V-72759","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4034","uuid":"2d903489-5afd-46e6-a9db-3f71a68c9533","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 53DA26DE908C00C7FDF45B8D5720F30EBCEBF250\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Enabling outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223050","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223050","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223050","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223050r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223050","rule_version":"DTBI1115-IE11","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Internet Zone.","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Pane >> Security Page >> Internet Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to \u201cEnabled\u201d. \n\nIn the Options window, select \"Enable\" from the \u201cOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Internet Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is \u201cEnabled\u201d. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the \u201cOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to \u201cEnable\u201d. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = \u201c3\u201d, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users will not be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-87399","V-72761","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7568","uuid":"fdbadd12-dfe7-4748-940f-f543ad69f3f7","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223051","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223051","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223051","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","rule_id_src":"SV-223051r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223051","rule_version":"DTBI112-IE11","rule_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Download signed ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Download signed ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. Signed code is better than unsigned code in that it may be easier to determine its author, but it is still potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59437","V-46573","CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"4440","uuid":"3d4255d3-9f1a-4684-aa9b-d600d84de698","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 58F0C7060962691EDBCAF86B817AE87DF79F6679\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223052","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223052","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223052","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223052r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223052","rule_version":"DTBI1120-IE11","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Restricted Sites Zone.","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Restricted Sites Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to \u201cEnabled\u201d.\n\nIn the Options windows, select \"Enable\" from the \u201cOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Restricted Sites Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is \u201cEnabled\u201d. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the \u201cOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to \u201cEnable\u201d. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = \u201c3\u201d, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users won\u2019t be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-87401","V-72763","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2065","uuid":"3d0f9479-0f14-4633-a865-563e60b521bd","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 845627BE8B18E006B9B80B58E6C7D5D86BFF2930\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Restricted Sites Zone.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223053","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223053","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223053","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","rule_id_src":"SV-223053r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223053","rule_version":"DTBI1125-IE11","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Internet Zone >> \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Internet Zone >> \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89849","V-75169","CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"4719","uuid":"c8b81ce7-f4a6-4a20-ad5a-6bb1a491a4d5","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EFED6854D5142430E77D91F566662DAECA480750\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223054","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223054","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223054","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","rule_id_src":"SV-223054r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223054","rule_version":"DTBI113-IE11","rule_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unsigned code is potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. They must also be digitally signed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59439","V-46575","CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"7227","uuid":"81322c14-8f5f-418d-9d2e-7c7bf6006f06","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C72D0D8146F9B31E831D228788FBB8EB4ED35350\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223055","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223055","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223055","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","rule_id_src":"SV-223055r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223055","rule_version":"DTBI1130-IE11","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Restricted Sites Zone >> \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Restricted Sites Zone >> \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89851","V-75171","CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"1680","uuid":"6f4727c3-155f-4d82-8d99-aa310fe3b808","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 29798B547419BC5347CCB56B373319680BBCEE8B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223056","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223056","title":"SRG-APP-000266","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223056","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266","rule_id_src":"SV-223056r961167_rule","rule_id":"SV-223056","rule_version":"DTBI1135-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Development Tools Must Be Disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Toolbars >> \u201cTurn off Developer Tools\u201d to \u201cEnabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Toolbars >> \u201cTurn off Developer Tools\u201d must be \u201cEnabled\u201d. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKEY_LOCAL_Machine\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\IEDevTools\nCriteria: If the value \"Disabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc. may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-106631","V-97527","CCI-001312"],"reference_identifier":"9013","uuid":"995402b9-73f8-4366-9732-c8f0b3cf9aec","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 99DF9BEE9F407ECA604102630B1E55E3069C8268\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Development Tools Must Be Disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223057","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223057","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223057","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223057r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223057","rule_version":"DTBI114-IE11","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"ActiveX controls not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59441","V-46577","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"2770","uuid":"79571d18-820b-49da-95eb-3cdb7ef4d32a","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 28D8CB911EADEB0347BC0412F2AE1E46B7E3BED4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223058","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223058","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223058","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223058r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223058","rule_version":"DTBI115-IE11","rule_title":"ActiveX controls and plug-ins must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether ActiveX controls and plug-ins can be run on pages from the specified zone. ActiveX controls not marked as safe should not be executed. If you enable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins can run without user intervention. If you disable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins are prevented from running.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59443","V-46579","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1221","uuid":"fa99870e-69c7-4ac8-bb7b-4acbe4016c1c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D24981B15E84E5DE11C1632F4F85B5E51831B1EC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'ActiveX controls and plug-ins must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223059","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223059","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223059","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223059r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223059","rule_version":"DTBI116-IE11","rule_title":"ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1405\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows management of whether ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting can interact with a script. If you enable this policy setting, script interaction can occur automatically without user intervention. ActiveX controls not marked as safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59445","V-46581","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3308","uuid":"3ff72b23-0ec6-40db-b2d9-fe85b0dbfbe0","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A2AFE82AF3AEA1C8B8EB2B1F306656800D2A2C80\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223060","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223060","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223060","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223060r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223060","rule_version":"DTBI119-IE11","rule_title":"File downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1803\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Sites located in the Restricted Sites Zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore downloads from this zone should be blocked. Files should not be able to be downloaded from sites that are considered restricted. This policy setting allows you to manage whether file downloads are permitted from the zone. This option is determined by the zone of the page with the link causing the download, not the zone from which the file is delivered.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59447","V-46583","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1365","uuid":"e31cf3b1-d4ef-4198-a30b-d185daddfbe7","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A03EFE46CAEC3BB36DBEAD4A9F8DC25A1A3E1039\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'File downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223061","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223061","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223061","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223061r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223061","rule_version":"DTBI121-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59451","V-46587","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6027","uuid":"bc2d95cf-0f05-4b57-aab2-1d433e7109fa","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 59334F0411F1B627F689D4F8F7616994FD7542B3\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Java permissions must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223062","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223062","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223062","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","rule_id_src":"SV-223062r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223062","rule_version":"DTBI122-IE11","rule_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Access data sources across domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Access data sources across domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1406\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The ability to access data zones across domains could cause the user to unknowingly access content hosted on an unauthorized server. This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer can access data from another security zone using the Microsoft XML Parser (MSXML) or ActiveX Data Objects (ADO).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59453","V-46589","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"1455","uuid":"d7e17131-2b41-4c48-82b0-638eaa4ff757","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6B5BD7E726918347B988391BF6355527814012C5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223063","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223063","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223063","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223063r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223063","rule_version":"DTBI123-IE11","rule_title":"The Allow META REFRESH property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow META REFRESH' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow META REFRESH' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1608\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is possible that users will unknowingly be redirected to a site hosting malicious content. 'Allow META REFRESH' must have a level of protection based upon the site being browsed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether a user's browser can be redirected to another web page if the author of the web page uses the Meta Refresh setting to redirect browsers to another web page.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59455","V-46591","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7004","uuid":"c5e65ce1-5784-4074-89d6-e9957be5b2b9","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223064","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223064","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223064","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223064r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223064","rule_version":"DTBI126-IE11","rule_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1802\" is REG_DWORD=3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Content hosted on sites located in the Restricted Sites zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore this feature should be blocked for this zone. Drag and drop or copy and paste files must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59457","V-46593","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7582","uuid":"fe4f1027-fee3-491d-b06b-2f2488c4e876","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C5E6037315FFFC708CEBB631511170527F5AD86A\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223065","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223065","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223065","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223065r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223065","rule_version":"DTBI128-IE11","rule_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1804\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applications may be run and files may be downloaded from an IFRAME reference in the HTML of the pages in this zone. Launching of programs in IFRAME must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. If you enable this policy setting, applications can run and files can be downloaded from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone without user intervention. If you disable this setting, users are prevented from running applications and downloading files from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59461","V-46597","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2198","uuid":"b6717f09-b802-49c7-a535-e8d4d66475d0","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E1335402806D7798CF192C933290CE9124BC3494\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223066","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223066","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223066","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","rule_id_src":"SV-223066r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223066","rule_version":"DTBI129-IE11","rule_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1607\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Frames navigating across different domains are a security concern, because the user may think they are accessing pages on one site while they are actually accessing pages on another site. It is possible that a website hosting malicious content could use this feature in a manner similar to cross-site scripting (XSS). This policy setting allows you to manage the opening of sub-frames and access of applications across different domains.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59463","V-46599","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"8611","uuid":"75439ee4-86d7-4715-b40c-12f74646dd3c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223067","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223067","title":"SRG-APP-000231","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223067","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","rule_id_src":"SV-223067r961128_rule","rule_id":"SV-223067","rule_version":"DTBI132-IE11","rule_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Userdata persistence' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Userdata persistence' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1606\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Userdata persistence must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage the preservation of information in the browser's history, in Favorites, in an XML store, or directly within a web page saved to disk. When a user returns to a persisted page, the state of the page can be restored if this policy setting is not appropriately configured.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59465","V-46601","CCI-001199"],"reference_identifier":"4486","uuid":"a4c8163a-b1d5-4685-93fc-53266f1ebb6c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CED8457C581677DC02B32AB8B19E8FF49A834B2D\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223068","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223068","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223068","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223068r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223068","rule_version":"DTBI133-IE11","rule_title":"Active scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites Zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow active scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow active scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1400\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Active scripts hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. Active scripting must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script code on pages in the zone are run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59467","V-46603","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4243","uuid":"903c8d73-cca3-4d45-a475-6a9fc655f050","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B6EDAA6ED68BABCB54EDE198CC31FEE70DD82BB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Active scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites Zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223069","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223069","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223069","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223069r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223069","rule_version":"DTBI134-IE11","rule_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1407\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A malicious script could use the clipboard in an undesirable manner, for example, if the user had recently copied confidential information to the clipboard while editing a document, a malicious script could harvest that information. It might be possible to exploit other vulnerabilities in order to send the harvested data to the attacker. Allow paste operations via script must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59469","V-46605","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9328","uuid":"63a4072a-4b33-46f1-841d-5b2e736418d4","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B6A44547B17E07B449BEB01F5B18998357C6AC26\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223070","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223070","title":"SRG-APP-000219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223070","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","rule_id_src":"SV-223070r1043178_rule","rule_id":"SV-223070","rule_version":"DTBI136-IE11","rule_title":"Logon options must be configured and enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Logon options' to 'Enabled', and select 'Anonymous logon' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Logon options' must be 'Enabled', and 'Anonymous logon' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1A00\" is REG_DWORD = 196608 (decimal), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users could submit credentials to servers operated by malicious individuals who could then attempt to connect to legitimate servers with those captured credentials. Care must be taken with user credentials, automatic logon performance, and how default Windows credentials are passed to the websites. This policy setting allows management of settings for logon options. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from varying logon options. \u201cAnonymous logon\u201d disables HTTP authentication and uses the guest account only for the Common Internet File System (CIFS) protocol. \u201cPrompt for user name and password\u201d queries users for user IDs and passwords. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. \u201cAutomatic logon only in Intranet zone\u201d queries users for user IDs and passwords in other zones. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. \u201cAutomatic logon with current user name and password\u201d attempts logon using Windows NT Challenge Response. If Windows NT Challenge Response is supported by the server, the logon uses the user's network user name and password for login. If Windows NT Challenge Response is not supported by the server, the user is queried to provide the user name and password. If you disable this policy setting, logon is set to \u201cAutomatic logon only in Intranet zone\u201d. If you do not configure this policy setting, logon is set to \u201cAutomatic logon only in Intranet zone\u201d. The most secure option is to configure this setting to \u201cEnabled\u201d; \u201cAnonymous logon\u201d. This will prevent users from submitting credentials to servers in this security zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59471","V-46607","CCI-001184"],"reference_identifier":"5258","uuid":"e9e8aa46-2eb1-4c03-ad59-3982b329b3f1","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CCA069B97BEEABCAE7D89E6B2A3C4727CD4563E6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Logon options must be configured and enforced (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223071","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223071","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223071","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","rule_id_src":"SV-223071r960879_rule","rule_id":"SV-223071","rule_version":"DTBI300-IE11","rule_title":"Configuring History setting must be set to 40 days.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Delete Browsing History -> 'Disable Configuring History' to 'Enabled', and enter '40' in 'Days to keep pages in History'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Delete Browsing History -> 'Disable Configuring History' must be 'Enabled', and '40' entered in 'Days to keep pages in History'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Control Panel Criteria: If the value \"History\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding. AND  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Url History Criteria: If the value \"DaysToKeep\" is REG_DWORD = 40 (decimal), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting specifies the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The delete Browsing History option can be accessed using Tools, Internet Options, \"General\" tab, and then click Settings under Browsing History. If you enable this policy setting, a user cannot set the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List must be specified. Users will not be able to delete browsing history. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, a user can set the number of days that Internet Explorer tracks views of pages in the History List. Users can delete browsing history.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59473","V-46609","CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"3054","uuid":"b4706273-7148-4630-ab31-55026b12c284","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AF5A6B5890C0E7338E862D7818224A10D2A0F10D\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Configuring History setting must be set to 40 days.' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223072","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223072","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223072","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223072r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223072","rule_version":"DTBI318-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be set to disallow users to add/delete sites.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_zones_map_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting prevents users from adding sites to various security zones. Users should not be able to add sites to different zones, as this could allow them to bypass security controls of the system. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will be able to add or remove sites from the Trusted Sites and Restricted Sites zones at will and change settings in the Local Intranet zone. This configuration could allow sites that host malicious mobile code to be added to these zones, and users could execute the code.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59479","V-46615","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4894","uuid":"f63e59ae-51e9-40fb-bb26-0da8247015f6","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E75D53049048A92CB02E22DC8CF95462CA9B3C54\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer must be set to disallow users to add/delete sites.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223073","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223073","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223073","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223073r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223073","rule_version":"DTBI319-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to disallow users to change policies.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_options_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting prevents users from changing the Internet Explorer policies on the machine. Policy changes should be made by administrators only, so this setting should be enabled. If you enable this policy setting, you disable the \"Custom level\" button and \"Security\" level for this zone slider on the Security tab in the Internet Options dialog box. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users will be able to change the settings for security zones. It prevents users from changing security zone policy settings that are established by the administrator.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59481","V-46617","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7033","uuid":"32f84fa4-9640-4a03-bb98-315cc11dc9fc","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223074","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223074","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223074","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223074r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223074","rule_version":"DTBI320-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to use machine settings.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_HKLM_only\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting enforces consistent security zone settings to all users of the computer. Security zones control browser behavior at various websites and it is desirable to maintain a consistent policy for all users of a machine. This policy setting affects how security zone changes apply to different users. If you enable this policy setting, changes that one user makes to a security zone will apply to all users of that computer. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users of the same computer are allowed to establish their own security zone settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59483","V-46619","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5057","uuid":"e3622e63-3f71-41e8-acfb-109c30718eba","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6CAC2550C0CCF33000B4D69C6F70C89EB83AA7FB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer must be configured to use machine settings.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223075","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223075","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223075","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223075r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223075","rule_version":"DTBI325-IE11","rule_title":"Security checking features must be enforced.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' to 'Disabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security Criteria: If the value \"DisableSecuritySettingsCheck\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting turns off the Security Settings Check feature, which checks Internet Explorer security settings to determine when the settings put Internet Explorer at risk. If you enable this policy setting, the security settings check will not be performed. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the security settings check will be performed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59485","V-46621","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2260","uuid":"ac3460c9-1838-4bf5-8ccc-9baa59bbf7b0","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A423BCB75E7BB216C2A20DA3FD6C6979C3309E4D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Security checking features must be enforced.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223076","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223076","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223076","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223076r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223076","rule_version":"DTBI350-IE11","rule_title":"Software must be disallowed to run or install with invalid signatures.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page -> 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' to 'Disabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: Some legitimate software and controls may have an invalid signature. You should carefully test such software in isolation before it is allowed to be used on an organization's network.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page -> 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"RunInvalidSignatures\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft ActiveX controls and file downloads often have digital signatures attached that certify the file's integrity and the identity of the signer (creator) of the software. Such signatures help ensure unmodified software is downloaded and the user can positively identify the signer to determine whether you trust them enough to run their software.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59489","V-46625","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"7484","uuid":"a52f90e2-ce1c-4348-98b8-1cc972359d5c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D62BC7CDA92322288C648539491261C7096A3A8D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Software must be disallowed to run or install with invalid signatures.' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223077","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223077","title":"SRG-APP-000233","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223077","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","rule_id_src":"SV-223077r961131_rule","rule_id":"SV-223077","rule_version":"DTBI356-IE11","rule_title":"The 64-bit tab processes, when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows, must be turned on.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Isolation64Bit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer 11 uses 64-bit processes (for greater security) or 32-bit processes (for greater compatibility) when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows.Important: Some ActiveX controls and toolbars may not be available when 64-bit processes are used. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 32-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you don't configure this policy setting, users can turn this feature on or off using Internet Explorer settings. This feature is turned off by default.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59861","V-46995","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"2772","uuid":"a9177bff-6e3d-4672-97f9-b8b0d995ba0e","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 741B294C476291BB3E7D3300490F1BF0C4CF417E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The 64-bit tab processes, when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows, must be turned on.' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223078","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223078","title":"SRG-APP-000175","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223078","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","rule_id_src":"SV-223078r961038_rule","rule_id":"SV-223078","rule_version":"DTBI365-IE11","rule_title":"Checking for server certificate revocation must be enforced.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page -> 'Check for server certificate revocation' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page -> 'Check for server certificate revocation' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"CertificateRevocation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer will check revocation status of servers' certificates. Certificates are revoked when they have been compromised or are no longer valid, and this option protects users from submitting confidential data to a site that may be fraudulent or not secure. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check to see if server certificates have been revoked. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000605","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59493","V-46629","CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"2213","uuid":"9cf3abe6-0825-44cc-af6a-f1d6c0c93e53","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 037D73808ADEC23A17FB070B8133359B026D24DE\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Checking for server certificate revocation must be enforced.' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223079","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223079","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223079","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","rule_id_src":"SV-223079r960954_rule","rule_id":"SV-223079","rule_version":"DTBI370-IE11","rule_title":"Checking for signatures on downloaded programs must be enforced.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page -> 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page -> 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"CheckExeSignatures\" is REG_SZ = yes, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer checks for digital signatures (which identifies the publisher of signed software and verifies it has not been modified or tampered with) on user computers before downloading executable programs. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check the digital signatures of executable programs and display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you do not configure this policy, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59497","V-46633","CCI-001749"],"reference_identifier":"4478","uuid":"6dc04589-3fe0-49fc-b07e-23b716b7a190","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BE711C54EAC73293F9D126634BF90082D242357E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Checking for signatures on downloaded programs must be enforced.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223080","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223080","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223080","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223080r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223080","rule_version":"DTBI375-IE11","rule_title":"All network paths (UNCs) for Intranet sites must be disallowed.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' to 'Disabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\ZoneMap Criteria: If the value \"UNCAsIntranet\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some UNC paths could refer to servers not managed by the organization, which means they could host malicious content; and therefore, it is safest to not include all UNC paths in the Intranet Sites zone. This policy setting controls whether URLs representing UNCs are mapped into the local Intranet security zone. If you enable this policy setting, all network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone. If you disable this policy setting, network paths are not necessarily mapped into the Intranet Zone (other rules might map one there). If you do not configure this policy setting, users choose whether network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59499","V-46635","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3400","uuid":"6d2d16d2-258d-4605-9e16-4545cc6c19ea","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223081","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223081","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223081","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223081r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223081","rule_version":"DTBI385-IE11","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59501","V-46637","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1385","uuid":"74a6af2b-979c-4b99-aef7-929b3016213c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D07B37AC8BD0B65DB37983F6B4F66A7B47487C95\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223082","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223082","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223082","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223082r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223082","rule_version":"DTBI390-IE11","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59503","V-46639","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4176","uuid":"5eacf662-375f-4a74-9577-341523eea018","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AD5A435F10756D9247676EE8344E50DA4C8FA3F8\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223083","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223083","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223083","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223083r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223083","rule_version":"DTBI395-IE11","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59505","V-46641","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7431","uuid":"532e2e93-1290-4f80-b7f6-fc5623a8c49e","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4313BFF719E1492B2425087A370FA8A08FBC3086\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Scriptlets must be disallowed (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223084","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223084","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223084","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223084r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223084","rule_version":"DTBI415-IE11","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59507","V-46643","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6889","uuid":"75f797bf-903e-405e-b3f3-caf59dfa91fb","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BD2F5F2FBAEE5BB56301218C8BEA1A4F89821033\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Internet zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223085","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223085","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223085","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223085r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223085","rule_version":"DTBI425-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Local Machine zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Local Machine Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Local Machine Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59509","V-46645","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7573","uuid":"270a2594-af99-4de4-bab8-aa90aaf29132","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B7279539689B08CEF5121B46698651A757938F36\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Java permissions must be disallowed (Local Machine zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223086","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223086","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223086","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223086r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223086","rule_version":"DTBI426-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Local Machine zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page ->Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59869","V-47003","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"7819","uuid":"49a5d3c6-1079-400b-88f7-f65e4ba6661d","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 12FB05E830AE7A90A1F17533E18C0839DF12D652\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Local Machine zone.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223087","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223087","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223087","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223087r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223087","rule_version":"DTBI430-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Local Machine zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59511","V-46647","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5135","uuid":"6d456ceb-3b36-474e-9c03-3cd667592931","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7F19908D11192BF78841F92867CBF02EA12BF9FC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Local Machine zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223088","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223088","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223088","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223088r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223088","rule_version":"DTBI435-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Intranet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Intranet Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Intranet Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\1 Criteria: If the value\" 1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59513","V-46649","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4855","uuid":"6779cb51-1d38-44e8-a27d-35431e131a78","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 354A9CD600A982C39A0A7B0F31E3617AC0A95BE5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Intranet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223089","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223089","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223089","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223089r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223089","rule_version":"DTBI440-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Trusted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\2 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59517","V-46653","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9058","uuid":"7d3a4c76-849e-4f4c-a277-af669b8be91e","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E17F94EC30C5D4A4D646B0EF501B6F8479DA4843\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Trusted Sites zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223090","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223090","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223090","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223090r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223090","rule_version":"DTBI450-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59527","V-46663","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8058","uuid":"5000b8bb-0ed0-4634-8cec-3d0eeed6a5d3","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CCB1FD5A1EBE67D36CD5AB5BAC8BBC158BAA10DC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Restricted Sites zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223091","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223091","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223091","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223091r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223091","rule_version":"DTBI455-IE11","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59529","V-46665","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5557","uuid":"b99a00da-688c-4047-a352-1c0067ef66c4","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FEE3237CD24CCD670F0675F5D5E6823F18162011\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'XAML files must be disallowed (Internet zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223092","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223092","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223092","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223092r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223092","rule_version":"DTBI460-IE11","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59533","V-46669","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2456","uuid":"d416ebfe-9890-4fc9-b949-76516600be03","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 32873AA7D6524694A6D40324487473D23E351CBA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'XAML files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223093","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223093","title":"SRG-APP-000233","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223093","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","rule_id_src":"SV-223093r961131_rule","rule_id":"SV-223093","rule_version":"DTBI485-IE11","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59545","V-46681","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"6313","uuid":"8bf855aa-c736-4641-b02d-a21713554ea6","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C4D5901573DBBB7A1855111B88837A6815D83725\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Protected Mode must be enforced (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223094","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223094","title":"SRG-APP-000233","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223094","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","rule_id_src":"SV-223094r961131_rule","rule_id":"SV-223094","rule_version":"DTBI490-IE11","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled' and select 'Enable', from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59549","V-46685","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"3389","uuid":"da582204-a995-45c0-8fee-806d722b1e20","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A37AEACB33612FB6B7B3A5166A3E0EF4C180B7AF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Protected Mode must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223095","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223095","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223095","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223095r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223095","rule_version":"DTBI495-IE11","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59553","V-46689","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3245","uuid":"15d18fb2-5d7f-40a8-8ecc-2275c2b30987","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223096","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223096","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223096","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223096r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223096","rule_version":"DTBI500-IE11","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59555","V-46691","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1622","uuid":"df9c3cec-f037-4feb-9044-6a3ab8e71fac","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ACAEEBF2A7F46F8FE7B572368A2EE917705DFF35\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223097","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223097","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223097","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","rule_id_src":"SV-223097r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223097","rule_version":"DTBI515-IE11","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Internet zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows a user to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Internet zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If \"Prompt\" is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59557","V-46693","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"6339","uuid":"8de55e73-e367-400d-a576-80c60b588bd7","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C9B9787E7479D16E6940ADC52F4394A957F8186D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Internet zone.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223098","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223098","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223098","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","rule_id_src":"SV-223098r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223098","rule_version":"DTBI520-IE11","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Restricted Sites zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Restricted zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If Prompt is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59559","V-46695","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"9664","uuid":"395b9ed6-9ff7-45f3-9bc6-1d0f803298b4","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BD3A65FDF4B7F419AF68A9F38C38B97CBB63BA5E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Restricted Sites zone.' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223099","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223099","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223099","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223099r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223099","rule_version":"DTBI575-IE11","rule_title":"Allow binary and script behaviors must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow binary and script behaviors' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow binary and script behaviors' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2000\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage dynamic binary and script behaviors of components that encapsulate specific functionality for HTML elements, to which they were attached. If you enable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.   If you select \"Administrator approved\" in the drop-down box, only the behaviors listed in the Admin-approved Behaviors under Binary Behaviors Security Restriction policy are available.    If you disable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are not available unless applications have implemented a custom security manager. If you do not configure this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59565","V-46701","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4888","uuid":"f7454407-0e4b-4474-b09b-ffb0b13aac47","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EA8390A7FC990E59365309FE9DD12A9C1EBF27F1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Allow binary and script behaviors must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223100","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223100","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223100","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223100r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223100","rule_version":"DTBI580-IE11","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59569","V-46705","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5776","uuid":"1e6fec6f-3979-42a6-86d9-67aec592d34c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223101","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223101","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223101","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","rule_id_src":"SV-223101r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223101","rule_version":"DTBI590-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced. (Reserved)","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Consistent Mime Handling -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Consistent Mime Handling -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting your network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59573","V-46709","CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"6962","uuid":"a0b22240-0854-406f-9c05-a4f7cbd87226","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 23DCA1402250869765A7EDE5A393F578B71C9AA7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced. (Reserved)' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223102","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223102","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223102","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","rule_id_src":"SV-223102r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223102","rule_version":"DTBI592-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Consistent Mime Handling -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Consistent Mime Handling -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to the organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59575","V-46711","CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"6464","uuid":"a1752a79-a9d0-4a02-a709-c109beb0348c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223103","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223103","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223103","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","rule_id_src":"SV-223103r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223103","rule_version":"DTBI594-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Consistent Mime Handling -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Consistent Mime Handling -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates that the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure that executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59577","V-46713","CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"5320","uuid":"e0e6861b-a2cb-46c8-a1c3-db2aec863114","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 31F1F985FAA20D528BE18643E08651EDEDA372EA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (iexplore).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223104","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223104","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223104","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","rule_id_src":"SV-223104r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223104","rule_version":"DTBI595-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends you configure this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59579","V-46715","CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"7262","uuid":"859853ef-82c8-47ac-ae90-b493aca72c11","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223105","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223105","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223105","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","rule_id_src":"SV-223105r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223105","rule_version":"DTBI596-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59581","V-46717","CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"5800","uuid":"65d11d11-d64f-4a6b-9c26-68abace98116","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223106","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223106","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223106","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","rule_id_src":"SV-223106r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223106","rule_version":"DTBI597-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59583","V-46719","CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"1203","uuid":"297b48ab-3b50-4ed2-a26f-636d479524fa","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 49674ABFDFC84733B08C857620C87CFE3BA1B044\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (iexplore).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223107","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223107","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223107","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223107r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223107","rule_version":"DTBI599-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> MK Protocol Security Restriction -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> MK Protocol Security Restriction -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59585","V-46721","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9365","uuid":"3d88ea36-b885-48e7-bdec-491ef1ccb138","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 97CB37BF1ABC0D002A5DEEA8F616B09B3C73CE0B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Reserved).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223108","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223108","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223108","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223108r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223108","rule_version":"DTBI600-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> MK Protocol Security Restriction -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> MK Protocol Security Restriction -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59587","V-46723","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7390","uuid":"e0cc2f9d-ccb6-4611-abc1-02adc79b581f","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 39F3DA41C9D917F40038503B637B1809F09ECE1D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Explorer).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223109","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223109","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223109","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223109r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223109","rule_version":"DTBI605-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> MK Protocol Security Restriction -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> MK Protocol Security Restriction -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59589","V-46725","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6390","uuid":"d2994e52-fea3-4dad-a5df-2e691e6ed06e","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 02D0791301A3A3BCA66F65CEBD6E5D9F6253F71C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (iexplore).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223110","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223110","title":"SRG-APP-000233","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223110","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","rule_id_src":"SV-223110r961131_rule","rule_id":"SV-223110","rule_version":"DTBI610-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Protection From Zone Elevation -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Protection From Zone Elevation -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59591","V-46727","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"1088","uuid":"65ad244a-da19-4114-b724-80f454e96c8e","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F17BFF5F6624C08422389CB0F839EB8F65CF0875\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Reserved).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223111","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223111","title":"SRG-APP-000233","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223111","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","rule_id_src":"SV-223111r961131_rule","rule_id":"SV-223111","rule_version":"DTBI612-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Protection From Zone Elevation -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Protection From Zone Elevation -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends configuring this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59593","V-46729","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"9490","uuid":"0c786b57-dd82-405d-a4b6-224192a90ba4","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DC8104C9B5F7A93DDDE86C179D7F955554684607\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Explorer).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223112","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223112","title":"SRG-APP-000233","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223112","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","rule_id_src":"SV-223112r961131_rule","rule_id":"SV-223112","rule_version":"DTBI614-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Protection From Zone Elevation -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Protection From Zone Elevation -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59595","V-46731","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"5543","uuid":"a3d85e7d-70cc-4815-90ec-43dac39b502a","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5FD21CF3D80DB627421AE89D210498AA5ABF81EB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (iexplore).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223113","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223113","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223113","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223113r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223113","rule_version":"DTBI630-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict File Download -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict File Download -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59597","V-46733","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3730","uuid":"c0d508a1-0633-4bca-9c53-92e17395ec62","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0FEBB0850DFDB65A2CD459F21869F84D66C7DD65\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Reserved).' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223114","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223114","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223114","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223114r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223114","rule_version":"DTBI635-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict File Download -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict File Download -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59645","V-46779","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2309","uuid":"89a1f463-b210-45d1-9368-858f6b3e5faf","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 44DFF91986CD06FCC7A26745043D172D03F2F081\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Explorer).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223115","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223115","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223115","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223115r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223115","rule_version":"DTBI640-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict File Download -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict File Download -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59647","V-46781","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2878","uuid":"7b24c661-6ad7-406f-91cd-98370319b4db","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1F6AADB360ED7C6D515BCD609D76416DA95B3686\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (iexplore).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223116","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223116","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223116","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223116r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223116","rule_version":"DTBI645-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Scripted Window Security Restrictions -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Scripted Window Security Restrictions -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force the user to interact with a window containing malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows, and create windows that hide other windows. Recommend configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59653","V-46787","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8493","uuid":"e0ee7c93-4c60-4a14-a2dd-f7e121ec526c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 46AF78E5DB7BDF0A501C5742761A0BDD6603334B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Reserved).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223117","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223117","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223117","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223117r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223117","rule_version":"DTBI647-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Scripted Window Security Restrictions -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Scripted Window Security Restrictions -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59655","V-46789","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6288","uuid":"365c0656-a7d3-4b62-bf5d-479c6949d959","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A7B52106C363053FCB82C0F0AEBEBFEF8D36B4AD\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Explorer).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223118","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223118","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223118","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223118r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223118","rule_version":"DTBI649-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Scripted Window Security Restrictions -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Scripted Window Security Restrictions -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59657","V-46791","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3622","uuid":"a0023a87-a010-4acd-b276-5af077b5e0fc","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223119","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223119","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223119","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223119r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223119","rule_version":"DTBI650-IE11","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59663","V-46797","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3866","uuid":"f5dc1d4f-b4bf-43d5-b946-5a8da5dafdd2","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9F139793B2AC96BD1E01382D65A61E2F7028E116\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for '.NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223120","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223120","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223120","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223120r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223120","rule_version":"DTBI655-IE11","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. It may be possible for malicious content hosted on a website to take advantage of these components. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59665","V-46799","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3064","uuid":"1123d443-12e4-41dc-8666-e0f0edf4296c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 191074183342BB4DCAD4EEDD665F728307D594E1\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by '.NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223121","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223121","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223121","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223121r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223121","rule_version":"DTBI670-IE11","rule_title":"Scripting of Java applets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Scripting of Java applets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Scripting of Java applets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applets are exposed to scripts within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are queried to choose whether to allow scripts to access applets. If you disable this policy setting, scripts are prevented from accessing applets. If you do not configure this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59667","V-46801","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8439","uuid":"b30356cf-10bc-43c4-9df5-e3ce5857ec6c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0AAA53459DC45FC2270DE7EAA27719927F699E2D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Scripting of Java applets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223122","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223122","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223122","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223122r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223122","rule_version":"DTBI690-IE11","rule_title":"AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Use FormSuggest\" is REG_SZ = no, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This AutoComplete feature suggests possible matches when users are filling in forms. It is possible that this feature will cache sensitive data and store it in the user's profile, where it might not be protected as rigorously as required by organizational policy. If you enable this setting, the user is not presented with suggested matches when filling in forms. If you disable this setting, the user is presented with suggested possible matches when filling forms. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom to turn on the auto-complete feature for forms. To display this option, the user opens the Internet Options dialog box, clicks the \"Contents\" tab, and clicks the \"Settings\" button.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59673","V-46807","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2752","uuid":"fb5e347e-8ad4-491c-8d74-656a7f7c3708","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 96133F8F6B848C9213E9B25C5F7F4698E1C751F5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223123","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223123","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223123","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223123r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223123","rule_version":"DTBI715-IE11","rule_title":"Crash Detection management must be enforced.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Turn off Crash Detection' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Turn off Crash Detection' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Restrictions Criteria: If the value \"NoCrashDetection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The 'Turn off Crash Detection' policy setting allows you to manage the crash detection feature of add-on management in Internet Explorer. A crash report could contain sensitive information from the computer's memory. If you enable this policy setting, a crash in Internet Explorer will be similar to one on a computer running Windows XP Professional Service Pack 1 and earlier, where Windows Error Reporting will be invoked. If you disable this policy setting, the crash detection feature in add-on management will be functional.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59677","V-46811","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4986","uuid":"4a4b3773-9fc9-41af-abd4-06c72082afe4","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8ECC683AAAF3256502D7D4EDB2B6C37EBF984FC5\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Crash Detection management must be enforced.' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223124","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223124","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223124","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223124r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223124","rule_version":"DTBI725-IE11","rule_title":"Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' to 'Disabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' must be 'Disabled'. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest Passwords\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding. AND Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest PW Ask\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls automatic completion of fields in forms on web pages. It is possible that malware could be developed which would be able to extract the cached user names and passwords from the currently logged on user, which an attacker could then use to compromise that user's online accounts.  If you enable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for\" User names and passwords on forms\" will be turned on. If you disable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for \"User names and passwords on forms\" is turned off. The user also cannot opt to be prompted to save passwords. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom of turning on Auto Complete for \"User name and passwords on forms\", and the option of prompting to save passwords.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59681","V-46815","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2235","uuid":"1a5e53c9-5d32-464c-87b0-fb6ba61ae418","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 252E23C20F93CAB8B0F0415AAE67F105CF4F1947\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223125","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223125","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223125","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","rule_id_src":"SV-223125r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223125","rule_version":"DTBI740-IE11","rule_title":"Managing SmartScreen Filter use must be enforced.","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"On\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"On\" selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnabledV9\" is \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting is important from a security perspective because Microsoft has extensive data illustrating the positive impact the SmartScreen filter has had on reducing the risk of malware infection via visiting malicious websites. This policy setting allows users to enable the SmartScreen Filter, which will warn if the website being visited is known for fraudulent attempts to gather personal information through 'phishing' or is known to host malware. If you enable this setting the user will not be prompted to enable the SmartScreen Filter. It must be specified which mode the SmartScreen Filter uses: On or Off. If the feature is On, all website addresses not contained on the filters allow list, will be sent automatically to Microsoft without prompting the user. If this feature is set to Off, the feature will not run. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user is prompted to decide whether to turn on SmartScreen Filter during the first-run experience.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59685","V-46819","CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"8537","uuid":"7f29f7a9-dc34-4707-a37a-74606f03751b","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1BA7F7E9B23D38B952AFFA3D43BA07F90637C5D0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Managing SmartScreen Filter use must be enforced.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223126","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223126","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223126","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","rule_id_src":"SV-223126r960879_rule","rule_id":"SV-223126","rule_version":"DTBI760-IE11","rule_title":"Browser must retain history on exit.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Delete Browsing History -> 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' to 'Disabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Delete Browsing History -> 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"ClearBrowsingHistoryOnExit\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Delete Browsing History on exit automatically deletes specified items when the last browser window closes.  Disabling this function will prevent users from deleting their browsing history, which could be used to identify malicious websites and files that could later be used for anti-virus and Intrusion Detection System (IDS) signatures.  Furthermore, preventing users from deleting browsing history could be used to identify abusive web surfing on government systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59695","V-46829","CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"2143","uuid":"d01f31a0-36b1-4c2d-a8c5-daca2f77d154","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 96A977E583DBA4A26E115D288B6F381F83CCD6CB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Browser must retain history on exit.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223127","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223127","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223127","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","rule_id_src":"SV-223127r960879_rule","rule_id":"SV-223127","rule_version":"DTBI770-IE11","rule_title":"Deleting websites that the user has visited must be disallowed.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Delete Browsing History -> 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Delete Browsing History -> 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"CleanHistory\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy prevents users from deleting the history of websites the user has visited. If you enable this policy setting, websites the user has visited will be preserved when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you disable this policy setting, websites that the user has visited will be deleted when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you do not configure this policy setting, the user will be able to select whether to delete or preserve websites the user visited when the user clicks \"Delete\".","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59707","V-46841","CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"1785","uuid":"ef8b80f5-7b25-407d-819e-562c2462e424","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C94B78A8CCED5AE16BA991F7B7884C06157D0434\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Deleting websites that the user has visited must be disallowed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223128","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223128","title":"SRG-APP-000080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223128","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","rule_id_src":"SV-223128r960864_rule","rule_id":"SV-223128","rule_version":"DTBI780-IE11","rule_title":"InPrivate Browsing must be disallowed.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Privacy -> 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Privacy -> 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"EnableInPrivateBrowsing\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"InPrivate Browsing lets the user control whether or not Internet Explorer saves the browsing history, cookies, and other data. User control of settings is not the preferred control method. The InPrivate Browsing feature in Internet Explorer makes browser privacy easy by not storing history, cookies, temporary Internet files, or other data. If you enable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be disabled. If you disable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be available for use. If you do not configure this setting, InPrivate Browsing can be turned on or off through the registry.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59713","V-46847","CCI-000166"],"reference_identifier":"7610","uuid":"fc701f53-21b3-4988-907c-502f6595393d","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C9AB35F43E1A71C27F76B29C603A0E66FEBF6E8A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'InPrivate Browsing must be disallowed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223129","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223129","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223129","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223129r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223129","rule_version":"DTBI800-IE11","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser control property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59715","V-46849","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4864","uuid":"dcbd893f-604b-40ca-a8bf-3b2e602b5337","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FCFC9E765CB1FE2B2EBE50855CC6062D406C210C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser control property must be disallowed (Internet zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223130","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223130","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223130","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223130r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223130","rule_version":"DTBI810-IE11","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59719","V-46853","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9642","uuid":"95b40c41-709b-402e-9633-e30ba6c06bf7","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 98E255D2BC9E09407832595CFFA7DF446E4B2FF7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223131","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223131","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223131","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223131r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223131","rule_version":"DTBI815-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features-> Notification Bar-> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features-> Notification Bar-> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59723","V-46857","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7476","uuid":"0e8610b5-d37e-4566-9302-2adbec0ebf07","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2B34ADD3140DBB7ED4180FFB5D5E6B5B8EAED472\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Reserved).' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223132","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223132","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223132","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223132r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223132","rule_version":"DTBI820-IE11","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be set to prompt (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Prompt' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Prompt' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \" Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59725","V-46859","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3327","uuid":"7386a32d-3b34-4961-841e-4bc450dca215","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E4A0233DE50D5371E4B2DBB3E4B26436647118D5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Security Warning for unsafe files must be set to prompt (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223133","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223133","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223133","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223133r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223133","rule_version":"DTBI825-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features-> Notification Bar-> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features-> Notification Bar-> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59727","V-46861","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3077","uuid":"596f72ea-9db9-4fa4-b9ff-a365d1cdfbd8","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 15ABB1319A5BF732B16B2B79EA776034789B6CBF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Explorer).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223134","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223134","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223134","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223134r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223134","rule_version":"DTBI830-IE11","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> ' Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59729","V-46865","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"9952","uuid":"021bc5fb-3975-4261-b18c-aeebf95f417a","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9A5710AF48D026D27EBC87269934A9BAF5A82F5B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223135","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223135","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223135","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223135r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223135","rule_version":"DTBI835-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features-> Notification Bar-> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features-> Notification Bar-> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59735","V-46869","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4477","uuid":"2a3387cb-f62c-47ab-b424-aabc5e818eeb","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 110F3F6942F47B526E187609F289BEBB97F75EE1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (iexplore).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223136","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223136","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223136","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223136r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223136","rule_version":"DTBI840-IE11","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter must be enforced (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59745","V-46879","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3891","uuid":"5eaffda7-80fe-4623-89cc-ccee54a8a3f8","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1DE7097DB3E6B7C29D9E2E32D6C9B28C5C35D0F0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Cross-Site Scripting Filter must be enforced (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223137","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223137","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223137","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223137r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223137","rule_version":"DTBI850-IE11","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser Control must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser Control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser Control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59749","V-46883","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3027","uuid":"b6d2a69a-b811-4d6a-adbc-2bc4f5f87334","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6A0C20ECE78B98851736E22DEF413B68A8D69ADD\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser Control must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223138","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223138","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223138","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223138r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223138","rule_version":"DTBI860-IE11","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59751","V-46885","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2859","uuid":"9dda12a7-0c7f-40bd-935c-738ecc1f06e5","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A80D8628E636F28C679129AD5A5B4F75D8652B2A\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Restricted Sites zone).' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223139","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223139","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223139","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223139r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223139","rule_version":"DTBI870-IE11","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \"Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59755","V-46889","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1099","uuid":"11a3c7a5-00fa-43b2-af3f-2aa9f7a2ac08","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F19F4FBADE53335CBE32A5607FB9929290CF87B8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Security Warning for unsafe files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' matches the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223140","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223140","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223140","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223140r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223140","rule_version":"DTBI880-IE11","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59759","V-46893","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"5152","uuid":"9db48e31-1683-4516-849a-b291d55ee259","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0EDF5FCACF6D722CEBF0F2900AF21BE52EDEE8E1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223141","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223141","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223141","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223141r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223141","rule_version":"DTBI890-IE11","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter property must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59761","V-46895","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1481","uuid":"d211d97e-c796-466b-b238-f07a0f07756b","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223142","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223142","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223142","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","rule_id_src":"SV-223142r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223142","rule_version":"DTBI900-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict ActiveX Install -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict ActiveX Install -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59763","V-46897","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"5667","uuid":"969beca0-de00-4f31-9534-a6eb641641da","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A4C79B8AC48D1C39DA7F92CD27A2DA2E4A8230B5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Reserved).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223143","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223143","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223143","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223143r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223143","rule_version":"DTBI910-IE11","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause them to perform an undesirable action. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59769","V-46903","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9642","uuid":"feebdf0f-ea5c-4b00-9683-8c16138ab8ef","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223144","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223144","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223144","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223144r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223144","rule_version":"DTBI920-IE11","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unsigned components are more likely to contain malicious code and it is more difficult to determine the author of the application - therefore they should be avoided if possible. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59773","V-46907","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3969","uuid":"9bcd9249-9ea5-4002-b0e5-3a1309706a3d","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B3667C8F3C51404CB357A3D09974ADE759911B05\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for '.NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223145","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223145","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223145","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223145r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223145","rule_version":"DTBI930-IE11","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It may be possible for someone to host malicious content on a website that takes advantage of these components. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59787","V-46921","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8275","uuid":"a1bcf534-d6bc-4b58-b4ee-414e98c719b1","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C438E03EF6BDE1B1E272017A5D7E7F5C42BA6B29\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for '.NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223146","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223146","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223146","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223146r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223146","rule_version":"DTBI940-IE11","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59793","V-46927","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7665","uuid":"919a07a9-937b-4945-92f1-f26c389fabaf","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223147","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223147","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223147","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223147r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223147","rule_version":"DTBI950-IE11","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause an undesirable action. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59805","V-46939","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1819","uuid":"0cedc7b2-c53d-4fb4-bee3-7d703f820656","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D169484E716F443FC18D6C79FC7191BE371F7B6B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223148","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223148","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223148","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223148r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223148","rule_version":"DTBI985-IE11","rule_title":"When Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled, ActiveX controls must be disallowed to run in Protected Mode.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"DisableEPMCompat\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting prevents ActiveX controls from running in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled. When a user has an ActiveX control installed that is not compatible with Enhanced Protected Mode and a website attempts to load the control, Internet Explorer notifies the user and gives the option to run the website in regular Protected Mode. This policy setting disables this notification and forces all websites to run in Enhanced Protected Mode. Enhanced Protected Mode provides additional protection against malicious websites by using 64-bit processes on 64-bit versions of Windows. For computers running at least Windows 8, Enhanced Protected Mode also limits the locations Internet Explorer can read from in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not give the user the option to disable Enhanced Protected Mode. All Protected Mode websites will run in Enhanced Protected Mode. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer notifies users and provides an option to run websites with incompatible ActiveX controls in regular Protected Mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59841","V-46975","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8193","uuid":"aed1be6e-22fc-4a41-8ef7-9e5888db6663","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B79169AB04A271286DDB8A03C6F9377CB9EAE2A2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'When Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled, ActiveX controls must be disallowed to run in Protected Mode.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-223149","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223149","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223149","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","rule_id_src":"SV-223149r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223149","rule_version":"DTBI990-IE11","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2709\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when both the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59847","V-46981","CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"3893","uuid":"57c2cb89-ae84-402b-b7fc-b0d50e272063","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C5E4EEE77D0D2B5C0DBFDDEAA611ECD44A5A83C3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Internet zone).' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-250540","group_tree":[{"id":"V-250540","title":"SRG-APP-000416","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-250540","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000416","rule_id_src":"SV-250540r1117186_rule","rule_id":"SV-250540","rule_version":"DTBI014-IE11","rule_title":"Turn off Encryption Support must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Advanced Page >> \"Turn off Encryption Support\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nSelect only \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Advanced Page >> \"Turn off Encryption Support\" must be \"Enabled\".\n\nVerify the only option selected is \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings!SecureProtocols.\n\nCriteria: If the value for \"SecureProtocols\" is not REG_DWORD = \"2048\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DOD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by allowing the user to turn on/off support for TLS and SSL. TLS is a protocol for protecting communications between the browser and the target server. When the browser attempts to set up a protected communication with the target server, the browser and server negotiate which protocol and version to use. The browser and server attempt to match each other's list of supported protocols and versions and pick the most preferred match.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-59337","V-46473","CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"8421","uuid":"0f49ba4f-37fd-4741-a9d8-072953e6aa9c","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BC41514D2ACDFDE6F3715D0AE33701CCC1A561A4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Turn off Encryption Support must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-250541","group_tree":[{"id":"V-250541","title":"SRG-APP-000416","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-250541","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000416","rule_id_src":"SV-250541r1117186_rule","rule_id":"SV-250541","rule_version":"DTBI1100-IE11","rule_title":"Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer) must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Security Features >> \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"No Sites\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Security Features >> \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"No Sites\" selected from the drop-down box. If \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" is not \"Enabled\" or any other drop-down option is selected, this is a finding. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableSSL3Fallback\" is REG_DWORD=0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DoD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by blocking an insecure fallback to SSL when TLS 1.0 or greater fails.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-79219","V-64729","CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"7587","uuid":"54901f08-8e98-4691-94f5-77f1a0272454","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 47654FDE664C4BF31717EFA39AB114E3A9DAC82B\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer) must be disabled.' is not present or not in use on this Internet Explorer 11."},{"group_id_src":"V-252910","group_tree":[{"id":"V-252910","title":"SRG-APP-000456","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-252910","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","rule_id_src":"SV-252910r1192839_rule","rule_id":"SV-252910","rule_version":"DTBI999-IE11","rule_title":"The version of Internet Explorer running on the system must be a supported version.","fix_text":"Disable the Internet Explorer 11 application. Open PowerShell as an Administrator and run the command (this is irreversible):\n\ndism /online /Remove-Capability /CapabilityName:Browser.InternetExplorer~~~~0.0.11.0\n\nRestart the system for the changes to take effect.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Internet Explorer 11 is no longer supported by the vendor with the exception of some operating system versions under extended support (Ex: Windows Server 2019).\n\nTo determine the status of Internet Explorer 11 on the system, open PowerShell as an Administrator and run the command:\n\ndism /online /get-capabilityinfo /capabilityname:Browser.InternetExplorer~~~~0.0.11.0\n\nWithin the returned results, if \"State : Installed\", this is a finding.\n\nWithin the returned results, if \"State : Not Present\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf the host operating system is supported under an extended support agreement, and \"State : Installed\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf nothing related to Internet Explorer is returned, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously.\n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw).\n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality, will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means the time period used must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may depend on the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002605"],"reference_identifier":"8968","uuid":"6ebf0734-fdc2-449d-a139-8274e4619864","stig_uuid":"7479966e-65be-42b3-9e62-7b21ff59c90b","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 72399CB39009A6E962EAACF527782F0A41878BA9\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The version of Internet Explorer running on the system must be a supported version.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Internet Explorer 11."}]}],"target_data":{"target_type":"Computing","host_name":"LEGACY-WIN7-01","ip_address":"10.30.7.10","mac_address":"00:1C:42:01:00:28","fqdn":"legacy-win7-01.utsec.mil","comments":"","role":"Workstation","is_web_database":false,"technology_area":"None","web_db_site":"","web_db_instance":"","classification":""},"title":"Evaluate-STIG_COMBINED"}